(11, 4, 1, 74, 'coronavirus-hospital-staff-prepare-for-possible-second-wave-1598296542', 'Coronavirus: Hospital staff prepare for possible second wave', 0, '<p>Staff inside a north Wales hospital have attracted patients and individuals to &quot;continue listening and sticking with the the guidelines&quot; simply because they prepare for a possible second wave of Covid-19.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The newest figures show Betsi Cadwaladr health board has observed a rise in deaths in comparison with other health boards.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But staff at Ysbyty Gwynedd in Bangor mentioned lots of people &quot;seem to think about the pandemic is finished&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The board mentioned it absolutely was progressively resuming normal services for patients.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It&#39;s seen a greater quantity of instances in Wrexham, that have the finest weekly volume of coronavirus-related deaths.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Interim leader Simon Dean mentioned the board was &quot;ready for a boost in cases&quot;, getting elevated bed capacity in hospitals, recruiting staff and established the three Ysbyty Enfys field hospitals.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Patients requiring urgent care received priority, whatever the effect the pandemic has received on services, he added.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;We have prioritised our waiting lists to make certain access for patients to treatment according to clinical priorities.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At Ysbyty Gwynedd hospital, receptionist Carol Ann Manley mentioned there is a &quot;mixture of feelings and responses&quot; from patients and visitors.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Most are still nervous plus a little afraid... possibly too afraid. Other people are too confident and appearance to think about the pandemic is finished therefore we know it isn&#39;t,&quot; she mentioned.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Nursing director Mandy Manley mentioned these are actually challenging occasions on her behalf team: &quot;At this time we have many userful stuff within the very first wave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I am c