(66, 4, 6, 40, 'seaweed-the-foodstuff-and-fuel-for-future-years-1598729385', 'Seaweed: The foodstuff and fuel for future years?', 0, '<p>Sunshine has provided method to rain and wind, because the motorboat chugs via a fjord within the Faroe Islands.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Its a little windy here,&quot; states Olavur Gregarsen. &quot;We&#39;ll observe how far we are able to arrive at the harvesting boat.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We soon achieve a sheltered place where steep mountain tops are searching lower on countless buoys bobbing within the ocean.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;They&#39;re supporting a horizontal line,&quot; explains Mr Gregarsen, the md of Sea Rainforest, a seaweed producer. &quot;At each metre another line hangs lower, and that is in which the seaweed grows.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Breaking waves</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Moored towards the ocean floor, the cultivation rig includes 50,000m (164,000ft) of underwater lattice-like ropes, made to withstand rough ocean conditions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;The primary structure is 10m lower. This way we steer clear of the largest breaking waves,&quot; he states.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Regardless of the Danish territory&#39;s remote North Atlantic location, Mr Gregarsen states the deep, nutrient-wealthy, waters are perfect for growing seaweed, having a stable temperature which is between 6C and 11C.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>His firm is one kind of a wave of seaweed farms which have popped up in Europe and The United States, spurred with a growing demand in the food industry yet others.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;You&#39;ve got a biomass you can use for food and feed, and replacing fossil-based items like packaging material from plastic,&quot; he states.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mechanisation</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Seaweeds are fast-growing algae. They utilise energy from sunlight, and occupy nutrients and co2 in the seawater. Scientists suggest seaweed may help fight global warming and offset carbon emissions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sea Rainforest lately won funding in the US United states doe to construct an identical system in California, where there&#39;s curiosity about developing industrialised seaweed production for future biofuels.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Aboard the harvesting boat the skipper controls an analog arm that lifts lines in the water. The seaweed is chopped free, filling containers. It&#39;s quick but untidy work. The line is then left to regrow. This season about 200 tonnes is going to be harvested.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But the organization is scaling up, and intends to double its capacity this season. It is not earning money at this time, but expects to soon, Mr Gregarsen informs me.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;We are able to observe how we are able to mechanise this, how the largest mtss is a really large-scale efficient activity,&quot; he states.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;There are hardly any firms that do that like a lucrative business, or no.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cosmetics and medicines</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Seaweed must be processed rapidly. In a small plant within the Faroese village of Kaldbak, machines clean the harvest. Some is dried and provided to food manufacturers. The remainder is fermented and shipped to animal feed producers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Most farmed seaweed is ingested in food, but extracts are utilized in a multitude of products. Whether it&#39;s tooth paste, cosmetics, medicines or commercial dog food, these frequently contain hydrocolloids produced from seaweed, that have gelling or thickening qualities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>And much more goods are coming, along with other firms focusing on textiles and plastic alternatives, including biodegradable packaging, water capsules, and consuming straws.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Seaweed production has boomed. Between 2005 and 2015 volumes bending, surpassing Thirty Dollars million tonnes yearly, reports the UN&#39;s Food and Agriculture Organization. It is a business a bigger factor than $6bn (&pound;5bn) worldwide.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Yet only a part of cultivation happens outdoors Asia, where farming can be a extended-established, but mostly work-intensive activity.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&#39;A great deal of effort&#39;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;The job cost is over the top in Europe, so that&#39;s one primary problem with it,&quot; explains Annette Bruhn, who&#39;s a senior investigator at Aarhus College in Denmark.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Plenty of effort should be place in mechanisation and upscaling.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To produce farming economical, she states &quot;the yield must increase as well as the cost must come down&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But farming systems aren&#39;t easily replicated. &quot;Different areas in a variety of waters, all require modifications. There is not one solution which may be prone to fit all,&quot; states Ms Bruhn.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, she&#39;s hopeful, and states you will find &quot;many areas where one can have breakthroughs&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is exactly what innovators like Sintef are attempting to do. The Norwegian research group is focusing on technology to streamline farming.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Now the majority of the seaweed can be used for food, but later on you want to apply it fish feed, fertilisers, biogas. We want bulk and we have to produce considerably faster,&quot; states research researcher Silje Forbord.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dry lab</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Prototype machines like the &quot;seaweed spinner&quot; instantly wrap spools of seedling-transporting threads onto lines, ready for deployment at ocean.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Another concept, SPoke (Standardized Manufacture of Algae), includes circular farm modules where seaweed grows from lines radiating outwards. It&#39;s designed so a robotic can move across the wheel-like spokes - either attaching threads transporting juvenile seaweed or harvesting it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;We have built one arm having a robot going backwards and forwards. That&#39;s been tested inside a dry lab,&quot; explains Ms Forbord, but more investment is going to be needed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ms Abreu does not think accessibility to land is really a restricting factor. Former salt works and fish farms might be repurposed, she states, mentioning you will find hectares of availability in Portugal, France, Italia, A holiday in greece and Poultry.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Onshore seaweed farming happens in Canada and Nigeria too. Micro-algae will also be grown in tank systems.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But there are more challenges.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;The primary bottleneck is energy cost. Dealing with tanks you&#39;ll need the pumping and also the aeration to help keep water moving,&quot; states Ms Abreu.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The firm can&#39;t survive on sales alone at this time. But Ms Abreu thinks the seaweed market continuously grow.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;It is a huge trend,&quot; she states. &quot;Each year there&#39;s increasingly more companies. You will find newcomers in most steps from the value chain.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'Seaweed, foodstuff and fuel for future years', '_113789068_seaweed.landscape_1598729385.jpg', '2020-08-29 23:29:45', '2021-08-14 22:40:58'),
(72, 4, 4, 19, 'tour-de-france-2020-alexander-kristoff-wins-stage-one-1598733027', 'Tour de France 2020: Alexander Kristoff wins stage one', 0, '<p>Alexander Kristoff timed his sprint finish perfectly to win the outlet stage from the Tour de France in Nice.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Following a large group crashed within the final 3km, Norwegian Kristoff, 33, surged home inside a sprint also involving Ireland&#39;s Mike Bennett, who had been 4th.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Rain made the roads treacherous and brought to many crashes, with Pavel Sivakov of Team Ineos two times coming off.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ineos&#39; protecting champion Egan Bernal largely prevented the problem and handle securely within the peloton.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Colombia&#39;s Nairo Quintana crashed, while Astana&#39;s decision to in the pace around the final descent from Levens saw Miguel Angel Lopez slide right into a road sign and motivated some stern exchanges for the team using their company riders within the peloton.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ineos&#39; Luke Rowe known as Astana&#39;s move &quot;pretty stupid&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I must say &#39;chapeau&#39; towards the whole peloton - minus Astana hitting it lower one climb and, consequently, their leader remained on his back,&quot; the British rider stated.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>France&#39;s Julian Alaphilippe seemed to be caught inside a crash, while compatriot Thibaut Pinot - among the race favourites - fell heavily for the finish and folded within the line having a ripped jersey.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, since the crash happened within the final 3km, he was credited with similar time because the group he was riding with, so wound up losing virtually no time on his rivals for that overall win.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The riders face a 186km mountainous second stage on Sunday, with two climbs above 1,500m.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &#39;Definitely a general change in yellow on stage two&#39; - Adam Yates&#39; stage guide</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Stage one because it happened</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&#39;It means a great deal in my career&#39;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Veteran Kristoff&#39;s newest stage win in the Tour came around the Champs-Elysees in Paris around the final stage from the 2018 race.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>While couple of expected him to win on Saturday, the very first rain in Nice since June labored in the favour as a number of his rivals, including Bennett and Australia&#39;s Caleb Ewan, were distracted by crashes around the 156km route.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Surging from the wheel of Peter Sagan, UAE-Team Emirates rider Kristoff held off Mads Pedersen and Cees Bol to assert another memorable victory - his 4th in the Tour - and something that saw him collect the very first yellow jersey of his career.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I usually imagined about putting on it,&quot; he told ITV4. &quot;It is now an aspiration coming true. You can&#39;t imagine a much better start.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;We didn&#39;t be prepared to win the sprint however i felt really strong and visiting the road I figured I would win.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;The boys stored me safe throughout the stage. I had been located on Sagan for any lengthy time. In the finish I had been the most powerful also it was an incredible moment for me personally.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;This means a great deal in my career. I&#39;m 33, have kids however i can continue to perform using the best.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Stage one result</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Alexander Kristoff (Nor/UAE-Team Emirates) 3hrs 46mins 23seconds</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Mads Pedersen (Living room/Trek-Segafredo) Same time</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Cees Bol (Ned/Sunweb)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. Mike Bennett (Ire/Deceuninck-Quick Step)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. Peter Sagan (Slo/Bora-Hansgrohe)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>6. Elia Viviani (Ita/Cofidis)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>7. Giacomo Nizzolo (Ita/NTT)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>8. Bryan Coquard (Fra/B&amp;B)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>9. Anthony Turgis (Fra/Total Direct Energie)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>10. Jasper Stuyen (Bel/Trek-Segafredo)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>General classification after stage one</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Alexander Kristoff (Nor/UAE-Team Emirates) 3hrs 46mins 23seconds</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Mads Pedersen (Living room/Trek-Segafredo)&nbsp; 4secs</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Cees Bol (Ned/Sunweb)&nbsp; 6secs</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. Mike Bennett (Ire/Deceuninck-Quick Step)&nbsp; 10secs</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. Peter Sagan (Slo/Bora-Hansgrohe)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>6. Elia Viviani (Ita/Cofidis)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>7. Giacomo Nizzolo (Ita/NTT)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>8. Bryan Coquard (Fra/B&amp;B)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>9. Anthony Turgis (Fra/Total Direct Energie)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>10. Jasper Stuyen (Bel/Trek-Segafredo)</p>', 'Tour de France 2020, Alexander Kristoff', '_114174580_hi063086634_1598733027.jpg', '2020-08-30 00:30:27', '2021-05-27 14:49:18'),
(73, 4, 4, 33, 'football-arsenel-vs-liverpool-1598770468', 'Football: Arsenel VS Liverpool', 1, '<p>Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang scored an excellent goal and netted the winning penalty inside a shootout as Arsenal beat Premier League champions Liverpool locally Shield in an empty Wembley Stadium.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Liverpool striker Rhian Brewster, introduced on in stoppage time, hit the crossbar together with his penalty - the only person not converted within the shootout.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Aubameyang&#39;s curling strike gave FA Cup winners Arsenal charge within the first half before Liverpool substitute Takumi Minamino equalised following the break.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Minamino&#39;s flicked pass to Mohamed Salah bounced back kindly for him to fit home from close range.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There is a fast VAR look for handball by Salah however the replay demonstrated no obvious contact.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It&#39;s the second year consecutively Liverpool have forfeit on penalties after Manchester City&#39;s victory in 2019.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Aubameyang leads Arsenal to maneuver silverware</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Aubameyang&#39;s importance to Arsenal used to be again proven in another impressive performance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Gabon worldwide, who scored two times within the FA Cup final in the same stadium this month, cut inside in the left and whipped the ball in to the far corner in emphatic style to spread out the scoring.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He ongoing to terrorise Liverpool&#39;s defence, exposing youthful right-back Neco Johnson.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>So when Aubameyang walked up to accept final penalty, using the score 4-4 within the shootout, there wasn&#39;t any way he would miss.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He&#39;s netted 71 goals in 110 Arsenal appearances with no Gunners player has scored greater than his five goals in the venue.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Arsenal boss Mikel Arteta stated on Friday he was &quot;pretty confident&quot; the skipper will sign a brand new contract following a lengthy, painful watch for supporters.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After lifting their second bit of silverware inside a month, it might cap off a really pleasing summer time for Arsenal if Aubameyang does eventually put pen to paper.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Stuttering Liverpool are unsuccessful again</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Liverpool were without regular starters Trent Alexander-Arnold and Jordan Henderson however they fielded a side many would feel were able to beating Arsenal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>They began off around the front feet, with Sadio Mane getting into behind on numerous occasions around the left and linking track of full-back Andy Robertson.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But sloppiness crept to their game because the first half used on - Virgil van Dijk berated Georginio Wijnaldum and Fabinho on separate occasions for giving the ball away too easily in midfield.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Arsenal&#39;s Ainsley Maitland-Niles was impressive and caused problems, while Bukayo Saka was busy around the Liverpool box.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, Liverpool had lots of chances to attain. An unmarked James Milner headed within the bar, Van Dijk almost got around the finish of the Mane flick-on and Roberto Firmino had the ball within the internet, only so that it is eliminated for offside.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Liverpool increased more dominant within the other half - Minamino deservedly came them level using more than fifteen minutes to experience - but they couldn&#39;t look for a champion.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Arsenal&#39;s Joe Willock were built with a brilliant chance to really make it 2-1 with 5 minutes to visit as he miscued his header following Cedric Soares&#39; mix in the right.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Liverpool manager Jurgen Klopp introduced off Wijnaldum, who&#39;d his penalty held in last year&#39;s shootout by City, and replaced him with 20-year-old Brewster, however the England youth worldwide crashed his place-start the bar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There&#39;s certainly you don&#39;t need to panic however the air of invincibility Liverpool had throughout the majority of the 2019-20 league campaign has worn out in recent several weeks carrying out a patch of two defeats along with a attract seven games in the finish of year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Man from the match - Ainsley Maitland-Niles</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&#39;You never get accustomed to winning&#39; - the things they stated</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Arsenal boss Mikel Arteta, talking with BT Sport: &quot;You won&#39;t ever get accustomed to winning. I understood the task we faced today from this incredible opponent. Thanks to you towards the players for that effort and gratifaction.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;The courage from the team, how aggressive i was with no ball and from the Liverpool press. I&#39;m pleased and understood within the other half we&#39;d suffer. However in the penalties we&#39;d courage to complete them right.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Within the last ten minutes we required the ball and performed within the final third. I&#39;m pleased the way they competed. It makes belief.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Liverpool manager Jurgen Klopp, talking with BT Sport: &quot;We deserved the equaliser and may have scored more but we did not do this.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Whenever you play against a formation such as this then you have to be really fresh within the final third and you have to pressure it, create angles. The rhythm for your fell a bit. Today it wasn&#39;t enough.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Penalty shootout domination - the very best of the stats</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Arsenal have won the city Shield for any 16th time (including shared titles), overtaking opponents Liverpool (15 occasions) and just behind Manchester U . s . (21). The Gunners have won the trophy in four from the last seven seasons.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Liverpool are the initial side ever to get rid of the city Shield on penalties at the spine-to-back years this is the very first time the Reds have took part in your competition two times in 2 seasons without winning it (including shared) because the 1983 and 1984 matches.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Arsenal have won the city Shield as FA Cup winners seven occasions (including as league/cup double winners and including shared titles) - greater than every other side. All of their last four Community Shield victories came as FA Cup winners.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Those are the just the second side to win the city Shield following a penalty shootout more often than once, after Manchester U . s . (five occasions).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Arsenal have won nine of the last 11 penalty shootouts in most competitions, including two locally Shield. Meanwhile, Liverpool have forfeit three of the last five shootouts, including two locally Shield.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Aubameyang has become Arsenal&#39;s joint-top scorer in games performed at Wembley Stadium (5, level with Alexis Sanchez). Aubameyang&#39;s five goals in the ground came in just just 42 days.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Only Kevin De Bruyne (22) and Trent Alexander-Arnold (15) have given more assists for Premier League sides in most competitions since the beginning of last season than Arsenal&#39;s Bukayo Saka (13).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Minamino may be the first player to attain his first goal for Liverpool at Wembley, netting this goal in the 15th appearance with his twelfth shot for that Reds in most competitions.</p>', 'Football News, Arsenel VS Liverpool', '_114175174_gettyimages-1269531660_1598733630.jpg', '2020-08-30 00:40:30', '2021-07-22 07:25:59'),
(74, 4, 4, 80, 'england-conor-coady-ainsley-maitland-niles-called-up-by-gareth-southgate-1598734276', 'England: Conor Coady & Ainsley Maitland-Niles called up by Gareth Southgate', 0, '<p>Baby wolves captain Conor Coady and Arsenal full-back Ainsley Maitland-Niles happen to be put into Gareth Southgate&#39;s England squad for that Nations League games against Iceland and Denmark.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Baby wolves center-back Coady, 27, has performed every Premier League game for his side within the last two seasons.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Maitland-Niles was man from the match on Saturday and scored within the shootout as Arsenal beat Liverpool to win the city Shield on his 23rd birthday.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It&#39;s a first call-up for players.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Have symbolized England at youth level - Coady captaining his side towards the 2010 European Under-17 Championship and Maitland-Niles winning the 2017 Under-20 World Cup.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>England&#39;s players will come across up at St George&#39;s Park on Monday.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Southgate&#39;s side face their Euro 2016 conquerors Iceland in Reykjavik on 5 September before playing Denmark in Copenhagen 72 hours later.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The disruption caused towards the football calendar by coronavirus, including Euro 2020 being delayed with a year until 2021, means England haven&#39;t performed since November 2019, whenever a 4- win in Kosovo concluded their Euro 2020 qualification campaign.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Coady is really a direct substitute for Harry Maguire, who had been withdrawn in the squad by manager Southgate on Tuesday after receiving a suspended prison sentence around the Greek island of Syros.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Manchester U . s . captain, who had been in prison for irritated assault, fighting off arrest and repeated attempts of bribery, has since appealed from the decision, meaning the conviction continues to be nullified in compliance with Greek law.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He told the BBC he feared for his existence and thought he had been kidnapped throughout the incident on Mykonos.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Southgate stated withdrawing Maguire was &quot;within the needs of parties&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>England squad</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Goalkeepers: Dean Henderson, Jordan Pickford, Nick Pope.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Defenders: Trent Alexander-Arnold, Conor Coady, Eric Dier, Joe Gomez, Michael Keane, Ainsley Maitland-Niles, Tyrone Mings, Kieran Trippier, Kyle Master.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Midfielders: Phil Foden, Mason Mount, Kalvin Phillips, Declan Grain, James Ward-Prowse, Harry Winks.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Forwards: Tammy Abraham, Mason Greenwood, Danny Ings, Harry Kane, Marcus Rashford, Jadon Sancho, Raheem Sterling.</p>', 'England Football', '_114175509_ipiccy-collage_1598734276.jpg', '2020-08-30 00:51:16', '2021-08-17 21:46:08'),
(75, 4, 4, 27, 'novak-djokovic-beats-milos-raonic-to-win-western-and-southern-open-1598735208', 'Novak Djokovic beats Milos Raonic to win Western and Southern Open', 0, '<p>World number 1 Novak Djokovic stored up his unbeaten record in 2020 having a 1-6 6-3 6-4 victory over Milos Raonic to win the Western and Southern Open.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Serb, 33, equalled Rafael Nadal&#39;s record of 35 Masters 1000 Series titles using the comeback win in New You are able to.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Canadian Raonic, the planet number 30, required the very first occur 31 minutes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But Djokovic levelled before originating from 2- lower towards the 29-year-old within the deciding set to clinch his 80th ATP title in precisely two hrs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Since the development of the Masters 1000 in &#39;09, Djokovic may be the only player to assert all nine occasions - referred to as Career Golden Masters - which victory means he&#39;s achieved the task two times.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Raonic, an old world number 3, won all of the his eight ATP titles in 2016 and it was trying to end up being the first unseeded champion from the event.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He&#39;d not beaten Djokovic in 10 previous conferences but created some superb strokeplay to dominate the outlet set.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Djokovic performed a long match from the tournament as he required greater than three hrs to conquer Roberto Bautista Agut in Friday&#39;s semi-final and highlighted his stamina and resolve again to increase his record in 2020 to 23-.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The big event is generally locked in Ohio but continues to be switched to New You are able to to lessen unnecessary player travel prior to the US Open within the same city beginning on Monday.</p>', 'Novak Djokovic, Milos Raonic', '_114175249_hi063088526_1598735208.jpg', '2020-08-30 01:06:48', '2021-06-08 19:13:53'),
(76, 4, 4, 58, 'lewis-hamilton-on-pole-position-at-belgian-grand-prix-1598735407', 'Lewis Hamilton on pole position at Belgian Grand Prix', 0, '<p>Championship leader Lewis Hamilton is on pole position for that Belgian Grand Prix, finishing half another obvious of Mercedes team-mate Valtteri Bottas.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Hamilton was fastest on laps within the final qualifying session and beat Bottas by .511secs. Red Bull&#39;s Max Verstappen was .015secs from the Finn.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Daniel Ricciardo excelled with 4th put on the grid, in front of the second Red Bull of Alexander Albon.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ferrari battled, Charles Leclerc and Sebastian Vettel lower in 13th and 14th.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Belgian Grand Prix qualifying results</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Response to Hamilton&#39;s Belgian GP pole</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Hamilton&#39;s performance was certainly one of his most impressive, because he required his 93rd pole with two laps in another dimension as to the Bottas could manage.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On his first, Hamilton was .578secs obvious of his team-mate, and even though Bottas improved on his second run, so did the Briton.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Over team radio following the lap on Saturday, he dedicated his performance towards the actor Chadwick Boseman, most well-known because the star from the Black Panther film, who died of cancer of the colon overnight.</p>', 'Lewis Hamilton, Belgian Grand Prix', '_114173307_lewishamilton_1598735407.jpg', '2020-08-30 01:10:07', '2021-08-16 01:36:02'),
(77, 4, 4, 28, 'lionel-messi-man-city-psg-juventus-whats-the-latest-transfer-situation-1598807527', 'Lionel Messi: Man City, PSG, Juventus - what\'s the latest transfer situation?', 0, '<p>As speaking percentages then Manchester City are extremely much within the driving seat to become Lionel Messi&#39;s next club.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Paris St-Germain will be in touch with Messi&#39;s father, his agent, again about the potential of filling out the Barcelona captain, who posted a transfer request on Tuesday.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>And, possibly most intriguingly of, Juventus are actually searching in the hugely unlikely scenario of organising some very daring financial deals and sponsorships that may see Messi and Cristiano Ronaldo playing together the very first time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Exactly what a mouth-watering prospect that might be. But it&#39;s also hard.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Where could Messi go next?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Man City trio to remain despite Messi speculation</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the finish of the week of numerous headlines and rumours, there&#39;s two things we all know above other things: Messi greatly really wants to leave Barcelona and Barcelona would just like him the Argentina forward stay.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>That element is straightforward, however it promises to become a lot more complicated scenario because each side are absolutely convinced the &#39;10 June clause&#39; - the one which enables Messi to depart free of charge - provides them the authority to defend their position.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Messi thinks he is able to leave for free because that date was supposed to have been, effectively, the finish of year. However, the coronavirus pandemic meant the campaign wound up finishing using the Champions League final on 23 August, 2 days before Messi let Barcelona know his intentions within an official way (more about that later).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Barca firmly believe time for him to declare need to leave has passed which the 33-year-old is contracted before the finish of 2020-21.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The lawyers is going to be licking their lips in anticipation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>From Messi&#39;s side nothing has altered. He want to leave around the best terms possible.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Barcelona have stated the gamer isn&#39;t for purchase - unless of course obviously someone thinks it&#39;s worth spending the 700m euros required to trigger his buyout clause at this time - and find out no reason in almost any further conferences for the time being.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Messi doesn&#39;t wish to depart inside a bad way, not due to the board and surely due to the respect he&#39;s for that club as well as their fans.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lots of people have centered on the burofax delivered to tell Barcelona of his intention to depart, claiming it had been a disrespectful method of handing in the notice. It had been nothing like that. It had been confirmation - a kind of recorded delivery - that informed the club on paper what Messi had said excitedly verbally on numerous occasions since he stopped contract renewal negotiations around March.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It had been only a logical step on the way, having a meeting to try and arrange an amiable exit the following logical step. Messi&#39;s strategy continues to be unchanged throughout. The modification could be if he made the decision to visit war using the club.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Argentine doesn&#39;t have intends to make any statements within the immediate future, definitely not while you may still find a lot of things to go over and things are up in mid-air. When things begin to relocate the best direction for him, Messi will be ready to explain his feelings, although not before.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Players need to do their pre-season tests on Sunday after which training starts on Monday.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Rumours Manchester City would be ready to let any regular starters go in return for Messi are way from the mark. Defenders Angelino or Eric Garcia could feature inside a deal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>No club will probably be capable of paying a transfer fee of 100m euros plus Messi&#39;s salary, even considering his wages will disappear wherever he goes next.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Barcelona won&#39;t pay a swap of players they don&#39;t want anybody from City. They don&#39;t want to market and would only be ready to meet Messi to be able to renew his contract, to not negotiate a means out.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Everyone is positioning on obvious terms. Everything helps make the resolution impossible to calculate.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Josep Maria Bartomeu clearly doesn&#39;t wish to be the Barcelona president who lets Messi go.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But who&#39;s he considering? Definitely not the club because, as things stand, he intends to keep an unsatisfied player who not wish to be there and who might opt for free in 12 several weeks.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Messi&#39;s departure allows Barcelona to allow other players develop and grow pick up.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>And just what players they&#39;re. Frenkie de Jong, Miralem Pjanic, Antoine Griezmann, Ousmane Dembele, Philippe Coutinho, Gerard Pique and Marc-Andre Ter Stegen to mention only a couple of.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>They will have to purchase a strong central midfielder along with a center-back either now or soon, but that&#39;s entirely doable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To insist upon not letting Messi leave shows short-sightedness for Bartomeu.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We wait to determine what goes on next, beginning with whether Messi appears for training on Monday.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'Lionel Messi', '_114173402_messi_1598807525.jpg', '2020-08-30 21:12:07', '2021-07-28 18:03:34'),
(78, 4, 4, 31, 'england-v-pakistan-eoin-morgan-stars-as-his-side-win-by-five-wickets-1598811406', 'England v Pakistan: Eoin Morgan stars as his side win by five wickets', 0, '<p>England brilliantly chased 196 to conquer Pakistan by five wickets within the second Twenty20 worldwide at Emirates Old Trafford.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Captain Eoin Morgan smashed a 33-ball 66 and Dawid Malan was 55 not out as England completed their third greatest chase with five balls to spare.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The happy couple placed on 112 from 62 deliveries after England had lost opener Jonny Bairstow and Tom Banton in successive balls to leg-spinner Shadab Khan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With 18 needed England briefly stuttered, losing Morgan and Moeen Ali in just six balls, however the composed Malan saw England home.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It had been another fine batting performance from England&#39;s white-colored-ball outfit - the greatest chase by side against Pakistan in T20s.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Additionally, it composed for any ragged bowling performance which saw Mohammad Hafeez propel Pakistan for their total having a 69 from 36 balls.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>England, who&#39;ve won their past five T20 series, will require single- lead into Tuesday&#39;s series finale.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Morgan and Malan lead another stunning England chase</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the midway stage, it appeared as if England&#39;s bowling would cost them. Rather, Morgan and Malan required these to victory with outstanding ease.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It had been England&#39;s second chase well over 190 this season, getting made 226-5 to conquer Nigeria in Feb.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bairstow and Banton gave England a platform - their 66-run opening stand originating from 6.2 overs - but Morgan and Malan combined for any partnership filled with skill and experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Morgan narrowly survived an lbw appeal in Shadab&#39;s wicket-overtaking, an umpire&#39;s ask impact saw the not on-field decision stand, and later on he required charge of the sport brilliantly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He and Malan required time for you to play themselves in before you take 18 in the twelfth to reignite the chase.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pakistan were hampered by losing Mohammad Amir to injuries and also the England pair peppered the boundary effortlessly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Morgan holed on the fine leg boundary within the 17th over and Moeen chipped to mid-wicket, however the stand meant despite the late stutter an England win looked likely from the lengthy way to avoid it. Malan fittingly hit the winning runs having a fine four through cover.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Hafeez assault shows England bowling attack still needs work</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Malan is among the players attempting to cement his devote the XI and take full advantage of the lack of the regulars who&#39;re away using the Test squad. He required his chance excellently but bowlers didn&#39;t.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The seamers, Saqib Mahmood, Tom Curran and Chris Jordan, started waywardly, allowing Babar Azam and Fakhar Zaman to use a prompt 72-run opening stand with relative ease.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The ever-reliable Adil Rashid ignored both - Fakhar skied a catch to lengthy-on for 36 and Babar hit a brief ball to deep mid-wicket for 56 - but he offered up boundary possibilities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The pitch demonstrated to become a great one but England&#39;s tactics appeared poor. Their cutters and short balls were frequently hit towards the rope - Hafeez the primary beneficiary.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>England chosen yorkers late on also it demonstrated effective. Additionally, it elevated questions why England didn&#39;t make use of the tactic earlier.</p>', 'England v Pakistan', 'eng vs pak_1598811406.PNG', '2020-08-30 22:16:46', '2021-07-03 22:02:06'),
(79, 4, 4, 39, 'matt-doherty-tottenham-sign-defender-from-wolves-1598811646', 'Matt Doherty: Tottenham sign defender from Wolves', 0, '<p>Tottenham Hotspur have signed defender Matt Doherty from Premier League rivals Wolverhampton Wanderers to have an undisclosed fee.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Republic of eire right-back, 28, has signed a four-year cope with Spurs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Doherty remodeled 300 appearances for Baby wolves after joining from League of eire side Bohemians this year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He becomes Spurs&#39; third signing from the summer time following a arrivals of midfielder Pierre-Emile Hojbjerg and goalie Joe Hart.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I am very proud to become joining this type of big club,&quot; stated Doherty.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;[They&#39;ve] the very best stadium on the planet and perhaps the best proving ground on the planet.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;After I understood there is interest, it had been a no-brainer for me personally.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Time at Baby wolves was fantastic - I&#39;ve not had a bad word to say of the entire club whatsoever. I simply seem like coming here normally takes my game and my career one stage further.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Doherty performed in each and every Premier League bet on Wolves&#39; 2018-19 campaign and helped Nuno Espirito Santo&#39;s side to back-to-back seventh-place finishes since promotion in the Championship. They provided the quarter-finals of last season&#39;s Europa League but overlooked European football for 2020-21.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Spurs finished sixth within the top flight last term - in front of Baby wolves on goal difference - and arrived at the final 16 from the Champions League.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Doherty&#39;s move is another welcome financial boost to Bohemians, who&#39;d place a 10% sell-on clause in to the deal that required him to Baby wolves.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On Thursday, the Dublin club overlooked a money bonus once they lost on penalties to Hungarian side Fehervar within the Europa League.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bohemians&#39; chief operating officer, Daniel Lambert, published on social networking on Sunday describing this news of Doherty&#39;s transfer as &quot;fairly seismic&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'Matt Doherty, Wolves', '_114178053_gettyimages-1265272603_1598811646.jpg', '2020-08-30 22:20:46', '2021-08-14 22:39:49'),
(80, 4, 4, 45, 'ronaldinho-brazilian-stars-decline-from-barcelona-greatness-to-paraguay-prison-1598811865', 'Ronaldinho: Brazilian star\'s decline from Barcelona greatness to Paraguay prison', 0, '<p>Elasticos, rabonas, no-look passes which trademark toothy grin. At his peak, Ronaldinho was irresistible.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Through the 2000s, the Brazilian overcome the football world with the type of play YouTube is made for. And in the last decade he&#39;s won - and lost - greater than most players manage within their entire career.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Following a premature 2011 exit from AC Milan aged 30, he eclipsed Neymar within the more youthful man&#39;s own backyard, won a historic Copa Libertadores and made an appearance in Arab reality shows and Russian supermarket adverts. There is a Hollywood film with Jean-Claude van Damme.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This season, he lost his freedom, spending his 40th birthday kept in a Paraguayan prison.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In The month of january 2011, when Ronaldinho rotated his red-and-black stripes 90 levels by switching Milan for Flamengo, his Italian club&#39;s coach Massimiliano Allegri known as the choice &quot;a existence choice&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Quite simply: &#39;non-footballing reasons&#39;. As was the situation during 2 yrs at Paris St-Germain, his partying had forced a parting of the way. Performances were missing and persistence ran out.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The choice to go back home so at the start of his career surprised South america team-mate Rivaldo, who won the planet Cup alongside him in 2002.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;He might have ongoing longer in Europe, however it would be a personal decision,&quot; Rivaldo informs BBC Sport. &quot;He felt he&#39;d already written his story there, so wanted to return and finished in fashion, near to family and buddies.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In existence, as with football, Ronaldinho hasn&#39;t strayed too much in the spotlight. However the situation he faces now is much more serious than something that came before.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Short presentational gray line</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Born Ronaldo de Assis Moreira, Ronaldinho increased in Vila Nova, a ramshackle neighbourhood within the southern Brazilian town of Porto Alegre. His mother Miguelina offered cosmetics door-to-door, while father Joao labored nights within the carpark of local side Gremio. When older brother Roberto Assis signed professional terms together aged 17, the club provided a lavish rental property. Football, and particularly Gremio, lifted the household from poverty.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ronaldinho, requested in 2015 who he idolised when becoming an adult, told FourFourTwo: &quot;My buddy Assis, Rivelino, Romario, Ronaldo, Rivaldo and Diego Maradona.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>That very same rental property was the setting for any tragedy that will shape his existence and produce the siblings even closer together.</p>', 'Ronaldinho, Barcelona', '_113845645_roanldinho_messi_getty_c_1598811865.jpg', '2020-08-30 22:24:25', '2021-08-17 06:31:30'),
(82, 4, 9, 115, 'pierre-emerick-aubameyang-arsenal-striker-convinced-to-stay-mikel-arteta-1598812092', 'Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang: Arsenal striker \'convinced to stay\' - Mikel Arteta', 0, '<p>Arsenal manager Mikel Arteta thinks captain Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang continues to be &quot;convinced to remain for longer&quot; after his starring role locally Shield make an impression on Liverpool.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Forward Aubameyang, whose Gunners contract expires next summer time, curled inside a fantastic opener - before Takumi Minamino&#39;s equaliser - after which scored the winning penalty within the shootout at Wembley on Saturday.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;This is an exciting time for you to be a collection player,&quot; stated the 31-year-old Gabon worldwide.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The FA Cup winners happen to be attempting to tie Aubameyang lower to a different contract for a while.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He&#39;s scored 70 goals in 109 games since joining Arsenal from Borussia Dortmund for any club record &pound;56m in The month of january 2018.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Aubameyang is made captain in November after midfielder Granit Xhaka was stripped from the armband by Arteta&#39;s predecessor Unai Emery.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;My job is to try and convince him he&#39;s at the best place in the proper time,&quot; Arteta told BBC Radio 5 Live.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I believe we&#39;ve got that therefore we need to make the documents which takes a little time.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Arsenal beat Liverpool on penalties</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Watch Community Shield highlights on BBC iPlayer</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Aubameyang&#39;s excellent 20-yard strike on Saturday made him just the second Gunners player to attain five Wembley goals, after Alexis Sanchez.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>And they&#39;ve all come since This summer - he netted two times within the 2- make an impression on Manchester City within the FA Cup semi-final before another be used as Chelsea were beaten 2-one in the ultimate.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Requested about his future following the Community Shield, Aubameyang stated: &quot;We are likely to see nowadays. Today we go ahead and take trophy - there you have it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;We&#39;re improving. There&#39;s still try to do but I am really happy.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Aubameyang won the Bundesliga golden boot in 2017 and also the Premier League version in 2019, although his only major trophies would be the German Cup, FA Cup and French League Cup with Saint-Etienne.</p>', 'Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang, Mikel Arteta', 'a_1598812092.PNG', '2020-08-30 22:28:12', '2021-09-23 08:16:47'),
(83, 4, 9, 150, 'nba-play-offs-los-angeles-lakers-milwaukee-bucks-through-to-second-round-1598812455', 'NBA play-offs: Los Angeles Lakers & Milwaukee Bucks through to second round', 0, '<p>The La Opposing team and also the Milwaukee Dollars both arrived at the 2nd round from the National basketball association play-offs after games started again on Saturday.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Opposing team beat the Portland Trail Blazers 131-122 to win their Western Conference best-of-seven series 4-1.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Dollars also guaranteed a 4-1 series win within the Eastern Conference by beating the Orlando Magic 118-104 in game five.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The games were rescheduled once they were postponed in protest following a shooting of Jacob Blake.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A contract to resume the play-offs came following a &quot;candid, impassioned and productive conversation&quot; between National basketball association officials, players, coaches and staff.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lebron, who scored 36 points, 10 assists and 10 rebounds against Portland for his 25th career play-off triple-double and today includes a perfect 14- record within the first round from the play-offs, stated the Opposing team desired to &quot;improve because the series continued&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;So we did. There&#39;s an chance to decompress a little bit and watch for our next opponent,&quot; added James, after his side brushed beyond the Trail Blazers, who have been badly missing hurt star player Damian Lillard.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Opposing team will have either the Houston Rockets or even the Oklahoma City Thunder within the West&#39;s second round, as the Dollars will have fifth seeds the Miami Heat within the East.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Rockets, brought by James Harden&#39;s 31 points, thrashed the Thunder in game five of the series to guide 3-2 entering Monday evening&#39;s game six.</p>', 'NBA play-offs, Los Angeles Lakers, Milwaukee Bucks', '_114176937_giannisantetokounmpo_1598812455.jpg', '2020-08-30 22:34:15', '2021-08-12 07:55:41'),
(84, 4, 4, 49, 'south-africa-set-to-replace-japan-in-eight-team-tournament-1598812770', 'South Africa set to replace Japan in eight-team tournament', 0, '<p>World champions Nigeria are increasingly being arranged to switch Japan inside an eight-team tournament within the finish of year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Brave Blossoms, who located last year&#39;s World Cup, introduced out because of coronavirus travel limitations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Georgia were touted as replacements but World Rugby vice-chairman Bernard Laporte states they&#39;re in &quot;advanced discussions&quot; with Nigeria.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;It is good to be able to face the Springboks, world champions, but it&#39;s dirty,&quot; he mentioned.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A spokesperson for Nigeria Rugby mentioned they&#39;d &quot;no knowledge of these a contract being planned&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The tournament is replacing the autumn Tests and may begin on 14 November - 2 days following a final round in the 2020 Six Nations is completed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Nigeria could join group two, that&#39;s presently occupied by Scotland, Italia and France, and needs a fourth nation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Group one comprises England, Wales, Ireland and Fiji, while using two pool winners scheduled to fulfill in the final at Twickenham on 5 December.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Meanwhile, BBC Sport understands England&#39;s players have made the decision to possess a 25% cut for his or her match charges within this autumn&#39;s fixtures, a price reduction of roughly &pound;6,000 per match.</p>', 'South Africa Sports', '_114180092_kolisi_pa_1598812770.jpg', '2020-08-30 22:39:30', '2021-08-14 22:41:05'),
(85, 4, 4, 61, 'real-salt-lake-owner-dell-loy-hansen-to-sell-mls-club-after-criticising-players-protest-1598812871', 'Real Salt Lake: Owner Dell Loy Hansen to sell MLS club after criticising players\' protest', 0, '<p>Real Salt Lake owner Dell Loy Hansen would be to sell the main League Football team - days after he criticised the team&#39;s players for his or her protest within the Jacob Blake shooting.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Real&#39;s game in your own home to La FC was certainly one of five Major League Soccer matches known as off on Wednesday.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Hansen stated he felt &quot;disrespected&quot; through the postponement, adding: &quot;It&#39;s like somebody stabbed you.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>An MLS statement stated the league is needed &quot;offer the purchase efforts&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Blake, a black man, was shot seven occasions within the back by police last Sunday in Kenosha, Wisconsin, near Milwaukee.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On Wednesday, the Milwaukee Dollars known as business National basketball association fixture, which brought to games within the National basketball association, Major league baseball, National hockey league and MLS being known as off, while Japanese tennis player Naomi Osaka brought out of the WTA match in New You are able to on Thursday.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On Thursday, defender Nedum Onuoha stated he was thinking about his future at Real Salt Lake after Hansen&#39;s comments.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I&#39;d rather not be around because I am not here to experience for somebody who is not here to aid us,&quot; ex-Manchester City player Onuoha told BBC World Service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;We are attempting to produce a bigger conversation but many of those who are in power don&#39;t empathise or sympathise or do anything whatsoever. They&#39;re more worried about themselves.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Hansen&#39;s comments happen to be broadly condemned</p>\r\n\r\n<p>across US football&#39;s professional leagues.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Hansen owns the MLS club through Utah Soccer Holdings that also owns Utah Royals FC, who participate in the National Women&#39;s Soccer League and Real Monarchs within the second-tier U . s . Soccer League.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Millionaire Hansen had stated the cancellation from the game means he&#39;d reduce his degree of investment that the gym has making redundancies over the business.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;We are all sitting at a company attempting to build support and love around a group that props up city,&quot; he told a nearby radio station.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;All I&#39;m able to have to say is they supported other conditions across the country. They clearly didn&#39;t support our city or our organisation. That&#39;s fairly obvious.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;It is a moment of sadness. It&#39;s like somebody stabbed you and also you are trying to puzzle out a method to pull the knife out and move ahead. That is what it seems like. The disrespect is profound in my experience personally.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; National basketball association, Major league baseball and MLS postpone games</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; I do not feel safe in USA - Onuoha</p>', 'Real Salt Lake, MLS club', '_114181728_gettyimages-1228218460_1598812870.jpg', '2020-08-30 22:41:11', '2021-08-14 22:40:36');
