(86, 4, 4, 63, 'us-open-player-withdrawn-from-grand-slam-after-positive-coronavirus-test-1598813261', 'US Open: Player withdrawn from Grand Slam after positive coronavirus test', 0, '<p>A person continues to be withdrawn in the US Open, which starts on Monday, after testing positive for coronavirus.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The gamer, who is not named, is showing no signs and symptoms but must now isolate for ten days.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On Sunday, French number 17 seed Benoit Paire was replaced within the men&#39;s singles draw by Spain&#39;s Marcel Granollers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>An American Tennis Association statement stated: &quot;A person has tested positive for Covid-19 and it has been withdrawn in the tournament.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &#39;A US Open like no other&#39; - full preview</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; What&#39;s existence like in america Open bubble?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Top seeds for action on the first day - Monday&#39;s order of play</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Contact tracing may also determine whether close contacts will have to quarantine for fourteen days.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Paire have been scheduled to experience Kamil Majchrzak within the first round at Flushing Meadows in New You are able to on Tuesday, using the Polish player now listed as facing Granollers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>British number 1 Johanna Konta stated it had been &quot;shocking and worrisome&quot; a person had tested positive within the US Open bubble.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;We have were built with a couple of [positive tests] but it&#39;s certainly different when they have been here, had negative tests after which tested positive,&quot; stated Konta, who plays fellow Briton Louise Watson .</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;The problem we&#39;ve is it isn&#39;t a complete bubble, you may still find many people employed by the tournament who&#39;re coming out and in.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;It&#39;s as safe as possible get when it comes to the number of individuals are here to operate this operation.&quot;</p>', 'Grand Slam, US Open', '_114180796_gettyimages-1170599864-1_1598813260.jpg', '2020-08-30 22:47:41', '2021-08-17 20:07:38'),
(87, 4, 9, 152, 'weather-world-coronavirus-and-our-climate-1598814536', 'Weather World: Coronavirus and our climate', 0, '<p>&quot;It&#39;ll die within the summer time.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Which was the rather hopeful conjecture about coronavirus, with different misguided thought that growing temperatures would diminish its spread.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>That did not happen, and actually the main focus has now use the possibilities of an upsurge within the virus this winter season.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>That isn&#39;t a misplaced fear based on one expert featured within the programme. Dr Rachel Lowe in the London School of Hygiene and Tropical Medicine states the present spread from the virus is driven by the possible lack of immunity one of the population and has not yet become periodic like other infections for example influenza.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dr Lowe states we do not yet know precisely why some infections tend to be more prevalent in cooler several weeks. It might be something related to herpes itself however it may be lower to human conduct as increasing numbers of people have a tendency to crowd into indoor spaces for extended when it&#39;s cooler outdoors, which makes it simpler for that virus to spread.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Because of this, she informs the programme, coronavirus coupled with flus along with other &quot;winter&quot; illnesses could put significant pressure on emergency services if they&#39;re not fully prepared.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What we should do know of the pandemic is it did lead to an alteration within the atmosphere that no-you might have thought possible at the beginning of the entire year. Carbon emissions fell dramatically because of the decrease in work and travel as increasing numbers of countries entered lockdown. We speak with an environment researcher about whether this can end up being a brief fall or maybe it could have lasting effect on global warming predictions.</p>', 'Weather World, Coronavirus', '_114155543_covidhosp_1598814536.jpg', '2020-08-30 23:08:56', '2021-08-16 15:30:38'),
(88, 4, 9, 143, 'hurricane-laura-400000-without-power-in-louisiana-1598815731', 'Hurricane Laura: 400,000 without power in Louisiana', 0, '<p>Residents in seaside regions of Louisiana in america face the possibilities of days without power or water because the clean-up begins following a devastating impact of Hurricane Laura.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Greater than 400,000 were without turn on &#39;life was imple&#39; and 200,000 without water, officials stated.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Governor John Bel Edwards states the devastation and damage stretch completely to northern areas of Louisiana.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A minimum of 14 everyone was wiped out through the storm - 10 in Louisiana, four in Texas.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In Haiti, that was earlier badly hit by storms Marco and Laura, greater than 31 individuals are now reported to possess died.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>President Jesse Trump visited impacted areas in Louisiana and Texas on Saturday.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;One factor I understand relating to this condition, it rebuilds fast,&quot; he told a conference in Louisiana.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mr Trump stated losing existence would be a &quot;tremendous number&quot;, but added it &quot;might have been a great deal worse&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What is the response been?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The White-colored House has declared a significant disaster in a number of parishes in Louisiana - that will mean federal funds can be delivered to the toughest-hit areas urgently.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Assistance may include grants for temporary housing and residential repairs, low-cost loans to pay for uninsured property losses, along with other programs to help those and business proprietors get over the results from the disaster,&quot; a White-colored House statement stated.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Louisiana governor has known as Laura &quot;the most powerful storm to ever hit Louisiana&quot;. It had been a category-four hurricane at that time it hit.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;The devastation and damage stretch from south-west Louisiana completely through north Louisiana, using more than a 500, 000 power outages remaining, thousands of people displaced using their homes and, sadly, a minimum of 10 lives lost,&quot; Governor Edwards stated inside a statement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>From the 10 individuals to lose their resides in the condition, five died from deadly carbon monoxide poisoning from gas-powered emergency generators, four from trees falling and something from drowning.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In Texas, a guy was wiped out whenever a tree hit his home, and three people died in Port Arthur, possibly from deadly carbon monoxide poisoning, officials reported.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Around 8,000 homes were possibly destroyed within the two states, based on the Red Mix.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There is more structural damage from winds than anticipated, however the water damage and mold was under feared.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some 1,500 people, including National Guard troops, are now being deployed in save and clean-up missions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lauren Sylvester, a resident of Lake Charles, Louisiana, followed orders to evacuate.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>She returned to her house on Friday to see power lines and trees strewn around the streets.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;It&#39;s still an incredible amount of damage,&quot; she told AP news agency.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lawrence &quot;Lee&quot; Faulk had a similar experience - he found his home in Cameron Parish with no roof on.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;We need help,&quot; Mr Faulk told CBS news. &quot;We need ice, water, blue tarps - everything that you would associate with the storm, we need it. Like two hours ago.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>During his trip, President Trump met with those involved in relief efforts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In Lake Charles, Trump said &quot;come here fellas, I want a little power&quot;, before autographing pieces of paper. He handed one to a law officer and said: &quot;Here sell this tonight on Ebay, you&#39;ll get $10,000&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What other areas have suffered?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The death toll in Haiti has risen by 10 to 31 and eight people are missing, the country&#39;s civil protection service said. More than 6,000 homes were flooded in the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Four people are known to have died in neighbouring Dominican Republic.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cuba suffered damage but did not record any deaths.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In Jamaica, there were reports of landslides and flooded roads.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The US territory of Puerto Rico was also hit.</p>', 'Hurricane Laura, 400,000 without power in Louisiana', '_114173434_2114ab74-c067-4aa7-b261-5e9765fbdd0a_1598815731.jpg', '2020-08-30 23:28:51', '2021-08-13 07:06:19'),
(89, 4, 3, 44, 'germany-coronavirus-anger-after-attempt-to-storm-reichstag-1598817105', 'Germany coronavirus: Anger after attempt to storm Reichstag', 0, '<p>An effort to storm Germany&#39;s Reichstag during Saturday&#39;s big Berlin protest against Covid-19 limitations continues to be condemned by politicians over the political spectrum.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Demonstrators, many with far-right sympathies, broke via a cordon and ran in the steps from the parliament building before police spread them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The inside minister stated there must be &quot;zero tolerance&quot; for such conduct.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some 38,000 switched out for that wider, largely peaceful Berlin demonstration.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What went down in the Reichstag?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Demonstrators bearing the flag of former imperial Germany - utilized by the Reichsb&uuml;rger (Reich Citizens) far-right group - transformed a number of police to operate towards the building entrance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Police place the number involved at a number of hundred.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Scuffles started and also the protesters were then overcome by police using pepper spray. Multiple people were arrested.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Police rejected critique of the small deployment, saying they couldn&#39;t &quot;be everywhere constantly&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What&#39;s the response been?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;The Reichstag may be the domain in our parliament and also the symbolic center in our democracy. It&#39;s intolerable that troublemakers and extremists misuse it for his or her own purposes,&quot; stated Interior Minister Horst Seehofer.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>President Frank Walter Steinmeier condemned &quot;an intolerable attack around the heart in our democracy&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Individuals angered by our coronavirus measures or who doubt their necessity can perform so freely, in protests. But my tolerance ends when protesters hitch themselves towards the wagon of opponents of democracy and political rabble-rousers.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vice-Chancellor Olaf Scholz, in the Social Democrats, was one of many to sentence the display of far-right and German imperial symbols.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Social Democrats also have known as for improved security around parliament.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The organiser from the primary protest, tech entrepreneur Michael Ballweg, stated the Reichstag demonstrators had &quot;absolutely nothing to do&quot; together with his movement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What went down within the wider demonstration?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The protest had initially been banned however a court eventually permitted it to go forward provided that coronavirus measures for example mask-putting on and social-distancing were stuck to.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In most, 300 everyone was arrested at various locations, 200 after right-wing agitators put gemstones and bottles close to the Brandenburg Gate.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Police purchased the dispersal from the protest because the day continued because individuals participating were neglecting to observe coronavirus rules.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Protesters were carefully packed in places, and sitting together on the floor at some point.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Among individuals arrested was cookery author and conspiracy theorist Attila Hildmann, who&#39;d addressed crowds via a loudspeaker.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Although Germany has to date not seen the wave of cases affecting certain parts of Europe, its infection rate continues to be growing. New situation figures are reaching highs last observed in April.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Who organised the Berlin protests?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The demonstration was known as through the Stuttgart-based movement Querdenken 711 (or Lateral Thinking 711). The audience has greater than 16,000 supporters on Facebook and communicates largely through encrypted messaging service Telegram.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It believes that coronavirus rules infringe on fundamental legal rights and freedoms enshrined in Germany&#39;s metabolic rate and desires these to be lifted.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The protests also have acquired support from Robert F Kennedy Junior. The anti-vaccination campaigner, even the boy of assassinated US Democratic presidential hopeful Robert F Kennedy and nephew of assassinated US President John F Kennedy, what food was in the demonstration in Berlin.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Photos shared online also demonstrated flags and slogans from the conspiracy theory QAnon.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; What&#39;s QAnon?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Participants also incorporated families and kids. Many people have stated they simply want the authority to protest.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Counter-protests from the primary march also required place, about 100 people at one rally. &quot;You&#39;re marching with Nazis and Fascists,&quot; yelled some participants, based on broadcaster RBB.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What exactly are Germany&#39;s Covid-19 measures?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The nation was probably the most good at enforcing the framework of response known as prevent, identify, contain and treat.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It&#39;s been particularly good at maintaining your dying rate one of the over 70s lower.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It started relaxing physical distancing at the begining of April but ongoing to trace infections, that have seen a boost in August.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On Thursday, Chancellor Angela Merkel and also the 16 federal states introduced the absolute minimum &euro;50 (&pound;45 $59) acceptable for neglecting to put on a nose and mouth mask where purchased. A ban on major public occasions seemed to be extended until the coming year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Germany has recorded 242,000 infections, less compared to other major European nations. Its figure of 9,297 deaths is significantly less than the figures in Russia, the United kingdom, The country, France and Italia, Johns Hopkins College studies have shown.</p>', 'Germany coronavirus, Reichstag', '_114175518_7b312ecf-5466-471c-9f3d-644fce104887_1598817105.jpg', '2020-08-30 23:51:45', '2021-08-17 23:31:31'),
(90, 4, 7, 52, 'portland-clashes-fatal-shooting-as-rival-groups-protest-1598817493', 'Portland clashes: Fatal shooting as rival groups protest', 0, '<p>A guy continues to be shot dead in Or like a large procession of supporters of President Trump clashed with Black Lives Matter protesters in Portland.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Images in the scene demonstrated medics attempting to save the person, who made an appearance to become white-colored.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mother and father not given a name or specified if the shooting was directly from the clashes which started inside a downtown area.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Portland&#39;s roads happen to be the scene of frequent protests in recent days.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The town has turned into a focus for demonstrations against police brutality and racism because the police killing of African-American George Floyd in Minneapolis on 25 May triggered a wave of national and worldwide outrage.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Federal forces were sent by President Trump to Portland in This summer with what was referred to as moving to avoid violence but later withdrawn.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Acting homeland security chief Chad Wolf declined to eliminate delivering it well when pressed on ABC&#39;s Now.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;In my opinion all options continue being up for grabs, particularly once we discuss Portland,&quot; he stated.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What&#39;s been aware of the shooting?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The most recent pro-Trump rally was around the third Saturday consecutively.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Inside a statement, Portland police stated: &quot;Portland Police officials heard sounds of gunfire in the section of Southeast 3rd Avenue and Southwest Alder Street. They responded and discovered a target having a gunshot wound towards the chest.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The person didn&#39;t survive, they stated.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Or Live reported that &quot;camouflage gear&quot; with &quot;thin blue line patches&quot; was seen near the body - a typical manifestation of support for that police.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; How BLM went from Facebook publish to global movement</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Teen billed for police overtime after BLM rally</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Trump&#39;s attack on Portland protests described</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Should Wisconsin mother and father used different tactics?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Peter Bowes, BBC The United States correspondent</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The ongoing violence upon us roads brings into focus the evolving tone of Jesse Trump&#39;s election campaign - criticising metropolitan areas operated by Democrats, where a lot of the problem has happened, and framing themself because the law and order president.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Portland continues to be the epicentre of Black Lives Matter protests since law enforcement killing of George Floyd, however the convergence of professional-Trump supporters, in large figures, with anti-racism demonstrators marks an unpredictable escalation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tweeting &quot;LAW &amp; ORDER!!!&quot; hrs following the latest disturbances, Mr Trump causes it to be obvious the issue will dominate his attract the United states citizens for any second term at work.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This may be a pivotal week. On Tuesday obama will mind to Kenosha, within the political swing condition of Wisconsin, where violent protests adopted law enforcement shooting of Jacob Blake. The mentioned reason is perfect for Mr Trump to satisfy local police and &quot;survey damage from recent riots&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many Americans is going to be watching to find out if obama also reaches to Mr Blake and the family as well as for any expressions of empathy for individuals who&#39;re angry about police brutality.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>That which was the backdrop towards the shooting?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The shooting came among fights between your Trump supporters and BLM protesters within the city center.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tension rose following a convoy of some 600 vehicles flying flags and transporting an believed 1,000 Trump backers collected in a mall in Clackamas county around the borders before entering Portland&#39;s downtown.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Video demonstrated many people firing what local media referred to as pepper spray and pellets at BLM groups who&#39;d attempted to avoid them entering the town by blocking roads.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Police reported &quot;some cases of violence&quot; between &quot;demonstrators and counter-demonstrators&quot; and stated some arrests have been made.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The violence adopted last week&#39;s Republican convention which formally anointed Mr Trump because the party&#39;s presidential candidate.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Accepting the nomination inside a speech around the White-colored House lawn, he searched for to characterise Portland as the second Democratic-run city prey to &quot;rioting, looting, arson and violence&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The clashes are also available in the wake from the shooting by police of Jacob Blake. He was hit within the back seven occasions and seriously wounded by a police officer in Kenosha, Wisconsin, because he leaned right into a vehicle.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>How come Portland a flashpoint?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some protests in Portland over George Floyd&#39;s dying are actually broken by violence, arson, damage to property, arrests and allegations of police brutality.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Within This summer time, federal officials came strong critique for cracking lower on crowds - in the wishes in the municipality physiques - who&#39;d collected inside the city. Federal officials in unmarked vehicles came out to forcefully seize protesters within the roads and detain them without justification.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Trump administration described the protesters just like a violent mob, but city officials came a among peaceful demonstrators and smaller sized sized groups bent on making trouble.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Portland has furthermore seen violence between far-right groups, for instance Proud Boys and Patriot Prayer, and left-wing counter-demonstrators known as antifa, or anti-fascist movement.</p>', 'Portland clashes, Fatal shooting', '_114177158_gettyimages-1228264216_1598817493.jpg', '2020-08-30 23:58:13', '2021-08-17 14:22:32'),
(91, 4, 7, 54, 'woman-arrested-for-naked-video-on-indias-lakshman-jhula-bridge-1598817624', 'Woman arrested for naked video on India\'s Lakshman Jhula bridge', 0, '<p>A French lady continues to be arrested in India to make a relevant video of herself naked on the sacred bridge within the northern town of Rishikesh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The recording, shot around the Lakshman Jhula bridge, was published on social networking.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The lady faces charges under India&#39;s internet law, and is sentenced to as much as 3 years imprisonment if found guilty, AFP news agency reports.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The suspension bridge within the Ganges river and it is a holy site and popular place for vacationers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The lady, that has since been released on bail, told police the recording is made to advertise her jewellery business.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Maybe in France this stuff aren&#39;t considered objectionable. But Rishikesh is really a holy place and also the Lakshman Jhula is where where [Hindu gods] Ram, his brother Lakshman and wife Sita entered the Ganges,&quot; RK Saklani, mind from the police station in which the lady was taken, told AFP.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The lady, who is not formally identified, was arrested on Thursday after police were alerted towards the footage.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Throughout the questioning, she recognized to possess shot the recording in [the] nude but claimed she wasn&#39;t conscious that it&#39;s illegal in India. She stated the recording and also the photoshoot was meant to promote her bead-necklace business,&quot; another police official told the Indian newspaper Hindustan Occasions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The situation might take several weeks to process.</p>', 'Woman arrested for naked video on India\'s Lakshman Jhula bridge', '_114178954_gettyimages-481688233_1598817624.jpg', '2020-08-31 00:00:24', '2021-08-18 07:56:00'),
(92, 4, 4, 75, 'lionel-messi-barcelona-forwards-release-clause-remains-valid-says-la-liga-1598817728', 'Lionel Messi: Barcelona forward\'s release clause remains valid, says La Liga', 0, '<p>The 700m euros (&pound;624m) release clause in Lionel Messi&#39;s Barcelona contract continues to be valid, La Liga has stated.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Messi, 33, informed the club on Tuesday he wanted to depart and didn&#39;t attend a pre-season medical on Sunday.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Argentina forward intends to invoke a clause that will permit him to depart the club free of charge but Barcelona argue the deadline for your has expired.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Spain&#39;s top-flight competition La Liga now states it won&#39;t de-register the gamer unless of course the clause is met.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; What&#39;s the latest within the Messi transfer situation?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Where could Messi go next?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;In compliance using the relevant rule, La Liga won&#39;t approve a request to become de-registered like a player using the Spanish football federation, unless of course the quantity within the release clause continues to be compensated,&quot; your body stated inside a statement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Messi was due at Barcelona&#39;s proving ground at 10.15am local time on Sunday but didn&#39;t attend.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The player&#39;s lawyers intend to exercise a clause in the four-year contract, signed in 2017, which may have permitted him to depart the club free of charge if he&#39;d requested to do this by 10 June.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>They&#39;ll reason that date, nominally the finish of year, has become irrelevant following the coronavirus delays that brought towards the season&#39;s extension and also the team playing deep into August.</p>', 'Lionel Messi, Barcelona', '_114110138_lionel_messi_getty2_1598817727.jpg', '2020-08-31 00:02:08', '2021-08-15 12:33:36'),
(93, 4, 7, 61, 'french-spying-senior-army-officer-investigated-1598817875', 'French spying: Senior army officer investigated', 0, '<p>A senior French army officer is under analysis for any suspected &quot;breach of security&quot;, the military minister has confirmed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Florence Parly gave no further details but sources told French media the officer was stationed with Nato and located in Italia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The lieutenant-colonel was suspected of passing sensitive information to Russian intelligence, Europe 1 reports.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He&#39;s been remanded in child custody in Paris, radio stations station stated.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ms Parly told Europe 1 it had been France which had instigated the court proceedings within the situation also it was now at the disposal of prosecutors.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;We&#39;ve taken all of the protective measures which were necessary,&quot; she stated.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A judicial source told Agence France-Presse the officer have been remanded and it was being investigated over &quot;intelligence having a foreign energy that undermines the essential interests of the united states&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Europe 1 stated the officer involved had distant family roots in Russia and spoke the word what fluently.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It stated he labored in a command center near Naples.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The officer was arrested ten days ago because he prepared to go back to Italia from vacation in France, it stated.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The most recent arrest comes at any given time of hysteria among Nato partners, stemming mainly from questions regarding the ongoing dedication to the alliance of america under President Jesse Trump.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Last November, French President Emmanuel Macron described Nato as &quot;brain dead&quot; due to the waning US commitment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The most recent tensions have come to light over coal and oil within the eastern Mediterranean. Nato people A holiday in greece and Poultry are in loggerheads, with France appearing to affiliate with the Greeks.</p>', 'French spying, Senior army office', '_114179679_mediaitem114179388_1598817875.jpg', '2020-08-31 00:04:35', '2021-08-13 23:12:29'),
(94, 4, 9, 122, 'georgia-im-a-child-of-the-uk-rave-scene-1598818204', 'Georgia: \'I\'m a child of the UK rave scene\'', 0, '<p>Georgia Barnes was virtually born to the dancefloor.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Not literally, obviously, that might be a safety and health issue.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But because the daughter of Neil Barnes from United kingdom dance pioneers Leftfield, the 30-year-old spent her more youthful years taking in electronic house beats at live gigs and festivals while cultivating an appreciation of synth-pop sounds and beyond from around the globe.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Now, after honing her craft like a drummer [for Kae Tempest], producer and singer, the previous record shop assistant resides to the family name.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Like a one-lady dance machine though, Georgia&#39;s put on the BBC Seem of 2020 longlist, and subsequent nomination with this year&#39;s Mercury Prize - on her euphoric second album Seeking Thrills - was all lower to her very own hard graft (although a work of affection).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&#39;Witnessing dancefloor culture&#39;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I experienced a lengthy process with this particular record following the first [self-entitled 2015] record arrived on the scene,&quot; states Georgia, who scored a significant club hit this past year about Work The Dancefloor.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I felt like I desired to return to enter board a bit after which shut myself away and pay attention to plenty of music, especially my roots to be a young child from the United kingdom rave scene.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I have always were built with a passion for dance music and try to attended clubs since i have would be a youthful age, and that is the background music which i felt really excites me - for the reason that electronic world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;However I took it back and uncover its roots and extremely understand the type of music, after which I discovered the direction for that record,&quot; she adds.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;A great deal the lyrical submissions are inspired just by seeing people on dancefloors and witnessing dancefloor culture.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With dancefloors getting been cruelly vacated for many of 2020, because of Covid-19 concerns, Georgia continues to be spending her breakthrough year getting creative again at her home studio in north west London.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Anybody who tuned in doing perform at Radio 1&#39;s (virtual) Big Weekend may have seen the outcomes, as she covered the area in aluminium foil and &quot;attempted to produce such as this outer world... just like a live streaming strange spaceship&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I believe people thought it was strange and intriguing entering people&#39;s world&#39;s in different ways,&quot; she notes, from the pandemic-era trend for substitute online gigs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;This is where I saw live streaming really was great - and give people that sort of escapist moment during that which was a really hard time. Will still be trouble, however i think now for the finish [of lockdown] live streaming must kind of re-think. Maybe individuals don&#39;t need it just as much any longer.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&#39;Future is working collectively&#39;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What lots of people want without a doubt is really a go back to the actual live music experience, when is securely possible. And Georgia notes it&#39;s been a &quot;devastating&quot; here we are at a few of the nation&#39;s most-loved venues, and also the systems of individuals around them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Festival staff &#39;devastated&#39; by summer time of cancellations</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Music venues welcome extra emergency funding</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Venues signal &#39;red alert&#39; for live occasions</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Why 2020 &#39;is a write-off&#39; for gigs and festivals</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The increasing star have been booked to do only at that weekend&#39;s Studying and Leeds Festivals, that have been cancelled as well as other August bank holiday favourites, Creamfields and also the Notting Hill Circus.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>She states she was motivated to begin to see the recent crowdfunding efforts which avoided her &quot;favourite venue within the whole United kingdom&quot; - Sub Club in Glasgow, from sinking.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;It had been amazing to determine the entire dance community, even people outdoors the dance community, create this crowdfund and lift enough money to allow them to overcome the very first hurdle of the Covid journey. To determine that provided real optimism, like &#39;OK, the largest a genuine difference here&#39;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I believe the long run is working with each other more. I believe it comes down to all uniting and helping each other hopefully are going to that.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Georgia labored with only a couple of other reliable producers/songwriters on Seeking Thrills, which showed up in to the world in The month of january (prior to the virus had reduced our thrill-seeking capacities) billed as &quot;the very first great album from the decade&quot;, through the Evening Standard&#39;s David Smyth.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pitchfork&#39;s Anna Gaca described the album as &quot;the job of the budding pop mind finding her very own space around the dancefloor&quot;, while Jordan Bassett from the NME opined it &quot;captures the push and pull from the club having a writerly eye&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;On her behalf second album, a rhythmic hurry of club-pop, the London producer extols the merits of unpolluted living along with a obvious mind,&quot; authored Cat Empire within the Protector.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&#39;World has changed&#39;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Clean living is hardly something would affiliate using the 90s, when Georgia&#39;s dad&#39;s electronic outfit were assisting to soundtrack the country&#39;s nightlife.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Barnes senior was two times listed for that Mercury themself with Leftfield in 1995 and 2000.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sadly because of the virus, there won&#39;t be any &quot;crazy night&quot; - as Georgia&#39;s mother remembers the &#39;95 event - to mark the 2010 prize. The Brit school graduate thinks her very own generation of millennial artists, including fellow nominees Dua Lipa, Michael Kiwanuka and Stormzy, are less inclined to be astounded by the &quot;excesses&quot; of this era anyway.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Clearly a part of music continues to be hedonism and it is as being a bit around the peripheries of society,&quot; states Georgia. &quot;However I don&#39;t believe it is awesome any longer to complete what the things they did within the 90s.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;It may be pretty funny in the event you switched up available there is a lot of champagne released, a number of drugs being consumed while dining and people getting fights and winding each other up, which is similar to carnage,&quot; she continues.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;However I don&#39;t think that&#39;s awesome any more, especially during this time period [getting a worldwide pandemic and recession]. The world population has altered.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Former QPR and Arsenal youth team footballer, Georgia, states she&#39;ll be forever grateful to her parents for teaching her the requirement for being self-sufficient. Like getting the opportunity to produce her music in their room, for example.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I&#39;ve just had the opportunity to kind of steer my own, personal ship, that&#39;s the way i like it,&quot; she states.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Her father is not directly associated with her music alone, but he&#39;s doing offer &quot;his honest opinion&quot;, when requested.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In recent several weeks, apart from re-mixing a Jessie Ware track and fulfilling the childhood imagine appearing on the record alongside Gorillaz and New Order&#39;s Peter Hook, Georgia also started focus on a household music project, featuring her mother and brother.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In a perfect world, she&#39;d passion for her fans to become embracing her new tunes, and one another, while on a dancefloor somewhere. Instead of individuals at this time, however, she provides the BBC an alternate listening suggestion rather.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I usually love that scene in [US comedy-drama] Women, where Lena Dunham includes a bad day after which she puts [Robyn&#39;s track] Dancing By Myself on - it&#39;s just like a earphones moment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I simply hope people stick their earphones on and seem like they are able to escape or they think empowered to visit and seek an excitement.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Seeking Thrills has gone out now. Classic Studying&nbsp;&nbsp; Leeds performances can be found a few days ago around the BBC iPlayer and BBC Sounds. The Mercury Prize champion is going to be revealed on 24 September, with coverage on BBC Radio 6 Music and BBC Four TV.</p>', 'Georgia, UK rave scene', '_113936720_georgiafeb2020-creditryansaradjola_-2_1598818203.jpg', '2020-08-31 00:10:04', '2021-08-14 20:31:30'),
(95, 4, 3, 40, 'i-hate-suzie-five-star-reviews-for-billie-pipers-tv-return-1598818474', 'I Hate Suzie: Five-star reviews for Billie Piper\'s TV return', 0, '<p>Billie Piper&#39;s return on the horizon TV drama series, I Personally Don&#39;t Like Suzie, continues to be lauded by critics &quot;an outrageous ride&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Piper portrays the titular Suzie Pickles - an old child screen star, whose existence and career are switched upside lower with a compromising phone hack.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It finds her reunited with Secret Diary of the Call Girl author Lucy Prebble.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Protector gave it a 5-star review, describing Piper&#39;s character as &quot;nude, lewd and joyously from the rails&quot; in &quot;this scabrously funny drama&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Beneath everything, Prebble supports the reins firmly in her own fist and Piper keeps us - just, just - along the side of an endlessly charismatic but volatile, self-indulgent character,&quot; authored Lucy Mangan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I Personally Don&#39;t Like Suzie nails the arrested development and consequent issues - poor impulse control, irresponsibility and usually exhausting high-maintenance-liness - of the celebrity upon whom fame was visited so early.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;It is a wild ride that seems like a complete gift,&quot; she added.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Telegraph were similarly impressed, also choosing top marks while calling the show a &quot;glorious, fizzing monument towards the creativeness of Piper and Prebble&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I Personally Don&#39;t Like Suzie is outstanding portrait of 1 woman&#39;s descent,&quot; opined Chris Bennion.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&#39;Fame and privacy&#39;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Piper was nominated to have an Olivier Award on her performance in Prebble&#39;s 2012 take part in the Effect.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Critics noted her very own experience with getting been a enormous youthful singer-switched-actress who becomes famous in a youthful age won&#39; doubt have shared with her new role as Pickles.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Billie Piper: Trying to get it all is &#39;stressful&#39;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; It is time for any female Physician, states Billie</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Independent recommended that within the drama, Piper is &quot;playing a thinly disguised form of herself&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;A lot of I Personally Don&#39;t Like Suzie is filmed inside a frenetic, fast-cut style that reflects Suzie&#39;s descent into this contemporary nightmare,&quot; authored Erectile dysfunction Cumming.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Piper includes a rare gift for eliciting sympathy, even while Pickles keeps making new mistakes in her own effort to disguise that old ones.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;What emerges is really a black-comedy-horror about female friendship, modern fame, and also the impracticality of true privacy inside a world where everybody comes with an online camcorder within their pockets.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&#39;Genuinely is really a mess&#39;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Night Standard, who gave it four stars, asserted that &quot;Piper provides a raw, soul-baring performance&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I Personally Don&#39;t Like Suzie feels fresh and pacy with lots of dry wit. My only objection is, why can you hate someone known as Suzie?&quot; joked their author Susannah Butter, with higher reason.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Carol Midgely from the Occasions stated: &quot;I believe many people would agree that Piper is definitely an outstanding actress, playing Suzie with excruciating honesty.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;It&#39;s gratifying to determine Piper inside a TV role where she will stretch her legs, demonstrate to her class and employ towards the max her mesmerically significant face (she got five-star reviews and an array of awards on her &quot;career-defining&quot; role within the play Yerma)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;It was bold and intelligently acted television. But an immediate remedy for any fool who positively really wants to be &#39;a celebrity&#39;.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Image copyright Sky</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The NME recommended I Personally Don&#39;t Like Suzie is placed to get &quot;your brand-new favourite Television show a good unravelling pop star&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;She&#39;s a nightmare,&quot; Prebble, who co-produced the show together with her friend Piper, told the internet magazine.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;We actually were not thinking about making her &#39;likeable&#39; in inverted commas, or perhaps particularly relatable, because that&#39;s something which has been pressed lower our throats when designing figures for any lengthy time, especially with regards to women.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;We are kind of experimenting within this show, I suppose, with demonstrating somebody that genuinely is really a mess - not someone who appears just like a mess, but beneath it all she&#39;s a try-getter,&quot; added the Succession producer.</p>', 'I Hate Suzie, Billie Piper\'s TV', '_114159514_i_hate_suzie_sky-1392x884_1598818474.jpg', '2020-08-31 00:14:34', '2021-08-17 13:11:51'),
(96, 4, 3, 51, 'bts-humbled-to-bag-first-uk-chart-top-10-hit-1598818621', 'BTS \'humbled\' to bag first UK chart top 10 hit', 0, '<p>K-pop group BTS have guaranteed their first top ten United kingdom chart hit.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Their British-language single Dynamite debuted at number 3 on Friday&#39;s chart, beating their previous best effort Boy With Luv, which featured Halsey and arrived at number 13 this past year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;We&#39;re feeling humbled and honoured to possess earned a brand new personal best around the United kingdom Official Singles Chart,&quot; BTS stated.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Elsewhere around the chart, Vera Lynn&#39;s Land and Hope and Glory came back to the peak 20, carrying out a BBC Proms row.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&#39;Vibrant energy&#39;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Reacting towards the news of the achievement, through the Official Chart Company, the seven-strong South Korean boy-band stated: &quot;First of all, we give all credit to [their fans] Army - without their support and love from the first day, we wouldn&#39;t came to this point.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Dynamite was produced hoping of getting some vibrant souped up that the planet needs at this time more than ever before. Whether it made one individual more happy, then that&#39;s ample for all of us.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Earlier within the week the recording for that track broke YouTube records, being viewed an astonishing 101.a million occasions in 24 hrs after its release.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; BTS inflate YouTube records with Dynamite</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Regardless of the ever-growing K-Pop influence, Joel Corry and MNEK held onto top place within the singles chart for any sixth consecutive week, with Mind &amp; Heart.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>They fought against off competition from provocative rappers Cardi B and Megan Thee Stallion&#39;s as well as their broadly-discussed WAP.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Around the album chart, meanwhile, Vegas indie rockers The Killers guaranteed their sixth Number 1 album, with Imploding The Mirage going straight in at number 1.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Apart from BTS growing the web, now saw the beginning of a debate if the BBC should drop the loyal festival favourites Rule, Britannia! and Land of Hope and Glory from Yesterday from the Proms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Chineke! Foundation founder Chi-chi Nwanoku stated the songs carry &quot;jingoistic echoes of empire&quot;. But Pm Boris Manley told reporters it had been &quot;time we stopped our cringing embarrassment about our history&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As a result of the suggestion the songs might be dropped, an offer premiered online to obtain Dame Vera&#39;s form of Land Of Hope And Glory to number 1.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The song joined the chart at number 17 on Friday.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Boris Manley &#39;cannot believe&#39; BBC Proms decision</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Is the BBC Proms drop Rule, Britannia?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Dame Vera Lynn breaks her very own chart record</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It had been ultimately confirmed through the Proms that orchestral versions from the songs could be performed this season, using the lyrics not sang because of coronavirus limitations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Less performers is going to be permitted on stage, that makes it harder to do the songs having a traditional chorus.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The BBC stated sang versions would return entirely for 2021, however.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In May, 30 days before her dying, Dame Vera grew to become the earliest singer to attain a United kingdom top 40 album, beating her very own record, together with her finest hits collection.</p>', 'BTS, UK chart top 10 hit', '_114160185_gettyimages-1202254783_1598818621.jpg', '2020-08-31 00:17:01', '2021-08-17 19:59:37'),
(97, 4, 7, 36, 'james-bond-composer-david-arnold-says-music-industry-on-precipice-1598818790', 'James Bond composer David Arnold says music industry on \'precipice\'', 0, '<p>A number one composer, who labored on five Bond films, has spoken of his concerns for future years from the music business following the coronavirus lockdown.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>David Arnold, who composed the background music for Casino Royale and Independence Day, stated the was &quot;on the precipice&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Should there be not a way of getting a communal experience with live music I believe that will be considered a disaster,&quot; stated Arnold.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The federal government stated it&#39;d invested &pound;1.57bn inside a grant plan for music venues and organisations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Arnold stated many musicians were earning most out of live concerts, however these have been cancelled because of the lockdown.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I additionally think the way through which music is shipped through streaming services is inequitable,&quot; he stated.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many musicians have criticised payments provided by services like Spotify, Apple Music and Tidal, which may be less than $.003 per stream, but streaming is growing in recognition using the public.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&#39;Waste of potential&#39;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Arnold, who co-authored the background music for BBC drama Sherlock and it was musical director for that 2012 Olympic games, added: &quot;I believe we&#39;re on a precipice. It&#39;s nearly impossible like a music performer to earn money. Many will, but a great deal will not.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Arnold, who increased in Luton, stated the nation runs the chance of getting &quot;a swimming pool of musicians from individuals who are able to afford to get it done from the moneyed background... a dreadful waste of potential&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He recognized the colleges he visited - Beechwood Primary and Challneys Boys&#39; School - for uplifting him to experience music.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Each of individuals schools were outstanding in that they incredibly passionate and brilliant music teachers,&quot; he stated, adding he was &quot;pretty convinced&quot; they inspired him to become composer.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I wondered why a developed must have been so looking forward to music. I figured there has to be an incentive,&quot; he stated.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Novelist and comic author Neil Gaiman, who labored with Arnold on Good Omens, also told the BBC: &quot;My greatest fear for lockdown would be that the communal experience with likely to see somebody play won&#39;t exist anymore.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport spokesman stated government measures to aid the background music industry incorporated &quot;&pound;3.36m for 135 venues across England vulnerable to collapse in the coronavirus pandemic&quot; and &quot;grants and loans from your unparalleled &pound;1.57bn cultural recovery fund&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Socially distanced indoor performances are now able to occur so we persuade folks to aid our wonderful music venues which are opening by booking tickets and visiting them once more,&quot; he stated.</p>', 'James Bond, David Arnold', '_113564653_mediaitem113564652_1598818790.jpg', '2020-08-31 00:19:50', '2021-08-16 14:06:54');
