(163, 7, 3, 47, 'director-cuties-received-death-threats-through-a-netflix-movie-poster-1599318918', 'Director Cuties \"received death threats\" through a Netflix movie poster', 0, '<p>Director Cuties said he received death threats after the film&#39;s poster was criticized for the sexization of children.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Netflix apologized and removed the image after receiving significant response on social media last month.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Now director Monkey Dukure told Deadline he had &quot;received multiple death threats&quot; because of the poster.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He said Netflix CEO Ted Sarandos called him directly to apologize after the poster sparked controversy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cuties were initially presented at the Sundance Film Festival in January and received positive reviews from critics.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Things went pretty fast because after the delay [due to the coronavirus] I was completely focused on releasing the film in France. I found the poster at the same time as the American audience,&quot; said Ducourt.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;My reaction? It was a strange experience. I didn&#39;t see the poster until I got all these reactions on social media, direct messages from people, and attacks. I didn&#39;t understand what was going on. Then I went and saw what it was like. the poster. &quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Nuanced and sensitive film&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cuties follows an 11 year old boy who joins a dance group. Ducure says he wants to tackle the problem of sexualization among young girls.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Netflix featured scantily dressed girls on their billboards for the award-winning French drama that sparked online disapproval and a petition asking Netflix to reject the film.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, many have defended the film, saying Netflix didn&#39;t depict it accurately on the poster.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cuties has released in French theaters and is coming to Netflix this month</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This film is meant to provide commentary on the sexualization of teenage girls - rather than support it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;The truth of the film, which is reflected in the reviews and audience reactions, is that it is a nuanced and sensitive story about a young girl caught between cultures,&quot; said Deadline&#39;s Tom Greater.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In an interview with the publication, Dukure himself stated, &quot;I have received a lot of attacks on my character from people who have never seen the film and thought I was actually making a film apologizing for the hypersexualization of children.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Actress Tessa Thompson wrote on Twitter: &quot;Disappointed to see how her position is in the marketing field. I got answers from everyone. But it didn&#39;t quite fit the film I watched.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dukure said he got a &quot;very supportive&quot; message from those who watched the film and &quot;overwhelming support&quot; from the French government.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He added that the film was used as a teaching tool in his home country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In its apology, Netflix said that the promotional image &quot;does not represent&quot; the film itself and &quot;deeply regrets the inappropriate artwork&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;After that we had some discussions back and forth. Netflix apologized publicly and privately to me,&quot; explained Ducourt.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He confirmed that he had received a direct call from Ted Sarandos, Co-CEO of Netflix, but did not provide details of the discussion.</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<p>Cuties, originally titled Mignonnes, will be released to streaming services later this month.</p>\r\n</div>', 'Death Threats, Posters, Director', 'Maimouna Doucoure_1599318918.jpg', '2020-09-05 19:15:18', '2021-08-16 16:27:14'),
(164, 7, 3, 36, 'jane-garvey-leaves-the-womens-class-1599319002', 'Jane Garvey leaves the women\'s class', 0, '<p><strong>Jane Garvey television company will leave Women&#39;s Hour at the end of this year, the BBC confirmed.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Garvey has presented programs offering women&#39;s perspectives on the world since 2007.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the new year now there will be a new Radio 4 series of its own.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;It is a real privilege to play a small role in the history of this very special radio program,&quot; he said, adding how proud he was of his relationship with the audience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;On an unforgettable day, I interviewed David Cameron in the morning and Mary J. Blige in the afternoon. There is no other job like them,&quot; he said.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;But celebrities are not the reason people get involved in women&#39;s studies. The program still talks about problems and challenges that others don&#39;t approach. I am very proud of our relationship with the audience and the trust we have.&quot; they made us. &quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&quot;Great stay&quot;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>During the show, Garvey helps mark major legal changes for women, including 100 years of women&#39;s suffrage and the 50th anniversary of Abortion.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He interviewed Sally Chalen, who was released from prison when forced control became a crime, and actress Rose McGowan about her experiences with Harvey Weinstein and the #Metoo movement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Radio 4 supervisor Mohit Bakaya said there were &quot;few&quot; people &quot;to compare&quot; to Jane Garvey&#39;s brilliance &quot;when it came to&quot; radio presentation art. &quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;And while I understand that after 13 years as a clock women&#39;s representative, it is time to move on, I am glad she is staying online,&quot; she said.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Jenny Murray (left) and Jane Garvey were guests at Women&#39;s Clock 2016.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Garvey&#39;s new 9:00 am program starts in April 2021 and shows his interview &quot;People with unusual stories&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The podcast that is also moderated is Fi Glover entitled Fortunately ... with Fi and Jane, will be included in the broadcast schedule starting January 2021.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lady Jenny Murray left the women&#39;s class</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Earlier this summer, Garvey Damen&#39;s colleague Jenny Murray announced that she was leaving the show after 33 years.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lady Jenny is the longest-running presenter in Radio 4&#39;s 74 year history.</p>', 'Jane Gravey, Leaves', 'Jane Gravey_1599319002.jpg', '2020-09-05 19:16:42', '2021-08-15 19:52:20'),
(165, 7, 3, 51, 'mulan-critics-condemned-the-release-of-the-disney-remake-on-the-small-screen-1599319133', 'Mulan: Critics condemned the release of the Disney remake on the small screen', 0, '<p><strong>Disney&#39;s Mulan has received mixed reviews, with many reviewers saying it should be shown in theaters.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This live remake of the 1998 animated film was originally due for release in March but has been delayed by the coronavirus outbreak.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As a result, it is now available for rent in the UK for &pound; 19.99 via the Disney + streaming service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Why doesn&#39;t Disney put this on screen?&quot; Asked Robbie Colin to The Telegraph.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He described it as &quot;a visually stunning but heartless film&quot; adding that &quot;his big win is lost on the small screen&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;There is no scene, maybe even in [Director] Nicki Caro&#39;s film, that doesn&#39;t deserve to be seen on a scale larger than a living room,&quot; he said.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Empire&#39;s Beth Webb agrees that the small screen makes the film &quot;detrimental&quot;, adding that it feels like &quot;crying shame&quot; walking through the theater.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But he praised the film itself, writing: &quot;Mulan is not only the best live Disney adaptation to date, but an enchanting, touching and prickly show.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Caro previously directed Whale Rider and The Zookeeper&#39;s Wife before joining Mulan with Liu Yifei.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When Caro was appointed to direct Mulan in 2017, commentators noted that she was only the fifth woman in history to make a film with a budget of over $ 100 million (&pound; 75 million).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, some critics pointed out that large film budgets did not produce successful films.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Times&#39; Keven Maher gave the film only two stars in a review entitled &quot;How to screw up a $ 200 million film&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Describing the film as &quot;a structural catastrophic revival,&quot; he added, &quot;Mulan was careless, illogical and drunk with political correctness.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He concluded, &quot;Mulan is just showing us what we know all along. That women are just as good as boys, and that they are like their male predecessors (I mean the man who directed The Lone Ranger, Jack Giant Slayer, and Tomorrow land). ) can screw up a $ 200 million film. &quot;&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mulan told the story of a young Chinese girl who learned that her frail father had to be summoned to join the army.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Worried that he would never survive the rigors of war, he disguised himself as a man and took his place.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The original animation grossed $ 304 million (&pound; 244 million) worldwide when it was released in 1998.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dulcie Pierce of The Sun was super cool for a new live remake and gave him three stars.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;While there are some spectacular battle scenes with large casualties - but not at all bloodless -, there is a lack of humor in this version, which makes it unsafe and without a smile,&quot; he said.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The film received the same enthusiastic response from Vanity Fair&#39;s Richard Lawson, who said he &quot;managed to die.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;The new Mulan is a long-range action film with really cool battle choreography but no admiration. Even the disgusting remake of Beauty and the Beast is not so boring and unstable,&quot; he said.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Mulan&#39;s not bad. It&#39;s just a sluggish and lifeless product that is unlikely to overcome danger or attract a new generation of fans.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Charlotte O&#39;Sullivan of Evening Standard praised Yifei&#39;s &quot;stunning&quot; headline on her four-star live remake.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Liu often looks 13, but he&#39;s actually 33,&quot; wrote O&#39;Sullivan. &quot;She has a face you never tire of. There is something Meryl Streep has in her soul and all her movements are magical.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The power of Disney&#39;s nostalgia during the pandemic</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Why is Mulan facing a boycott</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Disney dropped Mulan after #MeToo</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He added, &quot;I had to kill Caro and his cameraman, Mandy Walker, so that most viewers would only see this on the small screen (Mulan was made for IMAX).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;But nothing can reduce the size of a character moving and moving. I am as sporty as socks in bed, but for many reasons this film changed me.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Variety&#39;s Peter Debruge also praised Yifei, writing, &quot;While not very convincing in disguise - muddy cheeks are not suitable for men - Liu commands our attention, as does his character as an imperial soldier.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He continued, &quot;Caro decided to prefer spectacle over loyalty by putting so much into the film that it seemed fast.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;On the other hand, their whirlwind approach invites you to take another look and provides a clean and elegant image that lasts far longer than Disney&#39;s unique offerings such as Dumbo, Alice, and Wonderland.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Peter Bradshaw of The Guardian, in his three star rating, described it as &quot;a great conversation machine washable - even though the envelope wasn&#39;t really pushed&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;The fight scenes are very well managed, well viewed and as interesting as anything else in the film, although for me the CGI illusory brilliance on the show diminishes its visceral power,&quot; he said.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;In the end, there was nothing &#39;wrong&#39; with Mulan,&quot; said James Laxford of Metro. &quot;This is a sweet adventure film with sleek graphics that showcases Caro&#39;s abilities on a big budget.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;He&#39;s struggling, however, with the same problems that puzzled the rest of the remake, and a more serious tone that makes you wonder if this is really the spectacular Disney family that many were expecting.&quot;</p>', 'Critics, Disney remarks', 'Cinemas in March_1599319133.jpg', '2020-09-05 19:18:53', '2021-08-18 02:27:52'),
(166, 7, 3, 84, 'filming-for-batman-was-suspended-after-robert-pattinson-tested-positive-for-the-coronavirus-1599319559', 'Filming for Batman was suspended after Robert Pattinson \"tested positive for the coronavirus.\"', 0, '<p><strong>The photo of Batman was discontinued again a few days after the restart after the Corona virus was blocked.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The break in the photo, confirmed by Warner Bros., is because lead actor Robert Pattinson has tested positive for the virus, according to US media.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Warner Bros. said a production team member isolated but didn&#39;t say who.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Filming began in Glasgow earlier this year but has been suspended due to the pandemic.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A studio spokesman said, &quot;A member of the Batman production has tested positive for Covid-19 and is isolated according to established protocols. Filming has been temporarily suspended.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vanity Fair reports that British actor Pattinson, 34, caught the virus days after filming resumed near London after a six-month delay in filming.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Batman&#39;s media signature was found by the film crew at Glasgow&#39;s Necropolis Cemetery</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Batman was originally slated to be released in June 2021, but has been postponed to October 2021.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Twilight star Pattinson follows in the footsteps of Christian Bale, Ben Affleck, Michael Keaton and George Clooney as Gotham City superheroes in this latest film directed by Matt Reeves.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pattinson, who also stars in the current tenet tenet, did not comment on the report.</p>', 'CoronaVirus Test, Positive, Robert Pattinson, Batman', 'Batman_1599319559.jpg', '2020-09-05 19:25:59', '2021-08-18 09:25:09');
INSERT INTO `posts` (`id`, `user_id`, `category_id`, `views`, `slug`, `title`, `type`, `description`, `tags`, `image`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(167, 7, 4, 36, 'when-england-was-humiliated-by-iceland-at-euro-2016-1599319784', 'When England was humiliated by Iceland at Euro 2016', 0, '<p>&quot;Sorry it had to end like this, but these things happen.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;There is no doubt about the result. I think we have made a big step, but we have to make big decisions and not throw them away.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I want to stay two more years. However, I am pragmatic and know that we are in business with results. It has been a fantastic journey.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;This country needs new leadership. While that is not the route I recommend leaving Europe, I will be the first to praise our extraordinary strength.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The last week of June 2016 was not the so-called lull in the news. In a tumultuous week, Prime Minister David Cameron resigned after Britain chose to leave the European Union and Roy Hodgson, England manager, resigned after Iceland&#39;s humiliating defeat at Euro 2016.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The two men were already preparing to leave the speech we had together there. It feels like a lifetime right?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A lot has changed as England prepare to face Iceland again this weekend - but what happened so drastically that night in Nice and what happened next?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Game of Champions&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>England were colorful in the group but the winner after Daniel Sturridge&#39;s injury against Wales helped keep the last 16 against Iceland.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Supported in France by nearly 10% of the country&#39;s small population of 330,000 - like Coventry, as they are notified daily during the tournament - Iceland, with Thunder supporters, are the second team out of all.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A draw with eventual winners Portugal and time-lapse winners against Austria sent Iceland away, but they started as big underdogs against England, even if it&#39;s 10 years since the three Lions crashed out in major tournaments and only their last two. Had won 13 knockout matches. for 90 minutes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Let&#39;s be realistic, England are playing a championship match tonight,&quot; said Chris Waddle on the radio during the party.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I would be very, very surprised if England didn&#39;t win this game 2-0, 3-1,&quot; said Danny Mills.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Iceland have done very well but there are only a handful of players to choose from. If England don&#39;t win this game it will be a real shame.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>That&#39;s right Danny ...</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All the equipment, I don&#39;t know</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Hodgson&#39;s English side dominated all matches in France without looking clinical.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When Rahim Stirling was fouled by captain Wayne Rooney for his country&#39;s 53rd and final goal in a fourth minute penalty, the country relaxed and dreamed of a quarter-final against hosts France.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, no one gave Iceland this scenario. A big bet was booked just two minutes later, Carrie Arnason nodded and Kyle Walker lost to Ragnar Sigurdsson, who joined the equalizer.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Colbain Sigthorson then fired a shot that England goalkeeper Joe Hart could not contain, and Iceland were on the brink of sporting nirvana.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>England scored just two shots on goal in the second half and barely tested goalkeeper Hannes Thor Haldorson, who will have more trial days to shoot a music video in another of his life.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I was just lost in words,&quot; Waddle said at the final whistle. I know England are getting bad results but it is the worst result I have ever seen.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When British fans threw the St. George at the stadium, Hodgson ready to say goodbye, announcing his resignation in writing just 19 minutes after the full-time whistle.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Icelandic television commentator Gudmundur Benedictson reacted to his reaction and attributed the shock to the outcome of the aforementioned EU referendum ...</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Don&#39;t ever wake me from this wonderful dream!&quot; he roared. &quot;Live whatever you want, England! Iceland will play France. France-Iceland! You can go home. You can go outside Europe.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;You can go anywhere you want. The story continues.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Everything is just headphones.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>BBC Sport pundits and former players have not missed the chance to weigh in on a very sad night for the English players. Here comes the introduction:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Former England captain Alan Shearer: &quot;It was the worst performance I have ever seen from an England team. It was a tactical failure.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;We were scratched, pensive, scratched and completely discouraged for 90 minutes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Our players gave up tonight. We all played under pressure, they gave up and the manager gave up. He gave Manchester United teenager Marcus Rashford four minutes and is still doing more than anyone.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;We are blinded by the Premier League. We think this is the best talent in the world. No. We just rely on the joy of foreign players and managers. We are not as good as we thought.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Former England winger Chris Waddle on BBC Radio 5 Live: &quot;You didn&#39;t show up. You won 1-0 but conceded one goal on Sunday morning.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;We don&#39;t have leaders, they&#39;re all morons, they&#39;re all just headphones and you can&#39;t get anything out of them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I will never pay to see Iceland, but they have a great friendship. England will now say we build a team for Qatar, then we will build a team for Timbuktu.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Euro 2016: Experts have their say when England leave the tournament</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What Happened Next?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>France demonstrated what the most senior nation had to do against Iceland - without any intention of offending - by pumping them 5-2 in Paris.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Of course, Hodgson ended up at Crystal Palace a year before the glare and continued his excellent work at club level.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For the 11 English players who started playing in Nice tonight, the humiliation is not as extreme as you think. They will all play for England again, with Hart playing 11 more games before being sent off.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kyle Walker, Eric Deere, Stirling and Kane are back on the list this weekend to face Iceland.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After the match, according to Hodgson, BBC experts agreed that England &quot;should be approached as a young and dynamic manager who knows about young players passing&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Football Association took note and turned to Gareth Southgate. The rest is history in the semifinals of the World Cup.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I just had fun! You moved to Big Sam, right? It went well.</p>', 'England, ICeland, Humilatred', 'England vs Iceland_1599319784.jpg', '2020-09-05 19:29:44', '2021-08-14 22:42:37'),
(168, 7, 4, 55, '2020-us-open-alexander-zverev-beat-adrian-manarino-after-a-long-delay-1599320328', '2020 US Open: Alexander Zverev beat Adrian Manarino after a long delay', 0, '<p>German fifth Alexander Zverev said he had been told there was a &quot;very slim chance&quot; that his third round of the US Open with Adrian Manarino would be played because of coronavirus restrictions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Manarino was in a &quot;bubble in a bubble&quot; after his French counterpart Benoit Payre passed a coronavirus test.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The match started almost three hours late before Zverev won in four sets.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The American Tennis Association said the postponement was the result of &quot;dialogue with health professionals&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Zverev said: &quot;I was told there was a very slim chance to play. I was waiting and very calm. I am happy he can play.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;He&#39;s for Benoit Pyr&eacute;, so New York might call and say he shouldn&#39;t play. It&#39;s political, not us, the players are just sitting around.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The committee&#39;s statement came shortly after the players started their bout at Flushing Meadows at around 5:15 p.m. local time (22:15 BST).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>So far there has been no explanation why the match at Louis Armstrong Stadium has been postponed by two hours 45 minutes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Communication with the players continued in the afternoon to keep them updated,&quot; said USTA, adding that they would not provide further details &quot;given the sensitivity of the medical issues involved.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After the match finally started, Manarino threatened to thwart the first draw.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>23-year-old Zverev made a tight second set before improving significantly in the third and fourth to turn the game into a 6-7 (4-7) 6-4 6-2 6-2 win.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The world number 7 German was also supported by Manarino&#39;s movement, which was hampered by a leg injury.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;There is a lot of room for improvement, I&#39;m still not at my best,&quot; said Zverev, who will next face Spaniard Alejandro Davidovich Fokina.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Djokovic has traveled to the US Open for the last 16</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The defeat of Evans ended Britain&#39;s hopes of a US Open singles</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Osaka comes in three sentences</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Williams faces Stevens&#39; test in New York</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Players in the &quot;bubble in a bubble&quot; are not satisfied with USTA</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On Sunday, the French number 17 was replaced by Paire in the men&#39;s draw with Spaniard Marcel Granollers at the closed-door Grand Slam in New York.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>USTA did not mention Paire by name, but the player wrote on social media Monday that he is &quot;feeling good for the moment&quot; and has no symptoms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Those in contact with Payers have been informed that they can continue to participate in the tournament because they are in a &quot;bubble within a bubble&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This means they are not withdrawn from the event, but must live, train and train in a separate area next to the other main bladder.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This has led to allegations of changes to USTA rules by Argentine Guido Pella, who was forced to withdraw from the Western and Southern Open last week along with Bolivian Hugo Delien due to a positive fitness coach.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Both Pella, ranked 29th, and Delien lost their matches in the first round of the US Open.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>USTA has also been criticized by players in the group associated with Paire.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Belgium&#39;s Kirsten Flipkens told them Thursday they can leave the United States until next weekend but can continue to follow the same protocol.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, on Friday evening, he said they had now been asked to quarantine their rooms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Flipkens, who lost singles on Wednesday and doubles on Thursday, posted a video on Instagram in which she was unable to open a window in her bedroom and was accompanied by Queen I Want to Break Free.</p>', 'Alexander, adrian', '_114251024_zverev_1599320328.jpg', '2020-09-05 19:38:48', '2021-08-14 22:36:41'),
(169, 7, 4, 49, 'novak-djokovic-advanced-to-the-fourth-round-of-the-us-open-and-beat-jan-leonard-struff-1599320517', 'Novak Djokovic advanced to the fourth round of the US Open and beat Jan-Leonard Struff', 0, '<p><strong>Novak Djokovic, world number 1, comfortably reached the fourth round of the US Open and beat Jan-Leonard Struff in straight sets.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The 33-year-old Serb dispatched Germany&#39;s 28th seed in the evening session at the Arthur Ash Stadium 6: 3, 6: 3, 6: 1.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Djokovic, who is eyeing his 18th Grand Slam title, remains unbeaten in 2020 and has now extended his winning streak to 26.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But fourth seed Stefanos Tsitsipas crashed out of Greece after losing six match points to Borna Koric.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He led 5-1 in the fourth set but failed to cross the finish line and Koric won six games in a row to send the game into the decider, which the Croat won in an incredible 6-7 (2: 7) round of 6: 1. 4 4-6 7-5 7-6 (7-4).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The 27th seed, who won in four hours 36 minutes, will meet Australian Jordan Thompson on Sunday, who is looking to reach his first quarter-final at a Grand Slam.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The 26-year-old Thompson reached the fourth round in C major for the first time and defeated Mikhail Kukushkin of Kazakhstan 7: 5: 6: 4: 6: 1.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Djokovic will play in the fourth round in New York against Spain&#39;s 20th Pablo Careno Busta.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;It was a very good performance for my country and I can read his serve well,&quot; said Djokovic.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The second and third sets really felt great on the pitch.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Djokovic, who beat Briton Kyle Edmund in four sets in the second round, beat Struff lightly in just four games at the Western Open and Southern Open, also playing at Flushing Meadows last week.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Struff was more competitive here in the first two sets, but in the end there was no response to Djokovic&#39;s tireless strength and accuracy as the Serb fell in love in the fourth game of the third set before advancing to the final.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Zverev said he was told it was highly unlikely that a Manarino match would be played</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The defeat of Evans ended Britain&#39;s hopes of a US Open singles</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Osaka comes in three sentences</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The return of Shapovalov and Gofin is important</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Canadian Denis Shapovalov made a sensational setback to beat 19th American Taylor Fritz in five straight sets.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The 21-year-old Shapovalov lost two sets to one and won the fourth set 5-2 before reaching the last 16 of the Grand Slam for the second time in his career.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Next up for Shapovalov, who scored four sets in his first two wins, was Belgian ninth seed David Goffin.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Of course I was tired so it&#39;s impossible not to say after five sets. But we had such a long break that the body felt quite fresh overall,&quot; Shapovalov said.</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<p>Goffin did an easier job than you would expect Filip Krainovic, seeded 26th, to win 6-1 7-6 (7-5) 6-4.</p>\r\n</div>', 'Fourth Round, Beat Jan Leonard Struff', 'Novak Djokovic_1599320517.jpg', '2020-09-05 19:41:57', '2021-08-15 17:35:02'),
(170, 7, 4, 72, '2020-us-open-naomi-osaka-beat-martha-kostyuk-and-reach-round-four-1599320733', '2020 US Open: Naomi Osaka beat Martha Kostyuk and reach round four', 0, '<p><strong><u>Naomi Osaka received a test from Marta Kostyuk before going three sets to advance to the fourth round of the US Open.</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2018 champion, fourth, won 6-3 6-7 (4-7) 6-2 against the 18-year-old Ukrainian at Arthur Ash Stadium in New York.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The 22-year-old Japanese Osaka had to save five breakpoints in order not to lose 3-1 in the decisive game, but went on to win the last five games of Flushing Meadows.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>She will then play Annette Contaveite.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The world number nine has sustained a tendon injury that forced them to leave last week&#39;s West and South Open finals carrying a heavy rope around their left thigh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Osaka, who speaks out against racism in the United States, appeared in court in Flushing Meadows wearing a face mask named Ahmaud Arbury, a black man who was shot while jogging in Georgia in February.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He said he would wear a mask with a different name for every game he played in New York.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Elsewhere in the women&#39;s draw, German champion Angelique Kerber beat Ann Lee 6: 3: 6: 4 and will now play 28th American Jennifer Brady, who sent French Caroline Garcia 6: 3: 6: 3.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Garcia beat the most prolific Karolina Pliskova in the preliminary round.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sixth Czech Petra Kvitova raced past American Jessica Pegula 6: 4, 6: 3 and hosted her last 16 games against Shelby Rodgers, also of the US.</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<p>Petra Martic won 6: 3: 6: 3 against Russian Varvara Gracheva, while eighth seed Croatia took on 23rd seed from Kazakhstan, Julia Putintseva.</p>\r\n</div>', 'Noami Osaka Beat, Martha Kostyuk, Round Four', 'Naomi Osaka_1599320733.jpg', '2020-09-05 19:45:33', '2021-08-14 22:36:45'),
(171, 7, 4, 57, 'kenya-perez-jepchirchir-broke-the-world-record-for-the-womens-half-marathon-1599320912', 'Kenya Perez Jepchirchir broke the world record for the women\'s half marathon', 0, '<p>Kenya&nbsp;&#39;Perez Jepchirchir set a new world record for the women&#39;s half marathon.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The 26-year-old fled to Prague in one hour five minutes and 34 seconds to use the 37 seconds set by Ethiopia&#39;s Netsanet Gudeta in 2018.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Jepchirchir covered the first 10 kilometers of the Letna Park route in 16.5 turns in 30:32.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I thought I could run 1:04:50, but I&#39;m very happy,&quot; said the 2016 half-marathon world champion.</p>', 'Kerez Perez, Broken World Record', 'Kenya peres_1599320912.jpg', '2020-09-05 19:48:32', '2021-08-17 18:24:52'),
(172, 7, 4, 62, 'erling-braut-haaland-scored-but-norway-lost-to-austria-1599321149', 'Erling Braut Haaland scored, but Norway lost to Austria', 0, '<p>Erling Braut Haaland scored his first senior goal for Norway, but it was not enough to save his country from a home defeat to Austria in the Nations League.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Austria lead 2-0 in Group B1 with penalties from Michael Gregoric and Marcel Sabitzer.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>20-year-old Haaland from Borussia Dortmund reduced the deficit to his third appearance in Norway with good results.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tottenham&#39;s Stephen Bergwyn meets Netherlands in Group A1 against Poland.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Scotland is disappointed with Israel at Hampden</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Northern Ireland match against Romania</p>\r\n\r\n<p>League of Nations 2020-21: what, when, where ... and why?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The striker pushed the host into an empty net after receiving feedback from Hans Heitboer.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Liverpool captain Virgil van Dyke, who sent another &pound; 35 million to Manchester United, replaces Donnie van de Beek.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Poland lost their prolific striker Robert Lewandowski, who helped Bayern Munich win the Champions League last month.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Stephen Bergwine celebrates the goal for the Netherlands against Poland</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Stephen Bergwyn joined Tottenham from PSV Eindhoven in January 2020 for &pound; 27 million.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In another Group A1 match, Italy had to settle for one point after a 1-1 draw with Bosnia and Herzegovina.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Former Manchester City striker Edin Dzeko gave the visitors the lead before Stefano Sensei equalized.</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<p>The Czech Republic started their group B2 impressively with a score of 3-1 in Slovakia, while Kazakhstan won 2-0 in Group C4 in Lithuania and Albania 2-0 in Belarus.</p>\r\n</div>', 'Erling Braut, Norway Lost', 'Erline_1599321149.jpg', '2020-09-05 19:52:29', '2021-08-16 10:55:31'),
(173, 7, 4, 46, 'the-czech-republic-is-advancing-against-scotland-in-the-league-of-nations-uefa-said-1599321325', 'The Czech Republic is advancing against Scotland in the League of Nations, UEFA said', 0, '<p>The Nations League games in the Czech Republic on Monday will continue as planned, UEFA and the Czech association said.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Czech Republic initially announced that it was shutting down among the hosts following the Covid-19 outbreak.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Scotland travel to Olomouc on Sunday after opening their 1-1 draw with Israel on Friday.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Steve Clark&#39;s team will train in Edinburgh on Saturday afternoon as planned.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Open equality between Scotland and Israel</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Czech plans to win the 3-1 tie in Slovakia were stalled after West Ham midfielder Tomasz Sucek and RB Leipzig striker Patrick Schick were instructed to self-isolate after contact with employees backstage tested positive. virus.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Czech Federation postponed the trip to Bratislava for 24 hours while the entire team was retested and the players traveled 200 kilometers after being split into small groups.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After the match, the Czech association announced that the team would not play against Scotland &quot;due to representative decisions and the current situation with Covid-19&quot;. The statement added: &quot;The national team will end the ongoing preparations immediately after defeating Slovakia.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<p>Last week, UEFA set guidelines for scenarios in which Covid-19 affects competition. A game will continue as long as at least 13 players are available, including a goalkeeper.</p>\r\n</div>', 'Czech Republic, National League', 'czech Republic_1599321325.jpg', '2020-09-05 19:55:25', '2021-08-14 22:41:25'),
(174, 7, 4, 33, 'tournament-championship-rory-mcilroy-impresses-as-dustin-johnson-and-john-ram-1599321513', 'Tournament Championship: Rory McIlroy impresses as Dustin Johnson and John Ram', 0, '<p><strong>Rory McIlroy made it through his last three holes to survive last season&#39;s $ 15 million (&pound; 11.3 million) bounty on the PGA Tour Championship.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The 31-year-old hit six under par and finished nine under at East Lake Golf Club in Atlanta.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Event players are disabled due to accumulated FedEx Cup points this season. McIlroy started seven shots behind Dustin Johnson.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Johnson reported for the eighth quarter and shared the lead with John Ram.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Johnson and Ram - number one and number two in the world - traded back and forth, hitting 13 under the total.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ram opened a big shot to equalize with Johnson in the 15th minute, but the American took a long shot to regain the lead as his opponent watched.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Moments later, on the 16th, Ram moved for the fifth time for his round with the other birds, ultimately ensuring they would start the second day sharing the lead.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>McIlroy, who became a father earlier this week, retaliated against the handicap system to win the tournament for the 2019 tournament.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He stuttered with three birds and two missed the first nine holes earlier this year before finding five birds in the back nine.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>McIlroy won the event again in 2016 and one win this week will put him on Tiger Woods&#39; record of three Tour Championship wins.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>How tournament championships work</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Players collect points from the FedEx Cup over the course of the season and the top 30 in the overall standings fight against the tournament championship.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The top ranked player starts the tournament with 72 holes at 10 under par, while the second start starts at eight under par.</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<p>The third seed is cut down to seven, and so on until the fifth seed on the fifth floor. 6-10 seeds ranging from -4; 11-15 seeds ranging from -3; and so on for 26-30 seeds starting at the same level.</p>\r\n</div>', 'Dustin johson, John Ram, Tornament', 'Dustin_1599321513.jpg', '2020-09-05 19:58:33', '2021-08-14 22:42:11'),
(175, 7, 5, 30, 'galaxy-z-fold2-samsungs-third-attempt-at-a-foldable-smartphone-1599346680', 'Galaxy Z Fold2: Samsung\'s third attempt at a foldable smartphone', 0, '<p>Samsung has presented its third attempt with a foldable smartphone: the Samsung Galaxy Z Fold2 5G.<br />\r\nThe original Galaxy Fold smartphone was put on hold for several months after some initial reviewers found the screen was damaged or slightly damaged.</p>', 'Samsubg, Folding SmartPhones', 'Samsunng_1599346679.jpg', '2020-09-06 02:58:00', '2021-08-14 22:38:56'),
(176, 7, 15, 72, 'alexa-chung-is-currently-exploring-barbours-archives-for-aw20-1599899602', 'Alexa Chung is currently exploring Barbour\'s archives for AW20', 0, '<p><strong>Alexa Chung and hereditary brand Barbour have teamed up to create an archived outerwear collection for Fall / Winter 2020. </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This season, various styles of Barbour&#39;s jackets from 1920 are recreated through Chung&#39;s Alexa Lens. Silhouettes are updated, lengths are cut, and new details are introduced to give the classic style a new feel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The processing of classic rustic clothing for this town went unnoticed by Chung, the writer, television presenter and designer of the brand of the same name. For spring / summer 2020, in collaboration with Barbour, he created a wardrobe with a transitional cut, whose style is closely related to nostalgic influences.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Commenting on the new series, Chung said, &quot;We have approached the design process with more ambition, digging deeper into the Barbour archives to explore new silhouettes and make them ours. This collection is reminiscent of elements of Nostalgia fueled by childhood memories of seeing a more personable person. old in Hampshire wearing a similar uniform. &quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Paul Wilkinson, Barbour&#39;s global director of sales and marketing, added, &quot;Alexa&#39;s passion and passion for Barbour&#39;s archives has helped create another special collection that highlights Barbour&#39;s rethinking and enduring appeal - classic country style with good fashion sense.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<p>The eleven-piece collection includes nine new jackets and two new styles of baseball caps. The full product line will be launched on September 4 at Barbour.com and select retailers around the world.</p>\r\n</div>', 'Barbours, Fashions', 'Alexa_1599346948.jpg', '2020-09-06 03:02:28', '2021-08-18 05:49:47'),
(177, 7, 2, 59, 'cos-makes-its-resale-debut-in-uk-germany-for-resale-launches-planned-worldwide-1599347024', 'Cos makes its resale debut in UK, Germany for resale, launches planned worldwide', 0, '<p>The London-based Cos brand from H&amp;M Group is the latest retailer to enter the resale market. The label debuted with a new service called Resell. It was launched this month in the UK and Germany and &quot;allows colleagues to upload their favorite songs&quot;. The website will be available to buyers worldwide this fall.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;This is a new digital space that provides a platform to buy and sell favorite clothing for cos and gives the brand community the opportunity to remodel their wardrobes in a wise and sustainable manner,&quot; the company said.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The developments &quot;reinforce Cos&#39;s ambition and its path to become fully circular and renewable by developing innovative ways to continue the brand&#39;s commitment to quality and longevity.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Online options are &quot;prepared by the community&quot; so that consumers can sell old items and &quot;buy new items from brand archives from the past 13 years&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;With beauty in simplicity and functionality in the foreground, each piece will have a unique story and offer a timeless wardrobe bracket to carry the wearer through the seasons,&quot; explains Kos.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>More and more fashion retailers are entering the resale arena to increase their sustainability efforts and create closer relationships with the community of buyers who buy their goods</p>', 'H&M, Brand', 'H&M_1599347024.jpg', '2020-09-06 03:03:44', '2021-08-15 06:46:42'),
(178, 7, 2, 57, 'john-lewis-is-modernizing-the-offering-adding-more-than-30-new-fashion-and-cosmetic-brands-1599347093', 'John Lewis is \"modernizing\" the offering, adding more than 30 new fashion and cosmetic brands', 0, '<p>John Lewis announced that they will be adding more than 30 new brands to their lineup of fashion, accessories and cosmetics for fall. They have appeared in stores and online, and their debut will resume in October.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The company said the brand was chosen because &quot;they directly meet the country&#39;s new needs as customers opt for more casual wardrobe options and the brand will help modernize John Lewis&#39; offerings.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The product launch also included the debut of new leisure categories including Athleta, Adidas by Sidla McCartney, Isle Jacobsen, Hornbaek and Calvin Klein Performance. So far, &quot;the product was very popular and the sales exceeded expectations,&quot; we were told.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Fashion Director Christine Casulis said: &ldquo;As part of our modernization work, we are introducing new brands that we believe truly meet the needs of our current customers, regardless of whether they are comfortable, stylish clothes that are smart enough to be to say a zoom or a skin care products that enhance your natural skin tone. Our goal is to be the fashion partner of choice for brands. &quot;&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>New women&#39;s clothing labels already released or due to launch this month include The Fold &quot;luxury business wear&quot;, online brand Sosandar, Ganni shoes, Serena Rees Les Girls Les Boys label and UK luxury footwear brand, Malone Souliers, Trainers Fila and Fat Face.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Next month will be their Nibs, a small British pajama brand with handmade prints, as well as Celtic &amp; Co. sheepskin label. made in England.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Other debuts include Longchamp and jewelery from Dinny Hall, Astrid &amp; Miyu and Wanderlust + Co. There&#39;s also Goddesses Charms and the ongoing label Togetherband,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>New beauty products include Beauty Tech (with high quality beauticians from MZ Skin, Foreo, Dermaflash and Beglow) as well as upscale Olaplex hair care and Kate Somerville skin care.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With New Balance, an exclusive collection for the desert by John-Lewis Barbour by Ben and Marina Fogle, as well as the Soho Vintage Dukes Cupboard Store, there are also several men&#39;s wear releases.</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<p>In addition, the retailer has expanded its sports offering to include high-performance apparel, outerwear and equipment of Peloton, Apex Bikes and Arcteryx.</p>\r\n</div>', '30New Fashions, Modernizing', 'John Lewis_1599347093.jpg', '2020-09-06 03:04:53', '2021-08-13 23:06:57'),
(179, 7, 2, 65, 'lourdes-leons-front-campaign-for-the-new-adidas-collection-by-stella-mccartney-1599347350', 'Lourdes Leon\'s front campaign for the new Adidas collection by Stella McCartney', 0, '<p>Stella McCartney&#39;s latest collection for Adidas by Stella McCartney comes as she launches her new ad campaign featuring Madonna&#39;s 23-year-old daughter, Lourdes Leon.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Environmental activists and young feminists were also asked to choreograph and direct campaigns.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The resulting image introduces two new products, the Sports Wardrobe Collection and Winter Capsules. They show a group of trails selected from a new generation captured in attractive clothing and matching shoes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lourdes Leon worked with Brooklyn-based director Anna Pollack to direct the campaign, which included artist Uzumaki Tsepeda, dancer Lynette Paz, drummer Anisia Kim Butts, and artists Umu Traore and Henry Chesley.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Leon comments: &quot;My generation is sensitive to the needs of other people and the planet and the state of the world affects us. I have known Stella all my life and believe in her continuing vision for this new, universal collection of looks with Adidas. Amazing due to my campaign and me. have the freedom to create something that reflects that authenticity. We work with a team of friends who support us and share our values - dancing and with each other in the wild wetlands outside New York City move in harmony. &quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The collection includes a training cabinet and winter capsules. Wardrobe Workout kicks off on August 20 with tracks designed for three different workout intensities, while the Winter Capsule features weather-resistant outerwear and seasonal items and is released on September 17.</p>', 'Stella McCartney, Adidas Collection', 'Adidas_1599347349.jpg', '2020-09-06 03:09:10', '2021-08-15 02:52:57'),
(180, 7, 2, 74, 'hm-x-kangol-the-90s-streetwear-brand-is-back-again-1599347453', 'H&M x Kangol: The 90s streetwear brand is back again', 0, '<p>Bucket Hats fans will soon have the opportunity to discover H&amp;M&#39;s new collaboration with Kangol, which includes 90s streetwear and accessories with the British brand&#39;s iconic Kangaroo logo.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Do you remember kangol. The hip hop brand remained humble in recent years, almost everywhere in the 1990s. The streetwear brand will take the lead this year thanks to fast fashion giant H&amp;M with the participation of R&amp;B singer Mabel, who models and designs several outfits.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Kangol is very excited to be working with H&amp;M and Mabel on this collaboration. The collection perfectly reflects the essence of Kangol today and includes many new updates to streetwear styles,&quot; said Hamish Morjaria, Head of Brands and Licensing Partnerships at Kangol.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In addition to the legendary Bucket Hat, this 31-piece collection includes a down jacket, belt bag and oversized knitwear.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The &quot;Don&#39;t Call Me Ip&quot; singer designed two of her own songs and inspired her entire collection.</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<p>The collaboration will be available September 17 on hm.com and in select stores around the world.</p>\r\n</div>', '90s Streetwear, brand', 'Kanool_1599347453.jpg', '2020-09-06 03:10:53', '2021-08-17 02:35:19'),
(181, 7, 6, 60, 'amazon-plans-to-create-10000-jobs-in-bellevue-washington-1599347548', 'Amazon plans to create 10,000 jobs in Bellevue, Washington', 0, '<p>Amazon.com Inc. plans to create 10,000 additional jobs in Bellevue, Washington, over the next few years, the e-commerce giant announced on Friday.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The company is opening new offices in US cities amid a boom in its business, thanks to a surge in online orders during the blockade triggered by the coronavirus.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Amazon previously announced it would create 15,000 jobs in Bellevue, which is 10 miles from its headquarters in Seattle.</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<p>In April and May, Amazon employed 175,000 jobs, from warehouse workers to delivery drivers, to keep up with demand.</p>\r\n</div>', 'Amazon, Jobs', 'Amazon_1599347548.jpg', '2020-09-06 03:12:28', '2021-08-17 10:49:09'),
(182, 7, 2, 69, 'dolce-gabbana-alta-moda-as-rinascita-in-florence-1599347920', 'Dolce & Gabbana: Alta Moda as Rinascita in Florence', 0, '<p><strong>Nostalgia for a more innocent era, and one where Italy was emerging from another great drama, was the theme of Dolce &amp; Gabbana&rsquo;s Alta Moda show in Florence Thursday night, the first women&rsquo;s fashion collection by a major house shown on the planet since lockdown this spring.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Specifically, a certain wistfulness for an event in Florence in 1951, when entrepreneur Giovanni Battista Giorgini staged the First Italian High Fashion Season in his private villa. Marking the first ever women&rsquo;s ready-to-wear season in Europe; the initial spark in the development of the Italian fashion industry, and indeed the reemergence of the nation from the darkness of World War II.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Domenico Dolce &amp; Stefano Gabbana named this collection Rinascita, in English rebirth, in deliberate juxtaposition to Renaissance, their title for the previous evening&rsquo;s bespoke menswear collection, staged in Florence&rsquo;s city hall.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Back in Feb 1951, that first tiny &ldquo;season&rdquo; featuring 10 small local fashion designers &ndash; names like Emilio Pucci, Emilio Schuberth and Sorelle Fontana &ndash; attracted just six buyers, but it was an exceptional event, which started international press and fashion magazines speaking about Italian fashion. Moreover, just as the canny Giorgini called on local crafts people to present their best ideas to the North American buyers he convinced to come to Florence, this week Milan-based Dolce &amp; Gabbana had some three dozen companies of tiny artisans collaborate on their glamorous invasion of Florence.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The end result was a frequently brilliant display of sunny Italian &eacute;lan and optimism, albeit made in retro silhouettes, recalling that more gentle era.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As dusk fell over the capital of Renaissance, the first models marched down the steps of the garden of Villa Bardini, which sweeps spectacularly down the river Arno. A stunning crinoline with a marvelous illustration of the Duomo; accessorized with a multi-million-euro ruby necklace and delightful iris-shaped hat, debuted the show. Sumptuous chic throughout &ndash; from the satin ball gowns in a print of the Palazzo Vecchio topped by a jet black feather tank glistening with crystals, to the flowing A-Line silk coat done with a water-color image of the Ponte Vecchio.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Before Domenico and Stefano went into overdrive at the finale. A trio of gloriously golden straw dresses, bustiers and jackets recalling the early Fifties to a bird of paradise gown made of scores of canary yellow cock feathers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Post-show, guests dined al fresco on beautifully laid tables with superb silver centerpieces courtesy of Pampaloni, from designs dating back to the 16th century. A golden tinged dinner, each dish finished with edible gold leaf courtesy of Giusto Manetti, including a main course of a gilded filetto di manzo. Two of local artisans who contributed to three days of Dolce &amp; Gabbana events, including a haute joaillerie showroom; bespoke menswear show and wine tasting in Italy&rsquo;s greatest quality wine producer, Antinori.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;The image of fashion nowadays is very big: giant shows, huge boutiques and massive social media reach, but artisans have tiny businesses. Literally, when you visit them, their studios are very small. You are face to face with them as soon as you walk in the door!&rdquo; chuckled Domenico Dolce, who visited Florence eight times this year, individually meeting each of the artisans.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After marching all the way to the bottom of the stairway and back up, the cast posed before an arbor of giant pink roses and crimson bougainvillea. Whether a semi-sheer lace coat finished with yellow clothe lilies and trimmed with ermine or a ravishing white tulle cocktail with tiny hand-made floral buds, the craftsmanship was impeccable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The duo taking their bow to a Pavarotti and Joan Sutherland duet of Libiamo Ne&rsquo;lieti Calici, and to golden fireworks display, before a backdrop of the neo-gothic Basilica of Santa Croce, where Michelangelo and Galileo are buried.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A final Dolce &amp; Gabbana display from the designers, and their never-ending love song to their own country.</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&ldquo;That&rsquo;s what we do. Our m&eacute;tier is to create Italian fashion. And that&rsquo;s what people expect when they come to see Dolce &amp; Gabbana &ndash; Italy,&rdquo; concluded Dolce.</p>\r\n</div>', 'Alta Moda, Rinascita', 'd65d07ff7aba5c7ab98a2e187a0786673229276_1599347920.jpg', '2020-09-06 03:18:40', '2021-08-14 13:24:07'),
(183, 7, 2, 60, 'comme-des-garcons-is-out-of-season-at-the-paris-track-1599348031', 'Comme des Garons is out of season at the Paris track', 0, '<p>Comme des Gar&ccedil;ons and its design team have pulled out of the upcoming Paris Fashion Week, at a huge loss to the catwalk calendar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Comme des Gar&ccedil;ons, Junya Watanabe and Noir Kei Ninomiya will not be appearing in Paris during the SS21 season,&quot; the home side said in a surprise statement on Friday.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;The collection will be displayed in a mini-show or presentation in Tokyo from 19-23 October as part of our seasonal showroom there. The new season of the Comme des Gar&ccedil;ons will also be available for viewing,&quot; the statement said.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The move marks the first time that legendary Japanese designer Ray Kawakubo, founder of the Comme des Gar&ccedil;ons and the driving force behind the wildly trendy Dover Street Market boutique chain, has fallen off the French women&#39;s clothing calendar in four decades.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>77-year-old Kawakubo made his first appearance in Paris in the late 1980s and quickly established himself as a major creative performer, known for his asymmetrical silhouette. great conceptual passion and diverse influences. Kawakubo is a great designer and only the second designer alive to have a single show at the Metropolitan Museum.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;While his prot&eacute;g&eacute; Junya Watanabe is a cult designer with a unique following, he wins thanks to his highly experimental fashion and innovative fabrics and craftsmanship. Meanwhile aspiring star Kay Ninomiya, Kawakubo&#39;s former assistant, is best known for her non-standard designers and artisanal construction.</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Their joint decision to spend next season in Paris - scheduled for Monday 28 September to Tuesday 6 October - is tiring on the official calendar.</p>\r\n</div>', 'Garcons, Paris Sesontrack', 'Cat walk_1599348031.jpg', '2020-09-06 03:20:31', '2021-08-17 19:45:01'),
(184, 7, 2, 66, 'tiziana-fausti-invests-in-10-corso-como-1599348109', 'Tiziana Fausti invests in 10 Corso Como', 0, '<p>A new chapter begins at 10 Corso Como. The famous Milan concept shop founded and operated by Carla Sotsani has announced the arrival of a new partner: Tiziania Fausti, founder of the luxury multi-brand shop named after him, which has been operating north of Milan in Bergamo for 40 years.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The two countries formed &quot;a joint venture to expand and strengthen the presence of 10 Corso Como in the world market,&quot; he said in a statement, without providing further details on the company&#39;s structure. &quot;The aim is to create a dynamic reality that meets the new demands of the market.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The partners &quot;will share their projects for the future development of 10 Corso Como in Italy and around the world, in particular through the 10 Corso Como-the-Global-Shop digital platform, with the aim of promoting the sensory experience of 10 Corso Como in to expand the digital world. . &quot;output continues.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In recent years, the business known in Milan as a lavish temple has slowed and its difficulties have intensified due to the Covid-19 crisis. In particular, the retailer, which blends fashion, art, photography, music, lifestyle and food, had to close its New York stores in April, less than two years after opening.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>10 Corso Como was founded by Sozzani in 1991 and has since expanded to Seoul, where it operates two stores, and to Japan, where it offers two discounts at department stores in Tokyo operated by the Sogo Seibu Group. With its latest move, the company, known for its choice of modern designer brands, will benefit from the new boost and commercial experience of Fausti, who has special experience in the luxury sector.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Fausti, founder and president of Holding Exor, the holding company of various companies, opened its first boutique in 1979 in downtown Bergamo. Since then, the business has gone beyond women&#39;s clothing to acquire men&#39;s wear, children&#39;s fashions and accessories, and shops. 100 square meters, dedicated to Dior.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This prime address also offers various discounts for well-known brands including Saint Laurent, Balenciaga, Gucci, Ala&iuml;a, Chlo&eacute; and Celine. The group, which also runs a boutique in Switzerland - Tiziana Fausti Lugano - opened its Terrazza Fausti restaurant, lounge and bar last year and will open a Bergamo-based store The F1rst on Friday, dedicated to the younger. Targeted customer base with an emphasis on modern fashion and street wear. Dress.</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<p>According to information from FashionNetwork.com, Fausty took an operational role in managing 10 Corso Como. Sozzani will continue to run the business and participate in new projects, but will focus his efforts on the cultural activities of Fondazione Sozzani as well as his art gallery and bookstore. &quot;I am proud of this joint venture which will bring new energy to the management team at 10 Corso Como,&quot; he said.</p>\r\n</div>', '10Corso Como, Investment', 'Carla Sozzani_1599348108.jpg', '2020-09-06 03:21:49', '2021-08-13 17:29:45'),
(185, 7, 2, 108, 'henkel-acquires-a-majority-stake-in-cosmetic-brands-hellobody-banana-beauty-mermaid-me-1599348188', 'Henkel acquires a majority stake in cosmetic brands HelloBody, Banana Beauty, Mermaid + Me', 0, '<p>Through the operation, Henkel, owner of Fa, Schwarzkopf and Diadermine, was able to, among other things, expand the beauty care division&#39;s brand portfolio and presence in the D2C beauty market, as well as strengthen its digital and social marketing skills. in areas such as data analysis and fast innovation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>HelloBody, Banana Beauty, and Mermaid + Me are three &quot;green and clean&quot; consumer brands that are mostly sold in Europe. Between June 2019 and June 2020, they generated total sales of 100 million euros.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>HelloBody is widely represented on social media and is looking for strategic partnerships to make an impact. It is active in the skin care, hair and body care categories. Mermaid + Me focuses on hair care products while Banana Beauty is a makeup brand. Among them, they have more than one and a half million active customers and it is hoped that Henkel Beauty Care can increase its presence on social commerce.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;With this acquisition, we strengthen our portfolio with fast-growing premium brands in attractive categories. Immediate customer loyalty provides us with valuable insights that help us create significant innovations for the entire retail business,&quot; said Jens-Martin Schwarzler, Executive Vice President of Henkels Business. beauty.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The remaining 25% stake in the business will remain in the hands of Bjoern Keune and Gennadi Tschernow, founders of Invincible Brands Holding and Equity Investment Fund Capital D. Both the founders and the current brand management team will remain.</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<p>In fiscal 2019, Henkel&#39;s Beauty Division achieved sales of 3.87 billion euros, 1.8% less.</p>\r\n</div>', 'Body Creams, Cosmetics brands', 'Rose breeze_1599348188.jpg', '2020-09-06 03:23:08', '2021-08-14 18:20:37'),
(186, 7, 2, 63, 'essilorluxottica-will-appeal-the-grandvision-decision-1599348316', 'EssilorLuxottica will appeal the GrandVision decision', 0, '<p>Glasses maker EssilorLuxottica said on Friday it would appeal the court&#39;s ruling on the proposed takeover of GrandVision targets after losing a Dutch lawsuit that could jeopardize a deal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>EssilorLuxottica confirmed that it has decided to appeal the decision rejecting GrandVision&#39;s request for corporate disclosure, the statement said.</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<p>Last month, the Rotterdam District Court said EssilorLuxottica had failed to prove its allegations that the Dutch company GrandVision had violated the Takeover Pact by failing to seek approval for action to block the spread of COVID-19 across Europe. .</p>\r\n</div>', 'GrandVision, Decision', 'GrandVision_1599348316.jpg', '2020-09-06 03:25:16', '2021-08-17 22:15:59');
INSERT INTO `posts` (`id`, `user_id`, `category_id`, `views`, `slug`, `title`, `type`, `description`, `tags`, `image`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(187, 7, 2, 58, 'the-smcp-reports-the-losses-from-the-effects-of-the-pandemic-but-has-the-money-to-cover-them-1599348426', 'The SMCP reports the losses from the effects of the pandemic but has the money to cover them', 0, '<p>The results of the first half of the SMCP on Friday show how big a hit it will be when the pandemic rages across the globe and fads most distant from most consumers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The company may make a profit (albeit smaller) based on EBITDA, but fall to a net loss when sales fall.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The company&#39;s sales fell 31% to 372.8 million euros or 33.5% organically (excluding the De Fursac acquisition).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On a positive note, mainland Chinese sales continued to increase gradually in the second quarter under owners Maje and Sandro and returned to sales growth in June. The &quot;solid implementation&quot; of the Covid-19 action plan has helped mitigate the effects of the crisis and saved the company more than 60 million euros. And the company has plenty of cash to finance its business activities with 219 million euros in banks at the end of June.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But the good news can&#39;t hide the weak figures. Adjusted EBITDA fell in the first six months of this year from &euro; 141 million in the previous year to &euro; 55.1 million, while profit-adjusted EBIT of &euro; 66.5 million at this time fell to &euro; 29.7 million. In 2019, the net loss was &euro; 88.5 million after a profit of &euro; 17.2 million 12 months ago. This figure includes a EUR 42.6 million loss to the reputation of other brands (Claudie Pierlot and De Fursac) due to the impact of the pandemic on these brands.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, the company did not present its four brands separately, nor were there any regional distractions or ideas about Q3 retail.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>CEO Daniel Lalonde said the results were heavily impacted by the pandemic but the group is &quot;very much prepared to tackle this challenging period because the fundamentals remain strong: we benefit from a geographically balanced portfolio of international brands, a strong position.&quot; in e-commerce and in agile organizations &rdquo;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He added that the company will continue its Covid-19 action plan until the second half of this year while working on its top priority to &quot;increase brand appeal, make a single channel between e-commerce and physical stores to build seamlessly and seamlessly.&quot; and acceleration of sustainable mode &rdquo;.</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<p>What really happened in the first half? The blockade measures in most countries (especially in Asia in the first quarter and in Europe / North America in the second quarter, as well as the cessation of tourist flows in the region) hit it hard. However, it said: &quot;While in-store traffic remains weak, the group reports solid conversion rates.&quot; This is something that many other companies report as consumers trying to shop seem more determined to buy. This was helped by a sales growth of 15% in e-commerce.</p>\r\n</div>', 'Smcp Reports, Losses', 'SMCP_1599348426.jpg', '2020-09-06 03:27:06', '2021-08-16 22:56:22'),
(188, 7, 2, 68, 'tommy-hilfiger-embraces-modest-fashion-by-releasing-his-first-hijab-1599348747', 'Tommy Hilfiger embraces modest fashion by releasing his first hijab', 0, '<p><strong>America&#39;s top fashion label Tommy Hilfiger has released its first hijab, a move that some see as a welcome change from greater diversity, others as a wise decision to join a growing segment of the fashion market.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Hilfiger hijab has the initials &quot;TH&quot; all over the garment and is made of fine jacquard fabric. Available in ivory and &quot;Captain Sky&quot; gray. Last month the label dressed in a Halima Aden model in a bespoke burqa for Sports Illustrated.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This is not the first time the fashion industry has realized the importance of what is called simple fashion. At New York Fashion Week 2016, Aniesa Hassibuan became the first designer to present a collection where all models wore a hijab. Dolce &amp; Gabbana, DKNY, and Mango created &quot;Ramadan Collection&quot; during simple fashion weeks from Miami to Amsterdam around the world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After the fashion industry has been criticized for a lack of diversity and racism following the protests against Black Lives Matter, Hilfiger&#39;s hijab can show that major fashion brands are promoting inclusive practices. However, Hassana El-Yakubi, founder of modest fashion brand PFH, said it also shows a changing market, not a culture.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;This is a clear indication of a growing Muslim consumer culture that is more profitable and growing more than ever,&quot; said El-Yakubi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>According to the Islamic fashion industry, that will be $ 88 billion by 2025, according to Grand View Research. &quot;I think the timing reflects the need to respond to the growing market desire of consumers - especially Millennials and Generation Z - to be more inclusive than the brands they support,&quot; said Arthur Zatskevich, editor-in-chief of fashion publications. Everyday Women&#39;s Clothing Industry.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Research shows that younger consumers care less about enrollment and more about choices that reflect their own values.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After years of being &quot;kidnapped&quot; from mass fashion, the perception of simple fashion has changed. &quot;I think we are experiencing constant cultural change rather than fleeting styles that are temporarily popular,&quot; said El-Yakubi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;More and more retailers are focusing on adding and adding products to their range that support modesty,&quot; said Christa Corrigan of retail intelligence firm Edited. He said 10% of shops covered by the company sell such clothing, compared to just 2% in 2019.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Zaczkiewicz said: &ldquo;It&#39;s important to understand that simple fashion is not a trend. People live like that. &quot;&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, most observers believe Hilfiger&#39;s hijab is just a small step towards wider acceptance of Muslim associations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Even though it has become a norm or a fad, the fact remains that Islamophobia and anti-Muslim sentiment have been at the forefront of all time in the United States,&quot; said El-Yakubi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Violence against hate crimes reached its highest level in 16 years in the US last year, while 52% of hate crimes in the UK were committed against Muslims in 2019.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Because modest clothing is usually considered a phenomenon spearheaded by women wearing the hijab, they usually bear the burden of that belief,&quot; said El-Yakubi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Muslim clothing remains a political lightning rod and keynote for Islamophobic rhetoric.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In July, the state of Baden-W&uuml;rttemberg banned the burqa and niqab in schools. Similar bans are followed in Sri Lanka and Denmark. Other countries that have banned Muslim clothing are Latvia, Austria, Bulgaria and Belgium.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Last year, French sports goods label Decathlon scrapped plans to sell sports hijabs after politicians reacted to religious tensions and refocused on Muslim women&#39;s clothing.</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<p>However, the removal of the hijab follows Hilfiger&#39;s promise to be more inclusive. Last month, parent company PVH announced a program to increase opportunities for people with bright colors in the company.</p>\r\n</div>', 'Hijab Fashion, embraces modest fashion', 'Hijab fashion_1599348747.jpg', '2020-09-06 03:32:27', '2021-08-17 09:08:26'),
(189, 7, 2, 60, 'estee-lauder-discusses-glowing-lines-amidst-the-black-lives-matter-protests-1599348827', 'Este Lauder discusses glowing lines amidst the Black Lives Matter protests', 0, '<p>Est&eacute;e Lauder is reviewing the language and marketing of her skin lightening cream after accusations of cultural insensitivity to competing cosmetic companies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The company, which owns 25 brands, including Bobbi Brown, Clinique and La Mer, did not disclose which products would be affected. She will evaluate the use of terms such as lightening and lightening in her products and consider whether a particular product line should have a broader nuance, Susan Acad, Est&eacute;e Lauder senior vice president, told Bloomberg.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This happened when a cosmetic company on social media was accused of being hypocritical for selling skin lightening products while supporting the Black Lives Matter movement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>An Instagram post about racial justice by Unilever, which sells India&#39;s most famous skin lightening product, formerly Fair &amp; Lovely, sparked angry comments. &quot;Your skin lightening brand has shaken thousands of people&#39;s perceptions of beauty and self-worth because of their skin color. How about fighting for justice by getting rid of it?&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Renowned writer and chef Padma Lakshmi wrote on Instagram about how the product made him feel insecure throughout his childhood. &quot;Colorism is a permanent social force in India and many countries in South Asia. I know it made me feel insecure growing up. We need to destroy this dangerous remnant of colonialism by showing off all skin colors.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In June, officials sent a letter to William Lauder, CEO of Est&eacute;e Lauder, urging him to do more to address racist issues. As a result, the company is committed to doing better, including working with more black-owned companies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Est&eacute;e Lauder isn&#39;t the first cosmetics company to take action. In June, Johnson &amp; Johnson announced that it would discontinue selling a skin lightening remover for dark spots under Clean &amp; Clear&#39;s Neutrogena Fine Fairness and Clear Fairness lines that are sold in the Middle East and Asia. Unilever also said it would rename its Fair &amp; Lovely line, now called Glow &amp; Lovely, and remove the words bright, bright, fair, fair, white and white from all of its brands and products. L&#39;Or&eacute;al says it will also remove words like whites and whites from its products.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The beauty industry has been criticized for not caring about different skin tones. In 2017, Rihanna&#39;s Fenty Beauty was seen as innovative, releasing 40 key notes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Because blacks don&#39;t rule, the beauty industry has always sidelined us and told us that our bodies and hair are not good and need to change,&quot; said Sami Schalk, professor of gender and women&#39;s studies at the university from Wisconsin-Madison to the Business of Fashion.</p>', 'Fashion, Highlights', 'Lightening and brightening products_1599348827.jpg', '2020-09-06 03:33:47', '2021-08-15 12:23:56'),
(190, 7, 2, 49, 'how-to-make-a-wardrobe-from-used-capsules-1599348929', 'How to make a wardrobe from used capsules', 0, '<p>Think vintage or secondhand clothing, and you&#39;ll probably think of silly prints, t-shirts for long-term group trips, and colorful tea dresses. They&#39;re all great if retro is your thing, but what if you like the casual look? With a campaign like Oxfam&#39;s Second Hand September, where we only need to buy second hand clothes for 30 days, is it possible to use purchases such as building blocks for capsule robe spaces?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;People are forced to use used goods for a variety of reasons,&quot; said Fanny Moyzant, co-founder of resale site Vestiaire Collective. &quot;Building a unique wardrobe is one of them,&quot; he said. &quot;It&#39;s so exciting to look for pieces you can&#39;t find anywhere else.&quot; Another reason, he says, is the desire to be greener. &quot;With the shift toward more conscious consumption, the concept of investing in quality clothing that will last for many years and building a used capsule wardrobe is becoming increasingly attractive.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The items in your capsule cabinet will vary based on your lifestyle and taste. However, these are clothes that you will wear over and over again and you don&#39;t have to worry about. General topics arise among experts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Moizant&#39;s &#39;uniform&#39; usually consists of jeans or high-waisted trousers, a t-shirt or knitwear, and then I&#39;ll wear sneakers, moccasins or high heels depending on the day.&quot; For Bay Garnett, thrift stylist and singer, thrift store shopping means &quot;long black skirt, shirt, gray T-shirt, denim shirt, nice cashmere sweater, and blazer.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For Holly Watkins, who has been selling second-hand clothing for decades, from market stalls to sales through her One Scoop shop, this includes &quot;some great jeans ... some great shirts - I love white shirts and striped shirts, denim jackets and jackets. Sophie Grattage and Dexter Burgess-Hunt, who run the Sylk Store on online resale site Depop, believe that &quot;every wardrobe needs high-waisted classics,&quot; as well as a simple T-shirt, some vintage jeans, and &quot;and a minimalist casual shirt. &quot;They all buy most of their used wardrobes - and that&#39;s how they do it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It&#39;s hard to tell if jeans are comfortable enough to wear when they close up or if they&#39;re really uncomfortable. Watkins started with Levi&#39;s 501s, which he has been wearing since he was a teenager. &quot;For me, crop denim is great,&quot; he said. &quot;For 20 years I have been selling, there are still many requests.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For all jeans, he said, &quot;You have to try them on.&quot; The first time you buy a brand of jeans, it can be a tough job. &quot;Buy online at a place you know will come back or go to a vintage store. Take your time,&quot; he says.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Shirts are a little tricky because they are often a little tricky,&quot; said Watkins. She recommends checking out the men&#39;s clothing section of the charity shop. &quot;Little men&#39;s shirts can look very nice or oversized.&quot; And he suggests choosing fabrics like silk and cotton over synthetic fibers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He admits that the illusory classic, the perfect white shirt, is hard to find secondhand because it&#39;s often a little tinted. But while she&#39;s had some super whitening accidents, she says that a small bottle of bleach or vanishing for white is &quot;brilliant if you soak it&quot;. The manufacturer offers to soak for half an hour, but Watkins recommends an overnight soak: &quot;You&#39;ll be amazed what comes out.&quot; He also recommends using white vinegar on the armpits.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Whether you&#39;re looking for something tidy for the office or a flock of seagulls that are too large, there&#39;s a used blazer for you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Take the time to find out what you are looking for,&quot; said Moizant. If you search online, &quot;Make sure you have narrowed your search and done some research. Don&#39;t be afraid to ask the salesperson additional questions or details about a particular measurement.&quot; &quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If the blazer doesn&#39;t fit well despite the sizing, don&#39;t be afraid to play with it, says Watkins, who often removes layers and shoulder pads to soften the shape and bring it closer to you. body. If you or a friend aren&#39;t sewing, it&#39;s a good idea to familiarize yourself with a local dry cleaning service. &quot;Most will work with a fairly experienced tailor who can get you a 12-15 pound blazer. You can try and it will suit you,&quot; he said.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Garnett recommends a little blazer: &quot;If it looks a little manic, try it, because sometimes light jackets look really stylish - a little rough at the edges or look too big.&quot; see how it feels. Sometimes you will be surprised. &quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Jumper</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ebay is full of old cashmere sweaters which are worth a look. Garnett also recommends going to a charity shop and looking for an old V-neck in the men&#39;s section. Moizant is a big fan of the big, &quot;never out of date&quot; turtleneck. He advises, &quot;Pick iconic brands and classic silhouettes that you know are timeless and can be used for any occasion.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But there is one word on everyone&#39;s lips: moth. &quot;I found a lot of good knitwear, but it broke,&quot; says Watkins. Unfortunately the moth will get all the tissue it deserves.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When shopping for produce, keep the sweater in a bright place, place your hands under the sleeves, and straighten it properly for moth damage. &quot;You don&#39;t want to bring something that might contain moth eggs into your home,&quot; says Watkins.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When you take something home and it has more holes than you think, Watkins recommends an invisible fix: &quot;If it&#39;s not completely destroyed, I&#39;ll take it.&quot; If you don&#39;t have these skills, they are easy to learn. And here, says Watkins, dry cleaning can be a valuable resource.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Of course there are always modern used items. &quot;You can definitely find modern used cashmere,&quot; says Watkins. She recommends eBay and says that as long as people are honest about the state of the sale, you should be fine.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Grattidge and Burgess-Hunt recommend that you have cloth bags in your closet: &quot;They protect your clothes from moths ... and keep items from losing their shape by hanging.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>How to make a used wardrobe capsule Sweatpants - I have attached a photo of Alexander Wang&#39;s knitwear and a painted vintage tie. Right now Ikat Dye is being sold as a main dye for me! Very easy to carry!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Smart pants will be in a lot of people&#39;s wardrobes. &quot;When I look for black pants, I look for brands like Comme des Garcons, Yohji, Yves Saint Laurent ... their shapes have stood the test of time,&quot; says Watkins. &quot;From a current perspective, I&#39;ve always thought brands like Joseph were good - brands like this are pretty easy to get.&quot; Look for good fabrics like wool and know their measurements.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>According to Watkins, if a vendor doesn&#39;t provide online measurements, don&#39;t be afraid to ask - he doesn&#39;t put them as defaults on his site, but he&#39;s always happy to send them to someone if he wants. &quot;It only takes one second,&quot; he said.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As with jeans, if you&#39;ve found pants that match, study their sizes and look for other pants with similar shapes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sports clothing</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Although not always considered a staple food, sports subordinates are already on the list of many.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I like a good track,&quot; said Watkins. She&#39;s still looking for a replacement for the hippest pair she&#39;s ever had - a pair of sweaty Betty&#39;s pure merino wool that &quot;can&#39;t make their knees wide&quot; picked up at a charity shop. Brands like Joseph, Akne, and Ganni, expensive second-hand items, are worth looking for secondhand.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Old-fashioned tracksuits were very different from what people are looking for today in this era of prestigious clothing, says Watkins. Still, he&#39;s a fan of Fruit of the Loom, whose items appear regularly on eBay or Depop.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>_________________________________________________________________________-</p>', 'wardRobe, Capsules', 'Fashion is abiut how adapt_1599348929.jpg', '2020-09-06 03:35:29', '2021-08-13 06:18:49'),
(191, 7, 2, 100, 'reuse-renew-recycle-old-fashioned-future-1599349164', 'Reuse, renew, recycle! Old fashioned future?', 0, '<p>Fashion changes can often be denoted by semantics. Take the word &quot;deadstock&quot;. Formal, an industrial term that is often interpreted as saying that manufacturers do not use substances, have recently become part of our common language. Brands using raw milk in their projects are becoming increasingly popular with consumers who appreciate the idea of saving waste from landfill. The fact that we even address this in fashion articles shows that sustainability is a priority in a post-pandemic world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Of course, as with most keywords, there is much more to it than meets the eye. In some fashion corners, this term is more likely to refer to unused and unused items rediscovered by handsome vintage dealers, as well as a number of contacts with old warehouses. Deadstock Nike Jordans, for example, would be a holy grail theme for the confident hip animal. This idea is also called into question in terms of its environmental benefits. Some argue that while using inanimate products is definitely better than making from scratch, brands can actually use what is known as &quot;available inventory&quot; - additional fabric manufacturers produce together with orders in the belief that it will be sold.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Without clear terminology, brands can name dead products, dead stocks for them because nobody buys them, not marketable items,&quot; said Dillis Williams, director of the Center for Sustainable Fashion at London College. fashion. &quot;This is a controversial area. The terminology can correct abused concepts and reinforce others.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Maybe we should return to a related term - &quot;upcycling&quot;. Often used to describe crafty projects at home that could, for example, turn an old water bottle into a toothbrush holder. Designers make it a touch of fashion by directing vintage clothes and fabrics. Virgil Abloh&#39;s latest collection for Louis Vuitton uses fabric from the brand&#39;s archives. Up to half of the Marine Serre collection is created this way. Collina Strada&#39;s latest collaboration with Browns uses clothing from the secondary market in Accra. This is a straightforward commentary on how the West shipped second-hand clothing to Africa before - because of their enormous volume - many of them ending up in landfills.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Not just high-end designers. A smaller group of labels is using this technique to turn old clothes into new ones. The Berlin-based Fade Out label, founded by Andrea Bonfini and Nicola Gomiero, uses 70% vintage clothing to create new clothes. Dresses and tops cost around 200 euros. Bonfini said this was done partly for environmental reasons, but also for aesthetic reasons. &quot;The vintage denim and the fabrics we recycle influence the uniqueness of each and every piece. We deconstruct and assemble all the clothes as a game of mosaic tiles every time they are different and unique.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Goodbye Francis&#39; Carly Sheck uses vintage blankets made everywhere from home permits to eBay to create his own work, including the $ 25 (&pound; 19) face mask featured on vogue.com. &quot;I want to show people that beautiful things can be made from textiles that are already there,&quot; he said. &quot;I firmly believe that some of these old textiles are made with more love and care, so they tend to last longer than newer materials made today.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Both Bonfini and Scheck enjoyed the original design. &quot;Usually you sketch out your idea and then you get the material,&quot; says Shek. &quot;However, with vintage or secondhand materials, usually the fabric is found and then the design is directed. I think this involves a lot more problem solving and a different part of the brain than most designers are used to.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For Bonfini, life can provide inspiration and material. &ldquo;The vintage bag collection was born after I made my own clothes. His bag was found at home after I moved, &quot;he said. &quot;For a cut made with an old football team scarf, we have to thank a friend who sells vintage clothing in Berlin and stumbled across a supply of scarves.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<p>Williams says these designers weren&#39;t the first to discover the fun of climbing. She checks the names Bethany Williams and Christopher Rayburn, but also cites Stella McCartney&#39;s first collection from 1996 using vintage lace and silk, and depicts JJ Knoki, a designer who became famous with items at the same time. Made from vintage t-shirts and denim cuts, like &quot;The Don Works That Way&quot;. She wanted to emphasize that &quot;we need multiple approaches&quot; to really increase the environmental impact of fashion, &quot;but the opportunities to reuse, renew and recycle clothing in the UK are enormous&quot;. The main purpose? &quot;We have to find ways to make a living and create fun and creativity with less clothing.&quot;</p>\r\n</div>', 'Reuse, fashion', 'Reuse_1599349164.jpg', '2020-09-06 03:39:24', '2021-08-16 01:06:57'),
(192, 7, 2, 97, 'kamala-harris-what-do-their-sneakers-mean-1599349260', 'Kamala Harris: What do their sneakers mean', 0, '<p>As a colorful woman wearing sneakers in the campaign, she introduced changes in political dress and more. Kamala Harris&#39; nomination for Joe Biden is historic: as the daughter of immigrants from Jamaica and India, she is the first woman of color to be on the presidential ticket of a major party. He was also the first person to wear campaign shoes in a prominent position.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>These are minor fashion details, but they relate to the larger cultural moments we&#39;re living in. &quot;Sneakers are one form of shoe that has entered many women&#39;s closets as part of a larger challenge to the ancient concept of femininity,&quot; says Elizabeth Semelhack, author of Sneaker X Culture: Collab. There has traditionally been a standard label for women&#39;s shoes in politics - either alpha (see: Nancy Pelosi stilettos, leopard-print heel by Theresa May) or conservative (sliding sandals by Elizabeth Warren, cat heels by Hillary Clinton, matching trousers)) . Semmelhack believed Harris&#39; shoes signal action. &quot;Sneakers are the same fashion as you want to roll up your sleeves,&quot; he said. They argued that Harris was a &quot;woman in action.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Harris&#39;s love for bohemian shoes was first noticed last year when he was a Democratic presidential candidate and appeared on Converse Chuck Taylor All Stars. As she told The Cut, &quot;I walked through the airport in Converse sneakers. I have the entire Chuck Taylor collection: a black pair, a white pair, I have a non-knit lace, one makes lace, which I wear in hot weather, that I wear it when it&#39;s cold, and the kind of platform I wear overalls. &quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Since James Dean wore it, Converse has been a shoe for rebels and outcasts. &quot;Chuck Taylor has a long history of using ideas to convey authenticity, not advertising,&quot; says Semmelhack. Fans include Andy Warhol, Ramones, Karl Lagerfeld and Kurt Cobain.</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<p>Nick Engwall, founder of the sneaker story, believes that choosing Harris shoes over the traditional business attire that politicians wear during a campaign could mean that he &quot;will attract others like me who think it makes him more authentic or normal.&quot; Jeff Carvalho, co-founder of the site Streetwear Highsnobiety&#39;s website, says she will &quot;help her connect not only with a younger audience but with the all-important Gen X crowd.&quot;</p>\r\n</div>', 'Kamala Harris, Sneakers, Fashions', 'Kamala Harris_1599349260.jpg', '2020-09-06 03:41:00', '2021-08-14 14:44:34'),
(193, 7, 2, 86, 'how-to-protect-autumn-from-your-summer-dresses-1599349447', 'How to protect autumn from your summer dresses', 0, '<p>A dress that doesn&#39;t have as many paella lunches this year as it should be is the perfect outfit for early fall.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The changes are good. It&#39;s like the whole premise of fashion when you think about it. It&#39;s an investment in the direction we&#39;re going to go from here. And here we are on the first weekend of September, the most important moment for any changes in the fashion calendar. We usually pack our summer closets here and visit the shops to freshen up in the fall.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But the changes in 2020 have occurred in a big way. In times of massive turbulence, I don&#39;t think it&#39;s a true reflection of a zeitgeist to talk about how the sage in green is a new blush in pink, or a chorus collar is a new polo tie or whatever. This is a time when fashion moves up to a more basic level.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mobilizing a summer wardrobe in late August does not make sense this year. Could summer end if it never happened? June without Glastonbury, July without school year end, August without the usual beach rituals. Our summer dressing room is actually not that tired. Not for lack of experience: since I didn&#39;t come to Ibiza, I wore my favorite silver caftan around the campfire in Dorset. And although there weren&#39;t any long, lazy days at the beach, my underwear saw a few short sharp drops in the North Sea. But it&#39;s not the same.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Instead of shopping again for fall, fashion is now about adapting a wardrobe from last season to the next. We have to be; Sometimes the incentive to buy a new product comes in yen for a relatively cheap hype that doesn&#39;t take up our time or effort.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Start with a summer dress: a light or patterned sleeveless dress that doesn&#39;t get as many paella lunches as expected this year is the perfect starting point for an early fall outfit. The vibration of the jacket increases gravity and keeps your hands warm. Models with a pale background like this dress are more complicated to wear over time, and you need to add tights to the equation. So make the most of it while you can still walk barefoot.</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<p>Oh, and by the way, sage is the new blush in pink. And the chorus collar is a new polo bond. There&#39;s something new in there if you want it. But the most revolutionary part of this season is the fact that you don&#39;t need anything new at all.</p>\r\n</div>', 'Fashion, Autumn from summer', 'Fashion is abiut how adapt_1599349447.jpg', '2020-09-06 03:44:07', '2021-08-14 05:14:23'),
(194, 7, 2, 82, 'why-silk-masks-are-better-for-your-skin-1599349553', 'Why silk masks are better for your skin', 0, '<p>Recent conversation about augmentation with renowned Manhattan dermatologist Dr. Dandy Engelman, have a family fight with me. The sleek black silk facepiece I wear to please loved ones who reject my claim of comfort over &quot;just a mother to be a fantasy,&quot; she says, is the best skin for us. Engelman (Consultant Dermatology at Elizabeth Arden) coined the term &quot;mask&quot; after seeing an increase in private patients - especially those wearing PPE at work - with acne, friction sores, clogged pores, and irritation during the crisis. 19</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Her first recommendation (before using beta hydroxy acid at night: I swear by Paula&#39;s Choice Skin Perfecting 2% BHA Liquid Exfoliant (10 to 30 million pounds) sweep up after cleansing) to switch to silk facials whenever possible. It causes the least amount of friction in any tissue, prevents minor skin wounds on the cheeks and nose from healing, clogs pores and blemishes in the process (Engelman calls it the &quot;acne mechanism&quot;).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Silk is also cool and breathable, which is an important aid in the chin area. My dermatologist approved mask mentioned above comes from Slip (&pound; 39), my favorite hair tie maker. It&#39;s expensive but beautifully finished, multi-layered (two or more layers of silk required to be safe), and has a flexible cord moving over the bridge of the nose while in surgery that removes skin dimples and stops creeping into my eyes. I love it, or as much as you can like masks in a pandemic.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The best calming serum</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But you don&#39;t have to spend that kind of money. A face mask that is comfortable and skin-friendly should be accessible to everyone. British independent brand Golden Hour makes masks across the country that come in a variety of colors and cost &pound; 9 (cheaper if you buy a few). Also very comfortable is a silk and ginger (&pound; 25) facecover in a soft charcoal hue that&#39;s flushed in pink and sand. They have a secure, elastic stitch that is quick to hit when you walk into the shop - important if, like me, you don&#39;t have to worry about the straps you see on much nicer masks.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are tons of brightly colored silk versions on the market - flowers, dots, Liberty prints, cartoons, stripes. But I might be wrong to turn it down because it is difficult to match with clothes and it reminds me of the crazy mask pediatricians wear to distract a happy child who is about to lose his attachment.</p>', 'Silk Masks, Fashion, Better Skin', 'Sali Hughes_1599349553.jpg', '2020-09-06 03:45:53', '2021-08-17 20:30:10'),
(195, 7, 2, 47, 'tara-simon-becomes-the-general-manager-of-too-faced-1599349776', 'Tara Simon becomes the General Manager of Too Faced', 0, '<p>Est&eacute;e Lauder Corporation announced on Friday that the Ulta Beauty Tara Simon Fellowship will join the group as Senior Vice President and Global General Manager of the Too Faced brand, effective August 31. President John Demsey.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In his new role, Simon will be responsible for developing and executing the global Too Faced strategy and leading the branding team. He will also work with brand founders Jerrod Blandino and Jeremy Johnson to find ways to build closeness with existing Too Faced fans and attract new customers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This is not the first time Simon has worked with Blandino and Johnson since 2006, at Ulta and Sephora.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Most recently, Simon worked as an SVP for the prestigious beauty merchandising at Ulta. In this role, she oversees the unprecedented growth of cosmetic retailers in overall market share in the prestigious beauty sector.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>During his tenure, Simon dramatically increased the number of prestigious brands Ulta sold. He&#39;s pulled exclusive product launches from big names like Mac and Clinique and successfully launched smaller start-ups.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Prior to joining Ulta in 2012, Simon was Chief Merchant and SVP of Planning and Inventory at Beauty Brands in Kansas for nearly four years. Previously he worked as a DMM for Sephora from 2006 to 2008.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Tara is a visionary strategic executive and brand manufacturer with extensive experience in prestigious beauty and makeup,&quot; said Demsey in a statement. &quot;This will help bring the unique history of the brand, which focuses on Jerrod&#39;s inspiring products and experiences, to new audiences around the world. His vast experience and ability to manage profitable business results in the multi-prestigious specialty beauty area makes him.&quot; is uniquely suited for taking Too Faced to a new level of success. &quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Simon, who holds a BBA in Marketing from the University of Texas at Red McCombs School of Business in Austin, has received a number of awards including the 2018 Cosmetic Executive Women Achiever Award.</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<p>She also served on the Harvard Women&#39;s Board of Directors, supported the Kennedy School&#39;s women&#39;s and public order programs, and served on the CEW National Board of Directors. He was previously a member of the NPD advisory board.</p>\r\n</div>', 'Fashion, General manager', 'Cosmetics_1599349776.jpg', '2020-09-06 03:49:36', '2021-08-12 00:10:09'),
(196, 7, 7, 39, 'coronavirus-arrests-during-protests-against-the-blockade-in-australia-1599349990', 'Coronavirus: arrests during protests against the blockade in Australia', 0, '<p>Australian police, amid protests against the blockade, have made dozens of arrests, of which hundreds have taken part across the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In Melbourne, the epicenter of the outbreak in Australia, about 300 people rallied despite the month-long clampdown.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He suggested that a possible travel bubble with New Zealand could boost tourism and help revitalize the economy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Without a vaccine, we might have to live like this for years,&quot; he warned.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Australia&#39;s arrest of the blockade is controversial</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Why is Melbourne seeing more cases when it&#39;s banned?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Australia&#39;s confirmed virus cases have tripled to more than 26,000 in the past two months, with the death toll rising from 104 to 748 over the same period.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What happened during the protests?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In Melbourne, protesters chanted &quot;Freedom&quot; and &quot;Human Rights&quot; amid an increasing police presence.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Victorian Prime Minister Daniel Andrews was also highlighted: &quot;We are in a city where Daniel Andrews&#39; healing is actually worse than what happened,&quot; protester Fiona Kat told AFP.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Police said they arrested 15 people - 14 for breaking lockdown rules and one for assaulting a police officer who had ripped his head off. They also fined more than 150 for breaking the lockdown.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Andrews condemned the incident: &quot;It is not safe, it is not smart, it is illegal. In fact, it is very selfish when people protest there,&quot; he told reporters.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There were smaller demonstrations elsewhere, including two in Sydney and one in Byron Bay, which local media said turned violent. Police arrested 14 people, including three people who allegedly assaulted police officers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The protests have been fueled in large part by extreme online groups exploring conspiracy theories on viruses and vaccinations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Police have previously criticized the arrest of a pregnant woman for promoting protests online. On Friday, officials stormed the home of a former bodybuilder and conspiracy theorist who also urged people to join the event.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Why is Melbourne enforcing such a strict ban?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Victoria has been on a six-week blockade since July to control the coronavirus outbreak that sparked a second wave in Australia. In Melbourne, the state capital, authorities have passed rules on stay and curfews. The castle closed many shops and forbade gatherings across the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Victoria is responsible for 75% of all infections in Australia and 90% of all deaths. The state reported 11 deaths and more than 70 new infections on Saturday, up from 725 new infections on August 5. However, after the restrictions were put in place, more health officials were hopeful for five weeks.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On Sunday, Mr. Andrews will announce easing restrictions. It follows calls from the federal government and the Australian business community for this purpose. The state accounts for about a quarter of the country&#39;s economy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, he called for caution. &quot;Until health problems can be resolved, there will be no economic improvement,&quot; he said.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What about other Australians?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There were five new coronavirus infections in New South Wales as of Saturday, one in Queensland and one in South Australia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Morrison said plans to reopen state lines in December would include developing ways to manage virus hotspots.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, Western Australia&#39;s largest geographic state is against the plan, while other states are not controlling the virus. No local broadcasts for 129 days and no restrictions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Western Australian Prime Minister Mark McGowan said the long desert borders would remain closed to save lives and protect major mining operations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After a national cabinet meeting on Friday, Morrison said Australia could also apply a hotspot approach to New Zealand.</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<p>It has since been confirmed that former Cook Islands Prime Minister Joseph Williams has died of the coronavirus in New Zealand. This was the second death in two days and a total of 24.</p>\r\n</div>', 'WORLD, ARRESTS, PROTEST', 'Arrested aUSTRALIAN_1599349990.jpg', '2020-09-06 03:53:10', '2021-08-15 23:40:17'),
(197, 7, 3, 82, 'biggest-lost-coach-erica-lugo-underwent-surgery-to-remove-loose-skin-after-losing-160-pounds-1599582108', 'Biggest Lost Coach Erica Lugo underwent surgery to remove loose skin after losing 160 pounds', 0, '<p><strong>Biggest Loser trainer Erica Lugo shared candid photos of her body after losing 160 pounds and announced that she will have surgery to remove her saggy skin.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Publication of transparency that is real, scary, and harsh. AF is nervous as I write and share,&quot; she took two photos on Friday September 4 showing excess skin and stretch marks in the middle after she tucked her thighs. &quot;I worked really hard to lose 160 kg. I am proud of the muscles I have built and I am more proud of the fact that I was able to hold my weight for 5 years.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;That&#39;s what I look like,&quot; he continued. &quot;Saggy skin hasn&#39;t been a part of my journey for 5 years. I&#39;ve always been nice to it. It&#39;s a sign of my struggles, but the more I start to build muscle and get slimmer, the more sagging my skin gets. No exercise or diet helps loose pockets in the skin of my thighs and stomach. &quot;&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lugo, who previously battled thyroid cancer, admits that &quot;it was not an easy decision&quot; to plan surgery.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.usmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Erica-Lugo-Wedding-4.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=86&amp;strip=all\" style=\"height:50%; width:100%\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;The Biggest Lost&quot; coach Erika Lugo has a surprising social distance from marriage</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;It&#39;s something I&#39;ve been researching for years,&quot; he continued. &quot;I&#39;ve been going back and forth for years and finally I&#39;m scheduled for September 22 with @athenixbody and I can&#39;t be more nervous, scared, but excited!&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He pledged more than 647,000 followers &quot;to follow every second of this journey&quot;. I just got the initial invitation to prepare for all postoperative care. 2 weeks till we go! &quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lugo, who coached The Biggest Loser earlier this year, told us Weekly in July that she struggled with her body image after arriving at the show location and told people in the dressing room not to wear tops.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Before and after! See &quot;The Biggest Loser&quot; in roles from premiere to finale</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;They were very kind and listened to me,&quot; he told us. &quot;They are so used to practicing the harvest all the time that they just have to change what they give me and I love it. ... I mean,&quot; I have a baby, I weigh 322 kilograms, it works. It&#39;s not that I have stretch marks and sagging skin that sticks to it, and I just don&#39;t like showing them on national television. &quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The gym owner admits she &quot;gets a lot of warmth because my body type is the trainer at the show,&quot; but says thousands of women end up feeling accepted as a size 8 or 10.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I have cellulite and stretch marks,&quot; says Lugo. &quot;I&#39;m very strong, but it doesn&#39;t affect how well I can train and how strong I am or how well I know fitness.&quot;</p>', 'Erica Lugo, Weight loose, 160 Pound', 'Erica_1599385296.jpg', '2020-09-06 13:41:36', '2021-08-15 22:42:57'),
(198, 7, 3, 73, 'sophie-turner-was-seen-with-joe-jonas-for-the-first-time-since-the-birth-of-their-daughter-villa-1599385431', 'Sophie Turner was seen with Joe Jonas for the first time since the birth of their daughter Villa', 0, '<p>You look good mom! Sophie Turner has been photographed in public with her husband Joe Jonas for the first time since giving birth to their first child.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Chronology of the relationship between Sophie Turner and Joe Jonas</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The 24-year-old Game of Thrones Fellow is seen holding hands with the 31-year-old Jonas Brothers singer as they stroll around their Los Angeles neighborhood in photographs from the Daily Mail on Thursday, September 3.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The couple wore sunglasses and face masks for the walk, and Turner demonstrated her postpartum weight loss in fitted white jeans and a striped T-shirt. The singer of &quot;Sucker&quot; was wearing black shorts and a black scarf.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Us Weekly confirmed in February that the couple, who got married in a surprise ceremony in Las Vegas in May 2019, are expecting their first child and become Turners &quot;in the middle of summer.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Hottest married couple in Hollywood</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Until future Emmy confirmed her pregnancy, she showed her growing baby on several trips with Jonas as they were quarantined amid the coronavirus pandemic.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Turner admitted in a March interview with Conan O&#39;Brien that she &quot;likes&quot; to be isolated at home with her husband.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I&#39;m an introvert. I&#39;m a homebody. If I could stay at home all day, I&#39;d do it, so that&#39;s great for me,&quot; said the Dark Phoenix actress. It also helps Jonas pamper and cook for his pregnant wife - later that month, he shares a photo of croner with a large bowl of pasta. &quot;One of the many advantages of marrying a good Italian man,&quot; she stamped the photo.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The couple met Willa on July 22 and confirmed the arrival of their baby girl in a statement five days later: &quot;Sophie Turner and Joe Jonas are excited to announce the birth of their baby.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A source told us that her daughter&#39;s nickname was &quot;not a last name or any abbreviation,&quot; but &quot;a name they chose some time ago, before the baby was born.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The two have yet to release a photo of their joy pack, but returned to Instagram on August 7 to spread an important message in the COVID-19 crisis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Jonas posted a photo of himself and his wife sitting on the sofa wearing white T-shirts on their Instagram story along with the message &quot;USE THAT MASK&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>More than a week later, Turner shared a photo of herself with her husband on Instagram as the Camp Rock Fellowship celebrated its 31st anniversary. &quot;Happy birthday to my love / grandmother / baby daddy,&quot; he wrote in the black and white photo.</p>', 'Sophie Turner, Joe jonas, Daughter Birth', 'Sophie_1599385431.jpg', '2020-09-06 13:43:51', '2021-08-17 19:22:59'),
(199, 7, 2, 79, 'the-leopard-shell-dress-you-will-wear-from-work-to-wedding-1599899452', 'The leopard shell dress you will wear from work to wedding', 0, '<p>Us Weekly partners so we can receive compensation for some links to products and services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Who doesn&#39;t love leopard prints? We&#39;ve been wearing it since we were kids and while we fear it will go out of style at some point, it&#39;s only solidifying itself as a major fashion bridge. It&#39;s a playful print that can be neutral, flattering, forgiving and never lose its cool!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are many leopard print options to choose from, but the only drawback is that it&#39;s harder to find a mediocre piece to find a great one. But hey, that&#39;s why we&#39;re here. We searched, filtered and narrowed down the options and these dresses were at the top!<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B07Z33TR6Q/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;linkCode=sl1&amp;tag=usmagazine05-20&amp;linkId=4ba4635bea0a68c3aedd49166db0f50a&amp;language=en_US\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This cotton shell dress is smooth, fluid, and casual, but not a dress that sacrifices sophistication for comfort. She won&#39;t settle for anything less than either and that&#39;s why we love her!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This dress features a buttoned front and an A-line silhouette with a smoky waist to accentuate your figure and tie the look together. It&#39;s also elastic so you can get more exercise. There are also skinny ties so you can add cute accents with ribbons. Another pretty detail that we love is the sleeves. The fabric is gathered to look like bell sleeves, but then put back on the wrist, stretchy so you can easily place the cuffs on your hands while putting on and taking off this dress. It also prevents the sleeves from falling over your fingers and becoming a nuisance all day long!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This dress is currently available in four colors. They all have leopard prints - just different options. The khaki version gives you the classic leopard look in a color that matches the big cat&#39;s real fur. But you can also try green, red, or maybe white if you want this snow leopard!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This dress is a great buy because it is affordable but can be worn anywhere. I go to work? Wear a pair of leather or leather mules, tie your hair in a low bun, and grab your cute glasses in a blue glow. Are you going to a wedding? It&#39;s time to get accessories with all your sparkly accessories and metal accents. Various silver stilettos with gemstone headbands, shiny clutches ... yes, you are sure to have this photo booth ready!</p>', 'Leopard shell, Dress, Wedding', 'Kirundo l_1599386375.jpg', '2020-09-06 13:59:35', '2021-08-12 00:11:40');
