(256, 4, 4, 26, 'football-sweden-vs-portugal-1599601121', 'Football: Sweden vs Portugal', 0, '<p>Portugal&#39;s Cristiano Ronaldo turned into the primary European to score 100 global objectives in men&#39;s football and afterward passed that mark with the two objectives in the Nations League prevail upon Sweden.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The skipper twisted a shocking free-kick into the top corner - the 57th of his profession - to arrive at the milestone.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Juventus forward, 35, at that point terminated in a fine second from fresh.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ronaldo, who played 81 minutes, is inside eight objectives of the world record.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Iran&#39;s Ali Daei - the main man to score more global objectives than Ronaldo - hit 109 during his playing profession from 1993 to 2006.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The following top scoring current players are India&#39;s Sunil Chhetri (72) and Argentina&#39;s Lionel Messi (70).&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The outcome implies shielding Nations League champions Portugal have won their initial two rounds of the current year&#39;s occasion.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Their errand was made simpler when Sweden had Gustav Svensson sent off for two appointments - yet there was a drawback to their success as Manchester City&#39;s Bernardo Silva was supplanted subsequent to enduring a presumed muscle strain.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Portugal could have won by additional with Bruno Fernandes hitting the bar and Ronaldo, on his 165th top, constraining a decent spare from Robin Olsen as he looked for a cap stunt.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Practically 50% of Ronaldo&#39;s global objectives have come since his 30th birthday celebration - 49 objectives in 47 games.</p>', 'Sweden vs Portugal', 'Portugal_1599601121.jpg', '2020-09-09 01:38:41', '2021-08-12 21:02:12'),
(257, 4, 4, 56, 'pfa-player-of-the-year-kevin-de-bruyne-and-beth-england-named-2020-winners-1599601309', 'PFA Player of the Year: Kevin de Bruyne and Beth England named 2020 winners', 0, '<p>Manchester City midfielder Kevin de Bruyne has won the Professional Footballers&#39; Association men&#39;s Players&#39; Player of the Year grant.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>De Bruyne, 29, applauded City administrator Pep Guardiola for helping him win the honor, saying &quot;he just leaves me alone me&quot;.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Beth England, 26, won the ladies&#39; honor having helped Chelsea do the Women&#39;s Super League and League Cup twofold.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Liverpool safeguard Trent Alexander-Arnold, 21, won the men&#39;s Young Player of the Year grant.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Jordan Henderson was among five Liverpool players to be named in the Premier League group of the period.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Also, Manchester United and England forward Marcus Rashford won a PFA merit grant for his work battling kid food neediness.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>De Bruyne beat a year ago&#39;s champ Virgil van Dijk, Alexander-Arnold, Sadio Mane, Henderson and City colleague Raheem Sterling to the honor decided in favor of by his kindred players.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Belgian is the primary Manchester City player to win the honor since its initiation toward the finish of the 1973-74 season.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;This is a major honor,&quot; he said. &quot;To be casted a ballot by your partners, rivals from different groups who you generally play against on the field. That they vote in favor of you for best player; it&#39;s stunning.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;It&#39;s possibly odd that I&#39;m the first at City, seeing all the great players who played there previously and who are as yet playing. In any case, it&#39;s ideal to speak to the club.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On Guardiola, he stated: &quot;He gives me a great deal of opportunity; I don&#39;t have the foggiest idea why, that is only the manner in which it goes between us.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;He knows in a single manner I will consistently put the group first and afterward clearly in the event that I can help myself I will do that. He confides in me totally.&quot;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For the third back to back year, the top honor for the men&#39;s class went to a player whose group didn&#39;t win the Premier League title.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Reds pair Van Dijk and Mohamed Salah were the previous two victors and proceeded to lift the trophy last season, having approached in earlier years.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>De Bruyne, however, contributed a record-equalling 20 helps and scored 13 objectives as Guardiola&#39;s side came sprinters up to Jurgen Klopp&#39;s group last term.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Britain, in the interim, scored 21 objectives in all rivalries for the Blues and forestalled Arsenal&#39;s Vivianne Miedema asserting the ladies&#39; honor twice in succession.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Britain additionally beat her Chelsea partners Sophie Ingle, Guro Reiten and Ji So-yun, and Arsenal&#39;s Kim Little.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;It&#39;s a gigantic honor to be decided in favor of by your kindred friends, so thank you to each and every individual who decided in favor of me,&quot; England said.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Alexander-Arnold won the men&#39;s young player of the year grant, in front of Manchester United couple Rashford and Mason Greenwood, Chelsea&#39;s Tammy Abraham and Mason Mount, and Arsenal&#39;s Bukayo Saka.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Groups of the year&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Head League group of the year: Nick Pope (Burnley), Trent Alexander-Arnold, Virgil van Dijk (both Liverpool), Caglar Soyuncu (Leicester), Andrew Robertson (Liverpool), David Silva (Manchester City), Jordan Henderson (Liverpool), Kevin de Bruyne (Manchester City), Jamie Vardy (Leicester), Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang (Arsenal), Sadio Mane (Liverpool).&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ladies&#39; Super League group of the year: Ann-Katrin Berger, Maren Mjelde (both Chelsea), Leah Williamson (Arsenal), Millie Bright, Magdalena Eriksson both Chelsea), Caroline Weir (Man City), Kim Little (Arsenal), Ji So-yun, Beth England (both Chelsea), Vivianne Miedema (Arsenal), Chloe Kelly (Man City).&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Title group of the year: Brice Samba (Nottingham Forest), Luke Ayling, Ben White, Liam Cooper (all Leeds), Joe Bryan (Fulham), Eberechi Eze (QPR), Kalvin Phillips (Leeds), Romaine Sawyers (West Brom), Aleksandar Mitrovic (Fulham), Ollie Watkins, Said Benrahma (both Brentford).&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Class One group of the year: Marko Marosi, Fankaty Dabo (both Coventry), Michael Ihiekwe (Rotherham), Robert Dickie (Oxford), Joe Jacobsen (Wycombe), Cameron Brannagan (Oxford), Liam Walsh (Coventry), Matt Crooks (Rotherham), Armand Gnanduillet (Blackpool), Ivan Toney (Peterborough), Matt Godden (Coventry).&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Class Two group of the year: Alex Palmer (Plymouth), Perry Ng (Crewe), Ben Tozer (Cheltenham), Charlie Goode (Northampton), Randell Williams (Exeter), Antoni Sarcevic, Danny Mayor (both Plymouth), Nicky Adams (Northampton), Charlie Kirk (Crewe), Eoin Doyle, Jerry Yates (both Swindon).&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Do the examiners concur?&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>London-based speculation organization Carteret Analytics worked out a rating for every player on the PFA waitlist by figuring the amount they added to their group winning football matches.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As indicated by its examination, De Bruyne was anticipated to win the PFA men&#39;s Player of the Year grant, scoring 382.4 in its rating framework. Van Dijk was nearest to the Belgian with 357.5.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Van Dijk helped Liverpool become champions without precedent for a long time, keeping 15 clean sheets in 38 games, while City&#39;s Raheem Sterling, who got 20 objectives last term, finished third with a 325.3 rating.</p>', 'PFA Player of the Year', 'PFA Player of the Year_1599601309.jpg', '2020-09-09 01:41:49', '2021-08-18 00:24:34'