(298, 4, 3, 51, 'the-songs-that-truly-defined-the-2010s-1599679269', 'The songs that truly defined the 2010s', 0, '<p>Most decades in mainstream music have been characterized by classes, arrangements or topographies, however the 2010s can be maybe best characterized by stages. Spotify propelled in the US, just as Apple Music, YouTube Music, Amazon Music and a Jay-Z-rebranded Tidal, and streaming figures got remembered for the singles and collection outlines. Online media separated dividers by making direct lines of correspondence among specialists and fans, with devotees, images and difficulties on YouTube, Instagram and all the more as of late TikTok turning into a vital window for the two fans and A&amp;R offices.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Accordingly, it was a period in which music turned out to be genuinely worldwide, and sorts appeared to change and circuit. Latin and K-pop got set up as significant kinds, EDM entered the standard. Hip-bounce was raised to another level, beating exciting music just because, and saw subgenres like snare and SoundCloud rap acheiving standard achievement. The 2010s was additionally bookended by two youthful female craftsmen &ndash; Adele and Billie Eilish &ndash; who in their own specific manner represented the present and fate of famous music.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here&#39;s our year-by-year manual for the tunes we think maybe best characterized the 2010s. These aren&#39;t really our main tunes, or the top rated melodies, however the tunes that characterized the soundtrack to the most recent 10 years. Tune in to all the singles out our Spotify playlist here.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Clearly, Adele&#39;s 21 or 19 collections were so famous in the UK that at one phase a duplicate was sold at regular intervals. Given how rapidly this melody got certain &ndash; booming out from wine bars, TVs, and the moved up windows of incalculable school runs &ndash; it&#39;s striking exactly how odd Adele&#39;s Rolling In The Deep is. A four-to-the-floor broadside