(301, 4, 3, 61, 'the-greatest-hip-hop-songs-of-all-time-1599679874', 'The greatest hip-hop songs of all time', 0, '<p>BBC Music surveyed more than 100 pundits in 15 nations to locate the best hip-jump tune ever &ndash; here&#39;s the best 25 rundown (Warning: Some tune titles in this rundown contain language a few perusers may discover hostile)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When Sugarhill Gang&#39;s Rapper&#39;s Delight came out 40 years prior, it was excused by numerous tastemakers as a gimmicky track made to bring in cash. At that point the melody began moving units in the millions and climbed its way up the US Billboard outlines, cresting at number 36 of every 1980, and at number three on the UK Singles Chart. Rapper&#39;s Delight wasn&#39;t the principal hip-bounce melody, yet it was the class&#39; business Big Bang, and a sign that this music conceived in the lodging venture foyers and open parks of the Bronx was in excess of a passing trend.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Hip-jump is mainstream society now. The class&#39; strength of radio waves, streaming numbers, and board outlines is evident, also its effect on everything from vanguard electronica to the DNA of standard popular music from craftsmen like Taylor Swift, Ed Sheeran and Ariana Grande.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In any case, it&#39;s more than that. Hip-jump has become a predominant social power, driving discussions about music, writing, and diversion forward. Cardi B and Common are famous actors. Youthful Thug has made a wake of imitators that length classes and sounds. Kendrick Lamar won a Pulitzer Prize for his 2018 collection DAMN. Also, it has become a genuinely worldwide marvel, crossing ethnic, etymological, and geological limits. The excursion from the turntables of DJ Kool Herc to the addictive, image ified hints of Megan Thee Stallion and Lil&#39; Nas X was long, yet hip jump is setting down deep roots.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We asked 108 pundits, specialists, tastemakers, makers, and picture takers from 15 unique nations to name their own best five hip-bounce tracks ever. There were in excess of 280 unique melodies named, a demonstration of the broadness and profundity of the class, and how the term &#39;most noteworthy&#39; can be deciphered in different ways.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The outcomes are ruled by the purported &#39;Brilliant Age&#39; of hip-bounce between the mid-80s and mid-90s, however there are a few shocks from a later vintage with Kanye West&#39;s Pusha T-helped Runaway taking twelfth spot. There was a surprising absence of ladies in the Top 25; just Queen Latifah&#39;s 1993 hit &quot;U.N.I.T.Y.&quot; and Lauryn Hill&#39;s remarkably appealing &quot;Doo Wop (That Thing)&quot; show up in the rundown. (You can peruse more on the shortage of female MCs in our rundown here.) Rapper&#39;s Delight, the track that ostensibly begun everything, came in at number 14.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The full rundown of pundits&#39; picks is underneath. One more thing to include: The reason for surveys like these ought to be to produce banter just as empower disclosure. What&#39;s more, we know that no rundown can be authoritative or will satisfy everybody &ndash; so take a gander at the rundown underneath, tune in to the playlist, and connect utilizing the hashtag #GreatestHipHopSongs, and let us realize what&#39;s missing. What&#39;s more, pay special mind to more highlights on the worldwide effect of hip-jump in the weeks to come.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>25.* Alright, Kendrick Lamar (2015)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>25.* Rosa Parks, OutKast (1998)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>24. The entirety Of The Lights, Kanye West ft. Rhianna, Kid Cudi (2010)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>23. Grindin&#39;, Clipse (2002)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>22. Lose Yourself, Eminem (2002)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>21. Doo Wop (That Thing), Lauryn Hill (1998)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>20. Global Players Anthem, UGK ft. OutKast (2007)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>19. U.N.I.T.Y., Queen Latifah (1993)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>18. Fuck Tha Police, NWA (1988)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>17. It Was A Good Day, Ice Cube (1992)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>16. B.O.B., OutKast (2000)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>15. They Reminisce Over You (T.R.O.Y.), Pete Rock and C.L. Smooth (1992)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>14. Rapper&#39;s Delight, Sugarhill Gang (1979)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>13. Settled completely, Eric B and Rakim (1987)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>12. Runaway, Kanye West ft. Pusha T (2010)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>11. Electric Relaxation, A Tribe Called Quest (1993)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>10. Dear Mama, Tupac Shakur (1995)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>9. N.Y. Perspective, Nas (1994)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>8. Passin&#39; Me By, The Pharcyde (1992)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>7. 93 Until Infinity, Souls of Mischief (1993)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>6. C.R.E.A.M., Wu-Tang Clan (1993)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. Nuthin&#39; But A &#39;G&#39; Thang, Dr. Dre ft. Sneak Doggy Dogg (1992)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. The Message, Grandmaster Flash and The Furious Five (1982)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Shook Ones (Part II), Mobb Deep (1995)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Battle The Power, Public Enemy (1989)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Succulent, Notorious B.I.G. (1994)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>More on BBC Music&#39;s most noteworthy hip-bounce melodies ever:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What pundits needed to state about the main 10&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Full rundown of pundits who took an interest &ndash; and how they casted a ballot&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Why Juicy is number one (not accessible in UK)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Patterns and amazements in the survey (not accessible in UK)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For what reason are there not many ladies in hip-jump surveys? (not accessible in UK)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Playlist of the main 25 tunes (Spotify)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What number of these melodies do you concur with? Tell us with the hashtag #GreatestHipHopSongs on Facebook or Twitter.</p>', 'hip-hop songs', 'hip-hop songs_1599679873.', '2020-09-09 23:31:14', '2021-08-15 05:15:16'),
(302, 4, 3, 46, '10-best-super-bowl-halftime-shows-of-all-time-1599680033', '10 best Super Bowl Halftime shows of all time', 0, '<p>During a time of atomised seeing propensities, there are scarcely any occasions that catch the same number of eyeballs as the Super Bowl. Its promotion openings are the most costly on US earthbound TV &ndash; $5.6m for 30 seconds, much thanks &ndash; and the Super Bowl Halftime show has gotten one of the most prominent gigs of the year.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Things have made some amazing progress since 1960, when the main Super Bowl Halftime show comprised of just the standard The Liberty Bell being performed by the University of Arizona Symphonic Marching Band. The present shows experience as much arranging as any set at the Grammys or Oscars.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This year, Shakira and Jennifer Lopez are gracing the phase at the Hard Rock Stadium at Miami Gardens in Florida. Apparently, the group are there to see the game between the San Francisco 49ers and the Kansas City Chiefs at Super Bowl LIV, yet in some cases the couple of moments of music intended for half-time amusement wait longer in the memory than the games themselves.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here, BBC Music takes a gander at 10 of the most critical exhibitions.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>10. Janet Jackson, Justin Timberlake, P Diddy, Nelly, Jessica Simpson and Kid Rock (2004)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Janet Jackson and Justin Timberlake at the Super Bowl Halftime show 2004&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Janet Jackson and Justin Timberlake at the Super Bowl Halftime show 2004&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Alright, bar test music round time. Would you be able to name the initial melody that Jessica Simpson acquainted the procedures with? What melody had its name rechanged to namecheck P Diddy? Name both of Kid Rock&#39;s two numbers? No, us not one or the other. That is on the grounds that what turned into the most renowned halftime show ever was eclipsed by an incident that birthed a totally different expression in the English language: &quot;closet breakdown&quot;.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The halftime show at Houston&#39;s Reliant Stadium saw the group, including Janet Jackson and Justin Timberlake, tear through 10 tracks on head of the coordinating band intermissions, yet its heritage is for one half-second during the outcome, where Jackson and Timberlake collaborated for the last&#39;s Rock Your Body. Which Timberlake did, quickly uncovering Jackson&#39;s somewhat secured right areola as he ripped off aspect of her apparel. Fines and claims followed &quot;Nipplegate&quot;, and Jackson quickly observed her music prohibited from radio and music video channels the world over on the grounds that many expected the occurrence had been a trick. Legend has it that a product developer was baffled to such an extent that he was unable to discover film of the occurrence online that he imagined YouTube.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>9. Michael Jackson (1993)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Michael Jackson at the Super Bowl Halftime show 1993&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Michael Jackson at the Super Bowl Halftime show 1993&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>One more decade, another Jackson, however this time the closet remained breakdown free. Michael Jackson&#39;s 1993 appearance at the Rose Bowl in Pasadena, California was a defining moment in halftime party, getting one of the most-watched occasions in US history.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The creation started with Jackson showing up on every one of the scene&#39;s monstrous jumbotron screens, with stunt duplicates at that point showing up on every one of them in a puff of smoke. Jackson himself &ndash; dressed like a Middle Eastern tyrant as envisioned by the craftsman Jeff Koons &ndash; at that point showed up, star bouncing up onto the focal point of the phase in a passage of split-second planning, particularly considering he sent the accompanying two minutes totally still as the group thundered their endorsement. It is top widescreen Jackson, an arena measured segue through Eighties-characterizing hits (Billie Jean), mid 90s songs of praise (Black Or White) and ensemble weighty singalongs (We Are The World, Heal The World).&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>8.Lady Gaga (2017)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Woman Gaga at the Super Bowl Halftime show 2017&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Woman Gaga at the Super Bowl Halftime show 2017&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>American football and Lady Gaga don&#39;t appear to be the most evident partners, however the Millennial Madonna has gained notoriety for her live shows &ndash; and Superbowl LI experienced what her Little Monsters have known for quite a while: Ain&#39;t no show like a Gaga show.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The starting saw Gaga playing out the US National Anthem from the bulwarks of the NRG Stadium in Houston, Texas, before segueing into Pete Seeger&#39;s This Land Is Your Land and the Pledge of Allegiance &ndash; and if this is sounding mystifyingly widely appealing, remember that behind her, an armada of somewhere in the range of 300 automatons were amassing to make an undulating Stars and Stripes banner.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Gaga then zipwired onto the stage &ndash; very Cirque Du Soleil &ndash; before arriving on a pinnacle appearing as though something left over from the terrible cityscape of Blade Runner; the ideal spot to then dispatch into Poker Face. With costuming by Versace and a transforming light show graciousness of entertainment pageant staples 22 Degrees, Gaga&#39;s show finished with a Thriller-esque beast crush highlighting apparently zombified football players. That is a remarkable show to need to follow with a ball game&hellip;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>7. U2 (2002)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>U2 at the Super Bowl Halftime show 2002&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>U2 at the Super Bowl Halftime show 2002&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>No vertigo-instigating zipwires for Bono in 2002 (the melody hadn&#39;t been delivered at this point). U2&#39;s halftime show &ndash; at the Mercedes-Benz Superdome in New Orleans &ndash; the ever-shared U2 decided on the more close to home methodology. With the remainder of the band as of now in front of an audience, Bono strolled through the group to the phase to the strains of Beautiful Day.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This was the primary Super Bowl to occur since the September 11 assaults; U2 checked it by indicating a looking over rundown of names of the individuals who had died as Bono ran around the round stage to the trademark tolling guitar of Where the Streets Have No Name. Love them or scorn them, U2 know how to transforms arenas into public administrations, and this was a lot of a day at the workplace.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>6. Bruce Springsteen and the E Street Band (2009)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bruce Springsteen and the E Street Band at the Super Bowl Halftime show 2009&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bruce Springsteen and the E Street Band at the Super Bowl Halftime show 2009&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Springsteen fans can express gratitude toward Tom Petty and the Heartbreakers, obviously for their Super Bowl appearance. The NFL&#39;s head of programming, Charles Coplin, was on a train home after work when an email sprung up saluting him on the Petty show &ndash; from Springsteen&#39;s chief Jon Landau. It was something other than watcher input &ndash; Landau was trying things out for probability of The Boss&#39; own halftime show. At the point when I got the note, it was, &#39;Amazing, they really like what we do and they&#39;re really intrigued&#39;,&quot; Coplin revealed to Rolling Stone in 2009. &quot;It was one of the great messages.&quot;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thus it was that on 1 February 2009, Bruce Springsteen and the E Street Band showed up at the Raymond James Stadium in Tampa Bay, Florida, with The Boss roaring into the mouthpiece with all the hell and damnation intensity of a Bible Belt evangelist: &quot;For the following 12 minutes, we will bring the honest and strong intensity of the E Street Band into your delightful home! I need you to move away from the guacamole plunge! I need you to put the chicken tenders down! Furthermore, turn your TV as far as possible up!&quot; No armadas of automatons or video deceit, yet a band bored into military snugness. At the point when the band slipped easily into Born To Run, the group&#39;s thunder probably been boisterous enough to inconvenience the establishments.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. Katy Perry, Lenny Kravitz, and Missy Elliott (2015)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Katy Perry, Lenny Kravitz, and Missy Elliott at the Super Bowl Halftime show 2015&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Katy Perry, Lenny Kravitz, and Missy Elliott at the Super Bowl Halftime show 2015&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Monster manikin tiger? Check. Alice in Wonderland-style strange chess board? Check. Moving volley balls, sharks and palm trees? Check, check, check. No U2-style plug in and play here, however Lenny Kravitz&#39;s commitment is the meaning of stripped back &ndash; his guitar, calfskin and pants as a glaring difference to the dayglo lunacy unfurling around him.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The unexpected change from the Nickelodeon immersion of Teenage Dreams and California Gurls into Missy Elliott&#39;s Get Ur Freak On is one of the extraordinary mind-set changes in halftime show history, as the moving sharks clear a path for curiously large football shirts. The teenager pop-meets-retro-rock-meets-hip-jump triumvirate turned into the most observed half-time show ever &ndash; getting a bigger number of eyeballs than the game itself.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. Madonna, LMFAO, Nicki Minaj, MIA, Cee Lo Green (2012)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Madonna, LMFAO, Nicki Minaj, MIA, Cee Lo Green at the Super Bowl Halftime show 2012&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Madonna, LMFAO, Nicki Minaj, MIA, Cee Lo Green at the Super Bowl Halftime show 2012&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Suggestions of glory meets moral dominant part goading underhandedness. Madonna made that big appearance at the Lucas Oil Stadium in Indianapolis flanked by a phalanx of oiled warriors like Cleopatra herself, monster fans uncovering her as the introduction to Vogue began.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It wasn&#39;t only the Madonna show, be that as it may. Curiosity move act LMFAO, rapper MIA, the then rising hip-bounce star Nicki Minaj and the heartfelt Cee-Lo Green &ndash; as the perspiring centurions from the introduction would bear witness to &ndash; it takes numerous hands to help the Material Girl. 10 years on from her MTV Video Music Awards contention, where she kissed Britney Spears and Christina Aguilera, Madonna herself turned away from upsetting the sullen stay-at-homes, yet MIA couldn&#39;t support herself: causing a minor outrage by flipping the feathered creature toward the finish of her short visitor rap.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Aerosmith, Britney Spears, &#39;NSync, Nelly and Mary J Blige (2001)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Aerosmith, Britney Spears, N&#39;Sync, Nelly, Mary J Blige at Super Bowl Halftime show 2001&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Aerosmith, Britney Spears, N&#39;Sync, Nelly, Mary J Blige at Super Bowl Halftime show 2001&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Another sort grafting megafest, putting together an adolescent pop titan, the US&#39;s nearest answer to The Rolling Stones, a rap whiz, a sovereign of R&amp;B and a five-headed, diagram beating boyband. The introduction went ahead like a had jukebox, with &#39;NSync and Aerosmith exchanging hits like Bye and Don&#39;t Want To Miss A Thing, and with &#39;NSync no uncertainty terrifying the safety net providers with some handheld fireworks.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Things unquestionably increase an indent for the finale, nonetheless. For Walk This Way, the supergroup roped I</p>', '10 best Super Bowl, Halftime shows', '10 best Super Bowl Halftime shows of all time_1599680033.', '2020-09-09 23:33:53', '2021-08-14 22:36:32');
