(317, 4, 10, 60, 'us-election-2020-polls-who-is-ahead-trump-or-biden-1599683427', 'US election 2020 polls: Who is ahead - Trump or Biden?', 0, '<p>Citizens in America will settle on 3 November whether Donald Trump stays in the White House for an additional four years.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Republican president is being tested by Democratic Party chosen one Joe Biden, who is most popular as Barack Obama&#39;s VP however has been in US legislative issues since the 1970s.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As political decision day draws near, surveying organizations will be attempting to check the state of mind of the country by asking citizens which coampetitor they like.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We&#39;ll be monitoring those surveys here and attempting to work out what they can and can&#39;t enlighten us regarding who will win the political race.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Biden is driving public presidential surveys&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Public surveys are a decent guide with respect to how mainstream an applicant is the nation over in general, yet they&#39;re not really a decent method to foresee the aftereffect of the political race.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In 2016, for instance, Hillary Clinton drove in the surveys and won almost 3,000,000 a larger number of votes than Donald Trump, yet she despite everything lost - that is on the grounds that the US utilizes an appointive school framework, so winning the most votes doesn&#39;t generally win you the political decision.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With that proviso aside, Joe Biden has been in front of Donald Trump in most public surveys since the beginning of the year. He has drifted around half lately and has had an important lead on events.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Who&#39;s ahead in public surveys?&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>DEMOCRAT&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>BIDEN&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>half&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>REPUBLICAN&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>TRUMP&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>42%&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pattern line indicating normal democratic aim dependent on singular surveys&n