(326, 4, 10, 62, 'are-us-cities-seeing-a-surge-in-violent-crime-as-trump-claims-1599685022', 'Are US cities seeing a surge in violent crime as Trump claims?', 0, '<p>President Donald Trump has said significant US urban communities are seeing a spike in wrongdoing, and has offered to send in government law implementation to handle the circumstance.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He has impugned a line of Democrat-run urban communities which are &quot;tormented by rough wrongdoing&quot;.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>New York, Chicago, Philadelphia, Detroit, Baltimore and these - Oakland is a wreck. We&#39;re not going to let this occur in our nation.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Donald Trump&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>US President&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We&#39;ve taken a gander at brutal wrongdoing, and discovered it&#39;s down by and large in numerous urban areas, yet murders and shootings have risen pointedly in a few.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Brutal wrongdoing keeps on falling&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>President Trump has said the crime percentage in specific urban areas, for example, New York is &quot;through the rooftop&quot;.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, in many significant US urban communities, including Chicago and New York, rough wrongdoing by and large is down contrasted and a similar time a year ago.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Different urban communities characterize fierce wrongdoing in somewhat various manners, however it as a rule incorporates murder, burglary, attack and assault.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Contrasting fierce crime percentages and this time a year ago&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Information up to 23 August&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Source: New York Police Department and Chicago Police Department&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Singular years can change however savage wrongdoing across America has been on a descending pattern since the 1990s.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Rough wrongdoing 2000-2019&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2019 assessments&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Source: FBI, Chicago Police Department, New York Police Department&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In April and May, rough wrongdoing in numerous US urban areas declined fundamentally contrasted and earlier years, due to some extent to Covid lockdown measures.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Yet, President Trump has highlighted a series of murders in specific urban communities, and crimes conversely have expanded pointedly in certain territories.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Where have murders risen?&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>An audit of information from 27 significant American urban areas found that Chicago drove the path as murders flooded.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The president has sent in excess of 100 government specialists to help nearby law implementation in Chicago.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Starting at 23 August, murders were up over half on this time a year ago.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Murders in Chicago&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Contrasted and same point in earlier years&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Information up to 23 August&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Source: Chicago Police Department&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>President Trump has likewise highlighted a series of shootings lately, and shooting occurrences in Chicago are up by over 60% contrasted with a similar point a year ago.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It&#39;s a comparative story in New York - shootings have nearly multiplied contrasted with a similar point in 2019, and the homicide rate is up by in excess of a third - despite the fact that attacks, assaults and burglaries are down.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>New York&#39;s homicide rate has diminished altogether since the 1990s, however June saw the most shootings in a solitary month since 1996, as indicated by the New York Police Department.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>President Trump has proposed extending the sending of government law authorization, as has been the situation in Chicago, to New York just as the north-eastern city of Philadelphia.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Murders in Philadelphia&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Contrasted and same point in earlier years&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Information up to 31 August&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Source: Philadelphia Police Department&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Philadelphia is seeing a spike in murders, while reports of other brutal wrongdoings have declined.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Murders are down somewhere else&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Albuquerque, New Mexico, is another city President Trump has sent many government specialists into, yet kills have fallen contrasted and earlier years.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The police boss in the city has stated: &quot;In spite of cases by government officials in Washington DC, Albuquerque has been keeping in general fierce wrongdoing level and has decreased manslaughters so far this year.&quot;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Murders in Albuquerque&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Contrasted and same point in earlier years&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Information up to 27 July&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Source: Albuquerque Police Department&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Murders in Albuquerque, a city of the greater part a million people, have dropped to 38 as per the most recent information accessible, contrasted and 44 at similar point in the past two years.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Different urban areas reserved by President Trump have likewise observed blended patterns. Murders are down in Baltimore, yet up in Oakland and Detroit contrasted and a similar time a year ago.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For what reason are a few urban areas seeing a spike in murders?&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It&#39;s difficult to put it down to one explanation.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Wrongdoing frequently ascends in the late spring because of a mix of reasons, for example, no school and more open air action.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Richard Rosenfield, an American criminologist, says: &quot;Normally as climate heats up, we see an expansion in road wrongdoing, including manslaughters.&quot;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This mid year has additionally observed individuals reappearing from lockdowns in different states.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The city hall leader of Chicago has placed the ascent in murders down partially to an &quot;immaculate tempest&quot; made by Covid, and the chairman of New York says the spike has been fuelled by &quot;frightful separation&quot; brought about by the pandemic.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The continuous pandemic has had boundless ramifications, including for law authorization.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Numerous courts in the US have been shut, and a few guilty parties have been delivered to stop the spread of Covid. That has driven &quot;to an inclination among guilty parties that they can perpetrate violations without risk of punishment&quot;, as indicated by a report by the Police Executive Research Forum.</p>', 'US cities seeing a surge in violent crime as Trump claims', 'Are US cities seeing a surge in violent crime as Trump claims_1599685022.jpg', '2020-09-10 00:57:02', '2021-08-17 20:52:49'),
(327, 4, 10, 95, 'justice-dept-seeks-to-defend-trump-defamation-case-1599685214', 'Justice dept seeks to defend Trump defamation case', 0, '<p>The US Department of Justice has made legitimate move to protect President Donald Trump in a criticism case from a lady who blames him for assaulting her.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Under a court recording, the office is moving to supplant the president&#39;s private legal advisors and assume control over the case.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Feature writer E Jean Carroll blames Mr Trump for attacking her in a Manhattan retail establishment during the 1990s.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In a claim, she contends the president stigmatized her when he denied her case by saying she &quot;wasn&#39;t his sort&quot;.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mr Trump&#39;s faultfinders state that during his administration he has undermined the US equity division, which is intended to work autonomously of the White House.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The president has as of not long ago been spoken to for the situation, which was recorded in New York state court in November 2019, by his own attorney Marc Kasowitz.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The sexual claims against Donald Trump&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ms Carroll&#39;s attorney, Roberta A Kaplan, said in an announcement on Tuesday evening that the equity division mediation was &quot;stunning&quot;.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What did the equity office state?&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Its legal advisors contend in Tuesday&#39;s court documenting that Mr Trump can be protected by government lawyers since he was serving in his ability as president when he denied Ms Carroll&#39;s charge.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;President Trump was acting inside the extent of his office as President of the United States at the hour of the occurrences out of which the Plaintiff&#39;s slander guarantee emerged,&quot; says the documenting.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It looks to raise the case to a government court from a state court.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Media captionLife after #MeToo&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The administration legal counselors refer to the Federal Tort Claims Act, which offers US government representatives a level of invulnerability from being sued.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>College of Texas graduate school educator Steve Vladeck revealed to CNN that such an intercession by the equity division was profoundly uncommon.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The lawful investigator said the court recording could adequately murder the case in light of the fact that the government can&#39;t be sued for maligning.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The move comes a month after a state court judge said Mr Trump couldn&#39;t utilize a lawful invulnerability guard for the situation.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The president is presently amidst a mission for re-appointment against Democratic challenger Joe Biden in November.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Biden denies ex-assistant&#39;s rape claim&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>How did E Jean Carroll react?&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ms Carroll - who is a guidance reporter for Elle magazine - said in an announcement: &quot;The present activities exhibit that Trump will do everything conceivable, including utilizing the full powers of the government, to impede revelation from going ahead for my situation before the forthcoming political decision to attempt to keep a jury from regularly choosing which one of us is lying.&quot;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Her legitimate group is requesting that the president give a DNA test so they can decide if his hereditary material is on a dark Donna Karan dress that she says she was wearing at the hour of the supposed attack.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Legal advisor Ms Kaplan said in an explanation that &quot;Trump&#39;s push to employ the intensity of the US government to sidestep obligation regarding his private unfortunate behavior is unprecedented and shows significantly more obviously how far he is happy to go to keep reality from coming out&quot;.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What does E Jean Carroll claim?&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>She says the assault occurred at a Bergdorf Goodman store in Midtown Manhattan in late 1995 or mid 1996, when the pair chanced upon one another while shopping.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The previous Apprentice star and land financier purportedly approached her for counsel when purchasing unmentionables for another lady and tongue in cheek approached her to demonstrate it for him.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the evolving rooms, she said Mr Trump rushed at her, stuck her against a divider and constrained himself on her.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Trump excuses assault claim as &#39;fiction&#39;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Trump says rape informer &#39;not my sort&#39;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Biden denies ex-associate&#39;s rape charge&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ms Carroll claims she figured out how to push him off after an &quot;enormous battle&quot;.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Both Mr Trump and Ms Carroll were matured around 50 at that point, and he was hitched to Marla Maples.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mr Trump has freely denied the charge a few times, including saying that Ms Carroll was &quot;absolutely lying&quot; and her case was &quot;fiction&quot;.</p>', 'Trump defamation case', '_107496077_gettyimages-497597272_1599685214.jpg', '2020-09-10 01:00:14', '2021-08-13 03:49:58'),
(328, 4, 10, 61, 'us-election-2020-has-trump-kept-his-promises-on-the-military-1599685396', 'US election 2020: Has Trump kept his promises on the military?', 0, '<p>US President Donald Trump has been safeguarding his record on military spending and his promise to scale back US association in unfamiliar wars.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In 2017 he said he would modify the nation&#39;s &quot;exhausted military&quot;. He has likewise required a decrease in US troops serving abroad.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We&#39;ve investigated the president&#39;s record on the military.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>President Trump&#39;s child, Donald Jr, as of late composed on Twitter: &quot;Trump appropriately supported our military after Obama-Biden devastated it.&quot;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The graph shows military spending has consistently expanded since President Trump got down to business in January 2017.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Nonetheless, this spending is still altogether lower than during the main term of the Obama organization, utilizing figures balanced for swelling.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Protection spending went up significantly under President Trump to date. I wouldn&#39;t call the development extraordinary, however,&quot; says Michael O&#39;Hanlon, a security individual at the Brookings Institution.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Mr Trump can guarantee credit for an enormous &#39;peacetime&#39; increment from an express that was at that point genuinely great under Mr Obama, whose safeguard spending plans were solid by chronicled principles as well - more than $100bn over the Cold War yearly normal, when balanced for swelling,&quot; says Mr O&#39;Hanlon.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Picture copyrightGETTY IMAGES&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Picture subtitle&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>US officer in Germany, where a large number of abroad soldiers are based&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Seeing military spending in the course of recent decades, contrasting it and the size of the US economy, we can see that current spending is at not even close to record levels.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>US military burning through 1990-2019&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Source: Stockholm International Peace Research Institute&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Military spending expanded significantly from 2002 as the US entered extended wars in Iraq and Afghanistan. It crested in 2010 as a level of GDP - the estimation all things considered and benefits - after which the US started moving away from its commitment in the Middle East and Central Asia.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Does the US have less abroad soldiers?&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>President Trump has since quite a while ago called for troops to return home and has reprimanded US military mediations for being expensive and insufficient.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mr O&#39;Hanlon says: &quot;Mr Trump has downsized the presence he acquired in Afghanistan and partly in Iraq and Syria.&quot;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This year the president diminished the quantity of troops in Afghanistan to 8,600 from 13,000 and plans to cut the number further before the 3 November political race.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, says Mr O&#39;Hanlon: &quot;He has just moved the needle unassumingly regarding worldwide activities and arrangements, as we remain wherever that we were on January 20, 2017 when he got to work.&quot;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The decrease of troops was a lot more prominent under President Obama, as both huge scope arrangements in Iraq and Afghanistan finished during his years in control.</p>', 'US election 2020', 'US election 2020 Has Trump kept his promises on the military_1599685396.jpg', '2020-09-10 01:03:16', '2021-08-12 21:09:25'),
(329, 4, 10, 75, 'us-2020-election-trump-targeted-in-misleading-puddle-video-1599685571', 'US 2020 Election: Trump targeted in misleading puddle video', 0, '<p>A deceptive video of US President Donald Trump has been broadly shared internet, meaning to give him looking confounded remaining close to a puddle of water in the grounds of the White House.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Independently, a phony picture is flowing via online media, indicating a pontoon evidently with a Trump 2020 banner on it, sitting at the base of a lake.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We&#39;ve investigated both of these.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What is the Trump puddle video?&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The 12-second video cut shows President Trump leaving correspondents toward a puddle in the White House grounds, which he at that point gazes at.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Picture inscription&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The full form shows the president sitting tight for Melania Trump before boarding Marine One&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The clasp was posted close by a tweet addressing President Trump&#39;s emotional well-being, guaranteeing he was &quot;lost and bewildered&quot;.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, the clasp has been taken outside of any relevant connection to the subject at hand from a more extended video, shot in August 2019. Twitter has hailed the clasp because it has been altered outside of any relevant connection to the issue at hand.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the full form, you can see the president leave the press and over towards the puddle, while anticipating First Lady Melania Trump to go with him on board the helicopter.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>President Trump can be seen highlighting the puddle to caution his better half not to step in it.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Picture copyrightGETTY IMAGES&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Picture subtitle&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Melania Trump maintains a strategic distance from the puddle and joins President Trump&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The puddle - and the president and first woman - can likewise be unmistakably found in a despite everything picture taken by a news photographic artist, who was there at that point.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The controlled video cut has now been taken out, yet has just been seen in excess of multiple times.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Shouldn&#39;t something be said about the Trump vessel picture?&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This image seems to show a pontoon with a favorable to Trump banner on it at the base of a lake in Texas.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It appeared online after a supportive of Trump vessel march in Austin, Texas, throughout the end of the week - one of various comparable occasions which have occurred over the US lately.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Experts in Texas reported a few vessels sinking during the pontoon march, however this image isn&#39;t of one of them.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It has been generally shared, including by Democratic administrator Shevrin Jones from Florida, who tweeted the image, saying: &quot;Gracious the imagery of it all...&quot;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>His tweet has been re-tweeted in excess of multiple times, and different posts have shared the picture on the web.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The image is really of a vessel which sank in Michigan in June, and the Trump banner has been included to the pontoon.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Picture inscription&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The first picture was taken in Grand Traverse Bay, Michigan in June&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The picture initially showed up on a nearby Michigan news site in June, which revealed that 10 individuals on the depressed vessel had been saved.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It&#39;s not satisfactory who initially included the Trump 2020 banner to the old picture.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mr Jones later tweeted saying: &quot;It&#39;s clearly photoshopped however the imagery remains.&quot;</p>', 'US 2020 Election', '_114282811_gettyimages-1263016246_1599685571.jpg', '2020-09-10 01:06:11', '2021-08-14 12:57:34'),
(331, 4, 10, 88, 'lake-travis-several-boats-sink-at-pro-trump-parade-in-texas-1599685953', 'Lake Travis: Several boats sink at pro-Trump parade in Texas', 0, '<p>A few vessels have sunk on a lake in the US territory of Texas during a motorcade to help President Donald Trump in November&#39;s political race, authorities state.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Specialists state the rough water was likely brought about by the huge number of vessels moving intently together on Lake Travis, close to the state capital, Austin.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pictures indicated vessels with Trump crusade banners moving nearby other people.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Media state individuals must be protected from the water, yet there were no quick reports of wounds.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The occasion, called Lake Travis Trump Boat Parade, was sorted out on Facebook, and in excess of 2,600 individuals stamped themselves as having gone to it.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Picture copyrightREUTERS&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Picture inscription&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In excess of 2,600 individuals stamped themselves as having gone to the occasion&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Picture copyrightREUTERS&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Picture subtitle&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The occasion was sorted out by supporters of President Trump on Lake Travis&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>An examination has been dispatched and there is no proof of any purposeful demonstration, Travis County Sheriff&#39;s Office representative Kristen Dark said.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;We reacted to different calls of vessels in trouble, a few of them sank,&quot; she said. &quot;We had an extraordinary number of pontoons on the lake today... At the point when they all began moving simultaneously, it produced critical waves.&quot;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The episode occurred around 12:00 (17:00 GMT) on Saturday, Labor Day weekend in the US. The occasion page said pontoons were approached to drive at 10mph (16km/h).&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Paul Yura, from the National Weather Service in Austin/San Antoni