(332, 4, 5, 63, 'tiktok-tries-to-remove-widely-shared-suicide-clip-1599686337', 'TikTok tries to remove widely shared suicide clip', 0, '<p>Video-sharing site TikTok is battling to bring down clasps indicating a man murdering himself.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The recording, which has been coursing on the stage for a few days, started on Facebook and has additionally been shared on Twitter and Instagram.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>TikTok is immensely mainstream with youngsters - and many have detailed going over the video and being damaged by the substance.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The application said it would boycott accounts more than once transferring cuts.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&#39;Cautioned others&#39;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Our frameworks have been naturally identifying and hailing these clasps for abusing our approaches against content that shows, applauds, praises, or advances self destruction,&quot; an agent said.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;We value our locale individuals who&#39;ve announced substance and cautioned others against viewing, drawing in or sharing such recordings on any stage, keeping in mind the individual and their family.&quot;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Facebook disclosed to BBC News: &quot;We eliminated the first video from Facebook a month ago, on the day it was streamed, and have utilized computerization innovation to eliminate duplicates and transfers since that time.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Our considerations stay with Ronnie&#39;s loved ones during this troublesome time.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On Monday, Brenda&#39;s 14-year-old little girl came running down the steps. She was covering her mouth, crying and saying she would have been debilitated.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;She was in such a state, shaking like a leaf and appropriately crying,&quot; Brenda, who lives close to Edinburgh, told the BBC.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I have never observed her that upset. It was terrible and took ages to get the words out of her.&quot;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Brenda clarified that her little girl had seen the self destruction video after it showed up inside the suggested clasps of TikTok&#39;s For You area.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;She was looking through tunes and clever recordings when a whiskery man in a white shirt shows up behind a work area,&quot; the mother stated, soon after he supposedly killed himself.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I have caught wind of trolling and terrible things however this tops everything. I called the police however they advised me that it isn&#39;t their business to police the web.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;My little girl was in a condition of stun, despite everything is in a condition of stun and this could remain with her for a considerable length of time.&quot;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Since the occurrence, she included, her girl had laid down with the light on and continued remembering the pictures she had seen. She included that her little girl felt frightened to go out and was feeling the loss of a day of school accordingly.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>line&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sensationalizing self-hurt&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is accounted for that a few clients are sharing the video, camouflaged behind pictures of little cats or other substance. Others have assembled their own recordings cautioning about the substance and asking individuals to erase it.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>TikTok&#39;s calculations regularly suggest content from individuals not legitimately followed by a client.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A few people have streamed their suicides on Facebook Live since its 2015 dispatch.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Facebook, which claims Instagram, has likewise confronted analysis that the stage shares content sensationalizing self-damage and self destruction.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After the passing of Molly Russell, in 2017, her dad said Instagram had &quot;helped execute his girl&quot;.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The BBC has data on what to do if kids see something upsetting on the web here&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For data and backing on emotional well-being and self destruction, access the BBC Action Line.</p>', 'TikTok tries to remove widely shared suicide clip', '_113263837_gettyimages-1223464222_1599686337.jpg', '2020-09-10 01:18:57', '2021-08-15 14:43:13'),
(333, 4, 5, 61, 'david-beckhams-guild-esports-to-float-on-london-stock-market-1599686457', 'David Beckham\'s Guild Esports to float on London stock market', 0, '<p>An e-sports organization in which David Beckham possesses a noteworthy stake is trying to raise &pound;20m by posting its offers on the London Stock Exchange.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Organization Esports will be the first in the UK to offer fans the opportunity to place cash into maneuvering its groups of gamers.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>E-sports, where observers watch players video gaming, has seen its ubiquity ascend during lockdown.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The organization intends to handle groups in the worldwide web based games Fortnite, CS:GO, Rocket League and Fifa.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It needs to develop its groups&#39; aptitudes utilizing frameworks like the Premier League&#39;s ability scholastics.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Prize and sponsorship cash for e-sports run in the millions and crowds rush to in excess of 100 million for certain occasions, overwhelming those for major games, for example, Wimbledon and the Tour de France.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Figures from Newzoo, a games market bits of knowledge organization, show that 2019, e-sports had an aggregate of 443 million watchers in 2020. Newzoo predicts the market will develop to 646 million watchers by 2023.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&#39;Worldwide impact&#39;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The offers will at first be offered to huge financial specialists one month from now, however a short time later will exchange openly on the securities exchange where anybody can get them.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cash raised from the underlying offer putting will be utilized to grow the business, including enlisting new players.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The venture further broadens David Beckham&#39;s wide-extending business interests, which incorporate design, aromas, whisky and a football club in Florida that he co-claims.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Society Esports said he would utilize his &quot;worldwide impact and following to help the improvement of the organization&#39;s image and business&quot;.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Beckham is one of the establishing investors in the business, holding what is depicted as a &quot;critical minority stake&quot;, despite the fact that the specific venture is undisclosed.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He isn&#39;t the primary footballer to detect the likely open doors in e-sports. Ribs and Real Madrid player Gareth Bale dispatched his e-sports association, Ellevens Esports, prior this year.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Carleton Curtis, the chief director of Guild Esports, stated: &quot;Organization will be the primary e-sports establishment to join the London financial exchange.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;It will furnish us with the reserve, validity and cash-flow to satisfy our aspiration to get one of the world&#39;s best 10 e-sports establishments inside three years.&quot;</p>', 'David Beckham\'s Guild Esports', '_114295475_gettyimages-1210255331-1_1599686457.jpg', '2020-09-10 01:20:57', '2021-08-14 22:38:18'),
(334, 4, 10, 151, 'facebook-profits-from-hate-claims-engineer-who-quit-1599735787', 'Facebook \'profits from hate\' claims engineer who quit', 1, '<p>A Facebook engineer has stopped the firm, saying they &quot;can not stomach anymore&quot; being important for an association &quot;benefitting off disdain&quot;.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ashok Chandwaney is the most recent worker to open up to the world about worries about how the organization manages disdain discourse.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The architect included it was &quot;deciding to be on an inappropriate side of history&quot;.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Facebook reacted by saying it had eliminated a great many scorn related posts. Another of its ex-engineers has additionally gone to its safeguard.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The push of the post by Ashok Chandwaney - who utilizes &quot;they&quot; and &quot;them&quot; as close to home pronouns - is that Facebook moves rapidly to take care of specific issues, yet with regards to managing scorn discourse, it is more intrigued by PR than executing genuine change.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Their five and a half years residency at the firm signified &quot;finding out about a bug in a gathering, and fixing it before the gathering is finished&quot;, they compose.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;The differentiation among that and our way to deal with disdain on the stage is amazing.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;To me being striking methods seeing something that is difficult to do at the same time, realizing it&#39;s the proper activity, focusing in and making a plunge.&quot;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>White patriotism and the utilization of the stage by a long shot right local armies were among the things they felt Facebook expected to accomplish more on, just as managing other political substance.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Consistently &#39;the plundering beginnings, the shooting fires&#39; stays up is a day that we decide to limit administrative danger to the detriment of the security of dark, indigenous and minorities.&quot;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Free discourse&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Facebook&#39;s refusal to eliminate that remark, posted by President Trump during the Black Lives Matter fights, was as opposed to Twitter, which named it as extolling viciousness.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The position drove a few representatives to leave, with others arranging walk-outs. Furthermore, publicists boycotted the stage for the period of July, over its disposition to loathe discourse.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Facebook reacted to the architect&#39;s post, saying: &quot;We don&#39;t benefit from disdain. We contribute billions of dollars every year to keep our locale safe and are in profound organization with outside specialists to survey and update our strategies.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;This late spring we dispatched an industry-driving strategy to follow QAnon, developed our reality checking program, and eliminated a large number of presents tied on disdain associations, over 96% of which we found before anybody detailed them to us.&quot;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>QAnon is a paranoid idea that trusts US President Trump is pursuing a mystery war against a &quot;covert government&quot; organization of pedophiles, some of whom are incredible government, business and media figures.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A few representatives were eager to safeguard the informal community.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Stepan Parunashvili - who functioned as a product engineer at Facebook for a long time up to 2019 yet has since helped to establish his own business - told the BBC that the informal organization required chance to thoroughly consider the issues in question.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Changing the meaning of &#39;disdain&#39;, even with excellent goals, is hazardous and loaded with tail chances,&quot; he clarified,&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;As I would like to think Facebook knows about that, and is treating this genuinely.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;They are not &#39;moving quick&#39; on changing the meaning of free discourse, and that is an extraordinary thing.&quot;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Facebook utilizes a huge number of specialists, and they are among the most generously compensated workers at the tech firm.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Controllers and strategy creators around the globe are worried about the development of scorn discourse, on Facebook as well as on all online media stages, with numerous nations dispatching enquiries into how the tech firms are managing the issue.</p>', 'Facebook, Facebook  News', '_114297287_facebooklogomoney_1599686533.jpg', '2020-09-10 01:22:13', '2021-08-14 15:45:33'),
(335, 7, 4, 52, 'ashley-barty-french-open-champion-eliminated-from-the-2020-corona-virus-tournament-1599687631', 'Ashley Barty: French Open Champion eliminated from the 2020 corona virus tournament', 0, '<p>World number 1 Ashley Barty has decided not to defend this year&#39;s French Open tennis title by withdrawing from the tournament because of the coronavirus.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Australian racer said that last year&#39;s event at Roland Garros was &quot;the most special tournament of my career, so it&#39;s not a decision I make easily&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The 24-year-old has cited health risks and an inability to train effectively with his coach in recent months.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Barty also decided not to participate in the US Open which was taking place in New York.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Barty, from Brisbane, stated that due to the closed state borders in Australia, he was unable to reunite with his Melbourne-based coach to prevent the spread of Covid-19.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;It has been a challenging year for everyone and while I am disappointed with the tennis front, the health and well-being of my family and team will always be my priority. Thanks to my fans for their continued support, I look forward to seeing you again. . &quot; play, &quot;he said.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The French Open is scheduled to start in Paris later this month, with attendance cuts and strict health protocols.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>38-year-old Serena Williams has yet to decide if she will attend.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A total of 11,500 fans will be able to take part in each day of the two-week tournament at Roland Garros starting September 27, which is divided into three zones around three places on site.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The event was postponed from May to September due to the coronavirus pandemic.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Spectators receive tickets for one of the three zones and must stay in this zone during the day. Wearing sanitary pads is mandatory for people over the age of 11. Players and staff are tested regularly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>France, like several European countries, has seen an increase in Covid-19 infections.</p>', 'Ashley Barty, French', 'Ashley Bartley_1599687631.jpg', '2020-09-10 01:40:31', '2021-08-16 15:19:57'),
(336, 7, 4, 47, 'nba-playoffs-boston-celtics-beat-toronto-raptors-los-angeles-clippers-denver-nuggets-1599687746', 'NBA playoffs: Boston Celtics beat Toronto Raptors, Los Angeles Clippers Denver Nuggets', 0, '<p><strong>The Boston Celtics beat the Toronto Raptors and lead series 3-2 in the Eastern Conference semifinals. The defending champions are on the verge of ending the NBA playoffs.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Star Defense led the Celtics 25-11 at the start of the quarter, winning 111-89. &quot;The work isn&#39;t done yet,&quot; Cayx told Caylan Brown. &quot;We have to go out and play with the same intensity.&quot; The Celtics can seal the best of seven draws in the sixth fixture on Wednesday.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Raptors Point defender Kyle Lowry said, &quot;You jumped very well. We weren&#39;t as confident as we could have been.&quot; In the evening&#39;s other match in Orlando, Florida, Paul George scored 32 points while the Los Angeles Clippers won a battle with the Denver Nuggets to lead 2-1 in the Western Conference semifinals.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Denver led midway through the third quarter with 78-67, and the leadership changed hands nine times before the start of the fourth quarter. &quot;This game boils down to one of two teams playing defense,&quot; said Clippers coach Doc Rivers. &quot;For three and a half the two teams scored basically and for the last six minutes it was our defense.&quot;</p>', 'NBA playoffs, Boston', 'Boston Celtics_1599687746.jpg', '2020-09-10 01:42:26', '2021-08-13 07:21:34'),
(337, 7, 11, 131, 'tournament-championship-dustin-johnson-wins-the-fedex-cup-title-with-a-tournament-win-1599899143', 'Tournament Championship: Dustin Johnson wins the FedEx Cup title with a tournament win', 0, '<p><strong>World number one Dustin Johnson won three shots last season from the PGA Touring Championship.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The 36-year-old American led five strokes and two under 68 in Monday&#39;s final at East Lake to win the $ 15 million FedEx Cup jackpot. This is the first FedEx Cup title for Johnson, who missed the final four years ago.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Compatriots Justin Thomas and Xander Schaufele registered a final lap 66 to end the match for second place on the 18th floor. Johnson told the Golf Channel: &quot;It&#39;s a tough golf course, so nobody&#39;s really safe. I know I have to play really well.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I got off to a very good start, I missed a few shots in the back but did a fairway when I had to get off that part. People gave me a good fight today.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I want to be a FedEx Cup champion, that&#39;s something in my career that I really like and I&#39;m very proud of the way I play, especially in the last four tournaments.&quot; Former US Open champion Johnson maintained his lead overnight after six holes but shot seven and eight lawbreakers in succession to give Thomas and Schaufele hope.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thomas applied pressure to the outer nine with five birds as he and Shovel moved briefly within two minutes before taking the lead for the day. Johnson, the first player to lead 54 holes in four consecutive Tiger Woods races in 1999, however, kept up his nerve and sealed the title with the last trick.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>American PGA winner Colin Morikawa made the final round 69 and finished sixth on the 13th floor, with a shot ahead of England&#39;s Tyrrell Hatton.&nbsp;Defending champion Northern Ireland and four-time grand winner Rory McIlroy fires backwards on the 11th floor.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>How tournament championships work</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Johnson kicked off the Atlanta show at 10 a.m., being nominated for the top ranked player in the Tour Championship. Event players were disabled due to accumulated FedEx Cup points during the season, and the top 30 overall battled for the tournament championship.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The top ranked player starts the tournament with 72 holes at 10 under par, while the second start starts at eight under par. The third seed is cut down to seven, and so on until the fifth seed on the fifth floor. 6-10 seeds ranging from -4; 11-15 seeds ranging from -3; and so on for seeds 26-30, starting at the same level.</p>', 'Tournament, Dustin Johnson', 'Dustin Johnson_1599687976.jpg', '2020-09-10 01:46:16', '2021-09-23 08:16:41'),
(338, 7, 4, 103, 'formula-1-is-set-to-revive-the-sprint-grid-sprint-plan-1599735755', 'Formula 1 is set to revive the sprint grid sprint plan', 1, '<p><strong>Formula 1 will revive plans to introduce sprint racing instead of qualifying.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mercedes blocked plans to test its idea this season, but Sunday&#39;s Italian Grand Prix gave F1 a boost. Two safety cars, a penalty for Louis Hamilton and a racing disruption at Monza mixed the field and resulted in a surprise win for Pierre Gasley of Alpha Tauri.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>F1 executive director Ross Brown said, &quot;The race shows the joy that a confusing package can provide.&quot; Mercedes believes the idea is a hoax and will not work out as F1 hoped for. Toto Wolf, head of Mercedes F1, said he rejected the three-point plan, arguing that sport is meritocracy, that the use of reverse grids in other categories causes events to be &quot;played out&quot; and that the idea is that one Team is too punishing the fastest cars against those who own the fastest cars. second and third.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Wolff also noted that in the poll of F1 fans, only 15% showed interest in reverse net racing. Pierre Gasley won the exciting Italian Grand Prix Louis Hamilton was responsible for the sentence Toto Wolf will remain at Mercedes in 2021</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But&nbsp; Sport News has learned that Brown and other F1 bosses are determined to carry on with the idea and give it a try later this season before using it more often in 2021.&nbsp;According to the rules in force, any changes to the rules during the championship year require unanimity. Therefore, F1 must convince Mercedes to support the plan to introduce it in one race at the end of the season.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>They hope that after winning the Drivers and Constructors title, the team can agree on a series of races before the season ends. The new contract the team signed last month for the period 2021-25 removes the need for unanimity on last-minute changes to launch rules and replaces them with a &quot;super majority&quot; vote.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Brown posted the back grid racing idea in his post-race column on the F1 website on Monday. &quot;Monza is a challenger for the reverse grid sprint race when we consider the best performance this year,&quot; he said.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Unfortunately we can&#39;t continue, but the concept is still something we and the FIA want to work on in the coming months and discuss with the team for next year. Of course, the teams will prepare their cars differently in a sprint race with a rear grille.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Right now, Mercedes has set its car to make the fastest laps and then control the race in front of them. If they know they have to overtake, they have to change that approach.&quot; &quot;We will continue to evaluate new formats to perfect the show, but always maintain the DNA of Formula 1.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If approved, the starting grid for the sprint race will be determined in the reverse order of the championship and the result will determine the starting grid for the main Grand Prix on Sunday.</p>', 'Revive Plan, Sprint Grid', 'Formula 1_1599688199.jpg', '2020-09-10 01:49:59', '2021-08-17 22:08:34');
INSERT INTO `posts` (`id`, `user_id`, `category_id`, `views`, `slug`, `title`, `type`, `description`, `tags`, `image`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(339, 7, 4, 67, 'maya-moore-wnba-stars-successful-campaign-to-release-jonathan-irons-1599688847', 'Maya Moore: WNBA star\'s successful campaign to release Jonathan Irons', 0, '<p><strong>Maya Moore was on her knees when Jonathan Irons was released from prison.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>It took a while for his strength to return. Then she got up and hugged him for the first time in more than 23 years, a single man. Eisen&#39;s first move outside of this building was the last in a journey they have undertaken together for more than a decade.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After recovering, Moore turned to the phone, recorded the momentous event, and said, &quot;All right, guys. It&#39;s over. It&#39;s over.&quot; The 2020 WNBA season begins on July 25. The Minnesota Lynx is eyeing a fifth title, but for the second year in a row they have done so without one of their star players.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In 2011 Moore was selected for the first round for the Lynx. Since then, he has helped them win four championships and was named MVP of the 2014 season. The 31-year-old also has two Olympic gold medals and two World Championship medals. Some would argue that he is the best the WNBA has ever seen.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In early 2019, she took the sport by surprise by giving up everything for the man she met 12 years ago. A man who has become her brother. Although he was only 16 years old at the time the crime occurred, Irons was tried as an adult.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On January 14, 1997, someone broke into Stanley Stotler&#39;s home on the outskirts of the white working class on St. Louis, Missouri. When Stotler returned, the thief shot him in the head. Stotler survived and was initially unable to identify the perpetrator on the six photos. According to the New York Times, a police officer asked him to make a good guess, and he pointed to a photo of Irons and other photos of African Americans.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Then, at the preliminary hearing, Stotler identifies Irons as the assailant. But there are no fingerprints linking the teenager to the crime. No traces of DNA or blood. There are no confirmed witnesses.&nbsp;The public defender did not allow Irons to stand up to claim his innocence, saying he was too young and uneducated.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Prosecutors said Irons admitted to offenses that he and his lawyers have denied. The officer who questioned Irons alone and did not record the interview. During the October 1998 trial, American politicians walked on heavy platforms. The penalties for juvenile offenders are severe.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>One prosecutor was quoted as saying by Irons: &quot;Don&#39;t be gentle with him because he is young. He is as dangerous as someone five times his age. &quot;We need to send a message to some of these young people that if you act like an old man, you will be treated like an old man.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In December 1998, at the age of 18, Irons was convicted of assault and theft by a white jury and jailed for 50 years.&nbsp;In 2007, nine years after that decision, 18-year-old Moore went to Missouri to visit his family and meet with Irons through the Prison Department they work with.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the following years he continued to return to Jefferson City, his hometown, to visit Irons. She sent him books by his favorite authors and talked to him on the phone before the big games. Finally he decided to take a break from his basketball career.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Why? Because he always believed that Eisen was telling the truth. &quot;There is something in the truth that makes you believe this will happen,&quot; said Moore.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;He just has to keep believing that if we can understand the truth in front of the right people who want to do the right thing, they will do it.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In early 2019, as he prepared for the new WNBA season, Moore had to work with Irons and his lawyers to request a retrial. He devoted himself to that matter. About 21 years after Irons was found guilty, prosecutors are still reluctant to admit defeat. They tried to prevent an investigation but failed, and in October 2019, Irons finally admitted his innocence.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On March 9, 2020, the Irons assessment was canceled. Judge Daniel Green described the original case as &quot;very lax and at least indirect&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In his ruling, the judge cited fingerprints on the door of Stotler&#39;s house that did not match Stotler&#39;s or Irons.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This is evidence that another person had committed the crime but was never turned over to the defense team at the 1998 trial. The Irons story is not unique and is based on a very complex system and problem to represent.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Netflix &#39;13. The 2016 documentary features statistics that show how disproportionate the number of prisons in the US are in African-American. Perhaps the most eye-opening thing is that while a white man in the country has a one in 17 chance of being behind bars, for a black man it is one in three.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But sometimes statistics aren&#39;t enough to make a difference. It takes a real human story. People saw Floyd as a father, a brother, someone who called his mother to death. Just as Floyd&#39;s death sparked a global race, Moore hopes the Irons story can change America&#39;s justice system.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;It&#39;s about long-term dehumanization that is consciously expressed through the system in our country,&quot; he said. &quot;The system that was consciously woven into the structure of our homes is still here and has influenced us for generations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;George Floyd is human and all other life is human. If you put someone down, you become inhuman.&quot; At the push of a button, you can sign an online petition calling for the release of convicted convicts. But that&#39;s not how Moore works.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He doesn&#39;t want every athlete to leave his job and join them. But he also doesn&#39;t care what your social media says. What matters is what people do when no one is watching. Moore battled dehumanization which he spoke of by playing chess with iron. He visited her on holidays. When he was released, he invited Irons over to his home. Your entire philosophy can be reduced to three words: Show yourself again and again.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;When you have the power or the resources, leave it and empower others,&quot; he said. Moore believes in sacrificing what he has in order to lift others and become better people. That is selflessness, many of us don&#39;t have the power to have access to. But selflessness may be what the world needs to make real change.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>And the fact that it was so closely tied to a man&#39;s future meant that, even though he did succeed on that occasion, he knew exactly how tough the fight would be. When asked what he learned when he released the Irons, the list is long and the scope of the problems is astonishing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Should drug laws be changed? Are the police overstated? Are you short on funds? What is better, criminal or restorative justice? How was the voting procedure changed?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Law enforcement reform is at the heart of the fight between Moore and Irons. But now he knows the importance of criminal justice reform and changes in the US approach to prison.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;It&#39;s very broad,&quot; said Moore.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;When I started my apprenticeship, I was just as devastated - as are all of us, the people who have opened our eyes lately.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When he&#39;s busy, Moore knows he can&#39;t do everything and he isn&#39;t alone in his struggles. He has inspired other athletes to follow suit. Former University of Connecticut teammates Renee Montgomery and Tiffany Hayes are taking a break from the WNBA this season to help with voter registration and social justice reform.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For now, Moore will stick to reforms. Their &quot;Win with Justice&quot; campaign seeks to challenge a &quot;winning&quot; culture that is meant to undermine our community&#39;s trust in those who are responsible for promoting public safety.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He said, &quot;I saw the connection between sport and the leadership that prosecutors have for winning and losing. What is victory and what is defeat?&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I will continue to try to help and share and enable others to do the same.&quot; It is not yet clear in what form Moore&#39;s work will continue or whether he will return to basketball. The release of Irons, now 40 years old, may be the end of a journey for him and Moore, but it will not be the end of their friendship.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I can&#39;t,&quot; said Irons when Moore asked him to explain his feelings about the camera recording the moment of his release.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He shook his head several times before finally muttering &quot;live&quot;. He paused and then continued: &quot;I feel like I can live now. Thanks to everyone who supported me - Maya and her family. I am so grateful that I have a place to go home to.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He wiped the tears from his eyes before removing the face masks made for him by other prisoners. These are called &quot;hopes&quot; because that is what they need. This is what Irons and Moore have needed for the past 13 years.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I won&#39;t forget it,&quot; he said. &quot;And I will help them as much as I can.&quot;</p>', 'Maya Moore, Successful Campaign', 'Maya Moore_1599688847.png', '2020-09-10 02:00:47', '2021-08-16 16:54:07'),
(340, 7, 4, 50, 'justin-and-corey-williams-the-los-angeles-brothers-create-superstar-cycling-1599689014', 'Justin and Corey Williams: The Los Angeles Brothers \"Create Superstar Cycling\"', 0, '<p><strong>Justin Williams sits on his hard shoulder and is heartbroken on a hot, scorching day in California.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Through the hot haze of hesitation on the Pacific Coast Highway, he watched trucks and cars pass by kicking dust and pressing it down his throat. Leaning on the pile of rubble beside his bicycle, he could barely lift a finger, let alone lift a thumb.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Williams motor in order. He didn&#39;t fall, but neither his brain nor his body were working properly. This will &quot;tie in&quot; - the athlete&#39;s term for endurance when the blood sugar in the body is so low that you can barely think clearly and your feet can no longer pedal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He was frustrated, helpless, and confused.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Finally a car stops and the future US racing champion is saved. From her aunt.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;My dad drove me 70 miles for my first real trip,&quot; explains Williams. &quot;But traveling wasn&#39;t the problem - he didn&#39;t teach me to eat and drink.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;My dad is used to a lot of pain and suffering and he insisted I had to get serious about cycling. The bike is expensive. He told me, &#39;This is not a game and if I want to invest in you you have to be serious. It&#39;s real money.&#39; &quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Williams Kalman&#39;s father is one of the top cyclists in Belize and a competitor to the Pan American Games. His son became the first US champion for black national criteria and road racing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Justin Williams proudly wears Stars and Stripes. But the journey that brought him here was far from an American dream. Instead, the story is marked by years of frustration, poor wages and underinvestment. He quit the sport twice before becoming champion. He&#39;s now part of a self-made team that is looking for a different path and trying to make a difference from within.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Williams describes himself as a patriot. He was voiced on social media after George Floyd&#39;s death in May. He felt there were many things that needed to be changed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A rookie who grew up in southern Los Angeles should watch out for guns, not pits. This is a city where people don&#39;t ride buses, let alone ride bicycles. Here, a long-running love affair with cars means that the 12-lane highway is unlikely to receive temporary treatment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Neither of that held Williams down.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;The best thing about the black community is the feeling of pride when something happens and someone has the opportunity,&quot; he said.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;People understand when someone does something outside of their circumstances. People realize that it is something. I don&#39;t look like a typical motorcyclist.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In 2007 things got serious. Williams turned professional at the age of 17 and joined the Rock Racing criteria team. Over the next five years he gave everything he had on the professional stage. He took her to the Tracks Livestrong development team, to major competitions in the US, Europe and beyond, and gave Williams a young and powerful &quot;culture shock&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;It&#39;s a change that&#39;s too dramatic,&quot; he said. &quot;So I went home and went to college and got a job that made me realize that I never wanted to work for anyone in my life!&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After taking the time to find out who he was, Justin instead helped bring his younger brother Corey into the sport and on a team that recognized the siblings&#39; talent and potential. Together, the pair impressed in a critical professional competition with another team, Silence.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Corey has skills I don&#39;t have,&quot; Justin said. &quot;I wanted to show him that he had support because I was alone. And then our story really started to develop.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Criterion races usually involve a series of rounds in one lap in which the opposing team tries to break free and beat their opponent to the final violent blast. It drew a healthy crowd to cities across the United States. The brothers went on to have one of their most successful years in 2016, winning some of the biggest competitions in the country. Corey won eight straight wins, he and Justin teamed up and finished their move.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Your relationship with your brother is difficult to imitate two boys with the same chemistry,&quot; said Justin. &quot;But the following year people said the team was too much for us. God forbid.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Justin signed a contract for another year, realizing that Corey would be getting a new contract as well.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Corey&#39;s contract bid never worked.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I asked Justin to join the team and then I got fired,&quot; said Corey, still looking incredulous.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>And herein lies the problem for two African-American cyclists. The problem with which black athletes, perhaps unwittingly, prints along the lines of racial prejudice. You face micro attacks which, despite the name, are no less painful.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Justin believes that the individuality of athletes is further thought in the &quot;too European&quot; structure. He believes drivers should not stand up for a team ethic that values compliance and compliance. He and Corey felt like they weren&#39;t one of them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;People in sports don&#39;t want to admit that you have to work ten times harder when you are black,&quot; says Justin.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;There were times that Corey didn&#39;t get the chance he deserved because they didn&#39;t know him and because he didn&#39;t talk to them and smiled. They called him grumpy or mean and he missed opportunities based on that.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I am very sociable, but it is something that grows out of necessity. It is deeper than being an optimist. Being optimistic is part of my survival.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;When you grew up in black America, people looked at you a certain way when you weren&#39;t inviting.&quot; Corey described himself as &quot;more introverted and shy&quot; than his brother.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He added, &quot;People who know me know that I am a good person and that I do a lot for people I know and love. If people want to think that I am somehow because we don&#39;t know each other, they are not worth it. You try to find out. Tofu. &quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dissatisfied, Justin left the sport for the second time. Corey goes on with other teams for an annual salary of often $ 4,500 before sharing the profits with the six-member team. Not just living a dream.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Along with the stars and stripes on Justin&#39;s T-shirt is a shiny lion - an allusion to his Rastafarian origins. It represents a new direction which he himself helps to shape. In 2018, he received $ 18,000 from the Specialized&#39;s Rocket Espresso team. With that money, he financed himself around a European racing chain with a fixed chain, acting as an independent chain. After more than a year, he&#39;s made six-figure wins as he takes the sport and earns it for himself.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Fixed gear racing [where the bike has only one gear and is therefore more difficult to ride] really embodies American culture,&quot; Justin said. I thought, &quot;This is how cycling is supposed to be in America.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I can keep my personal sponsorship, which leads to a better financial situation. And I have the most fun when I&#39;m alone.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Justin wants others in his position to benefit, starting with Corey. &quot;I had the best years I&#39;ve seen in cities like Milan, Barcelona and London, going out with friends, passed out on the floor and enjoying the places I&#39;ve been than just airports, hotels to see. race or get back on the plane. I throw it at his head, &quot;said Justin.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Corey found himself in an outdated professional team structure that didn&#39;t allow people to be innovative. He fell and wasn&#39;t allowed to make a name for himself. It just doesn&#39;t make sense.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;So I thought, &#39;Let&#39;s just give up and do it ourselves.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Los Angeles L39ion started in 2019. A team dedicated to increasing diversity and promoting inclusion.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Justin said: &quot;We made it clear with a gun that it was more than just a cycling team.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;You hear how you grew up to be more than just an athlete from LeBron James - that&#39;s what I imagined when I thought about doing it as an athlete. To be able to improve the lives of others and make someone&#39;s life a positive impact.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;We started looking for people we trusted - and there were a lot of them. Alex Garcia, a child I was driving, had to stop driving to help his mother. He had nowhere to go.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;It&#39;s not just about winning - it&#39;s a combination of everything that makes everything work: accessibility, results, social media, the way we position ourselves. This is how sport grows. You can see yourself in sport, when there are representatives and it will make you want to participate. &quot;&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Legion raised $ 120,000 through mass funding, though that doesn&#39;t even cover all of the driver&#39;s wages for a year&#39;s minimum wage. Then there are car costs, flights, administrative costs. Justin acts as mechanic and manager to keep costs down.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The team must be tough to make changes. Justin and Corey believe they want to create a California-owned sports franchise, but are also determined to expand across the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;For me, I want to build my own sport in America - thousands of fans screaming on tracks in downtown,&quot; Justin said.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Something has to change. If we wait for someone else to change, we&#39;re going to wait forever. I don&#39;t want my career to be frustrated and frustrated because I&#39;m afraid to get out of the box and do something different and new.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This time, they needed more than a father, more than community support - they needed the entire sport to be occupied and cared for.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;It&#39;s all about creating superstars,&quot; said Corey. &quot;And cycling is gone. We want people to fall in love with a hero. A superhero.&quot;</p>', 'Justine, corey williams, los Angeles', 'Justine and core_1599689014.jpg', '2020-09-10 02:03:34', '2021-08-14 01:44:54'),
(341, 7, 4, 92, 'tirreno-adriatico-pascal-ackermann-wins-stage-one-as-chris-froome-and-geraint-thomas-finish-safely-1599689078', 'Tirreno-Adriatico: Pascal Ackermann wins stage one as Chris Froome and Geraint Thomas finish safely', 0, '<p><strong>Chris Froome and Gerent Thomas of England moved safely in the first stage of the Tyrrhenian-Adriatic, which Germany&#39;s Pascal Ackermann won in Italy.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Racer Bora Hansgrohe Ackermann beat Fernando Gaviria of the United Arab Emirates in a series of sprints at Lido di Camaiore. Four-time Tour de France Froome winner and 2018 champion Thomas have been excluded from the Ineos Grenadiers team roster for the ongoing Grand Tour races in France.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The eight-day Tireno-Adriatico served as preparation for the Giro d&#39;Italia. 34-year-old Welshman Thomas is looking for his second win at the Grand Tour des Postponed Giro, which starts on 3 October, while Froome will lead the team at Vuelta a Espana from 20 October.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>British driver Simon Yates of Mitchellton-Scott, whose brother Adam conceded led the entirety of the Tour de France from Sunday to 2019, Tyrone Adriatic Primoz Roglic winner, also finished safely while continuing his own preparations for the Giro.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, at the end of most of the 133 km of terrain several riders were involved in a 1.5 km drop on the main course, as Ackermann won with a perfect timing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On the second stage on Tuesday, the riders will take a 201 km route from Lido di Camaiore to Follonica.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Tirreno-Adriatico stage one result</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Pascal Ackermann (Ger/ Bora-Hansgrohe) 2hrs 57mins 55secs</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Fernando Gaviria Rendon (Col/ UAE Team Emirates) same time</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Magnus Cort Nielsen (Den/ EF Pro Cycling)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. Szymon Sajnok (Pol/ CCC Team)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. Davide Cimolai (Ita/ Israel Start-Up Nation)</p>', 'Tirreno, Pascal Ackermann', 'Tirreno_1599689078.jpg', '2020-09-10 02:04:38', '2021-08-18 07:33:21'),
(342, 7, 4, 102, 'northern-ireland-defeated-by-norway-1599735745', 'Northern Ireland Defeated by Norway', 1, '<p><strong>Northern Ireland suffered a 5-1 defeat in the Norwegian Nations League in coach Ian Barakl&#39;s first home game.From a frenzied start, Paddy McNair replaced Mohamed Elunusi&#39;s opening in the second minute before the visitors took control of Windsor Park.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The impressive Erling Braut Haaland scored two incredible goals, Alexander Sorlot also scored twice. NI drew 1-1 with Romania in the first leg of the race on Friday.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Norway is &quot;clinical and cruel&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>See all the action and reaction from Norway&#39;s awkward win at Windsor Park After the euphoria of Gavin White&#39;s late equalizer, who won a point following the elimination of Josh Magenis in Bucharest, the defeat was a hot pursuit for the team.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The only positive result is captain Stephen Davis, who equaled Pat Jennings&#39; all-time record of 119 games, but the Rangers man will not be eager to celebrate once he and his teammates have advanced.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Three after 19 minutes, thanks to goals from Elyounoussi, Haaland and Sorloth, the result remained unchanged until the break before Haaland and Sorloth scored two more goals shortly after the break to snatch the game from the unlucky hosts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Haaland is too good because the Norwegian is superior to the toothless NI Borussia Dortmund striker Haaland is one of the most talked about perspectives in world football and he shows why with a dominant display against four home defenders, in which Daniel Ballard won only his second cap.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Norway opened the scoring in the second minute when Stefan Johansen&#39;s fierce shot fell to Michael Smith at the far post, allowing the free-tagged Eliunussi to control his chest and take a corner.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The lead was only for the final six minutes when Ballard challenged the search ball over Connor Washington. The striker ran towards him and when his shot was parried by goalkeeper Rune Yarstein, McNair was there to mark the rebound.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The visitors were back ahead a minute later when the tough Haaland ran to KO Sorlot to unleash a superb left-footed shot from outside the penalty area at home.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It was 3-1 in 19 minutes when left-wing Haitam Aleesami was hit with a volley from the far post by Sorloth and he scored four goals two minutes after the break, created by Haaland selflessly who beat Cathcart.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The lad from Dortmund showed his class again and didn&#39;t give Peacock-Farrell a chance by turning his left foot in the top corner.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The house bow couldn&#39;t have been worse for Barraclow</p>\r\n\r\n<p>While the overall performance in Romania was below average, at least the players showed a desire to get a result with a maximum of 10 people.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Playing in an empty Windsor Park will always be difficult for NI, especially given the vocal support they usually get from the crowd, but few thought the team-to-team gap would be as big as it used to be.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As strong and clinical as Norway, NI felt uneasy for most of the game, allowing physical opponents to outsmart their muscles and outperform them in all areas of the pitch.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Baracklow would have been boosted by McNair, who equalized four minutes into Norway&#39;s early opener, but they shut down immediately after the restart to give Halland a chance to deal with his missile.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many defenders will be up against the former RB Salzburg man and while Ballard is bravely doing his job, neither he nor Craig Cathcart have been able to stop the tough striker.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When the fifth goal came in more than half an hour of play it looked the bigger shot, as NI conceded five goals for the first time in an international race after losing to England in 1979.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Despite some positive results for NI, Captain Davis relishes the fact that he hit NI Pat Jennings&#39; record in his 119th international appearance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After his debut in February 2005, he would have had some tougher nights than in Belfast when he was on the captain&#39;s armband for the 67th time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With Jordan Thompson trying to fall deeper to get the ball behind four, Davis, 35, played a little further than the previous game but could not prevent his team from being beaten.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When Davis reached the personal stage, his old partner Johnny Evans disappeared from the list again after not traveling to Romania for personal reasons.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>His club, Leicester City, sent him a lucky note for Monday night&#39;s game, but he did not rejoin. Baracklow said he suffered minor injuries while exercising.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The manager, who is also without Jamal Lewis, will undoubtedly seek to bring veteran Evans back into his squad as Northern Ireland face this most important European qualifier in Bosnia and Herzegovina next month.</p>', 'Northern Ireland, Defeted', 'Norway_1599689556.jpg', '2020-09-10 02:12:36', '2021-08-12 00:06:25'),
(343, 7, 4, 105, 'novak-djokovics-disqualification-from-the-us-open-is-another-example-of-his-misjudgment-1599689641', 'Novak Djokovic\'s disqualification from the US Open is another example of his misjudgment. \"', 0, '<p>Novak Djokovic must have known that the opening of the US Open ended as soon as this tennis ball hit the linesman&#39;s neck.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tim Henman had to be disqualified when he accidentally hit a girl with the ball in the men&#39;s doubles ear at Wimbledon in 1995. and so did David Nalbandian when he kicked a judge in the shin in the 2012 Queen&#39;s Club final.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The rules are clear and should apply equally to the number one player in the world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Djokovic spent seven minutes convincing US Open referee Soeren Freemel about the defense case. But hitting the ball &quot;in a dangerous or reckless manner in court or for neglecting the consequences&quot; - to quote the rules - has no reason to be pardoned.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Indeed, procrastination will have far more serious consequences for sport and will leave the smell of preferential treatment for the rich and influential.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The action was not intended. Djokovic doesn&#39;t see where the loose ball is going, but that&#39;s part of the problem. In recent years, more than a few times, he failed to pay attention to the well-being of others in his quest for obvious success.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the 2016 French Open quarter-final against Tomas Berdych, Djokovic nearly hit the linesman after slipping from his hand after a heavy blow. And later that year, in a match against Dominic Thiem in the ATP final, he fired the ball at his coaching staff, who were seated directly in front of the crowd.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;That&#39;s not a problem for me. I didn&#39;t do it for the first time, &rdquo;Djokovic replied in a cross-examination.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Djokovic is disqualified from the US Open for hitting the referee with the ball</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Sad and empty&quot; Djokovic &quot;is very sorry&quot; for the judge&#39;s injury</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;The right decision was to disqualify Djokovic,&quot; said Henman</p>\r\n\r\n<p>His apology - manifest via Instagram to the linesman and the US Open - would have been much better delivered in person before the flight from New York. He said he &quot;had to take these lessons for my growth and development as a player and as a person&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Djokovic says it a lot, but we hope he does.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A perfect year on the pitch - Djokovic won all 26 of his matches before his unfortunate clash with Pablo Careno Busta - was a far cry from sailing anywhere else.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The 17-time Grand Slam winner is the driving force behind the Adria Tour: a series of show matches in the Serbian capital Belgrade and in the Croatian city of Zadar. Djokovic is one of four players who contracted Covid-19 when social distancing was abandoned - on tennis courts, during friendly football and basketball games, and at nightclubs that host weekend parties.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;We do it with a pure heart and with sincere intentions,&quot; Djokovic said in another apology on Instagram. But it was rated very poorly and did not help tennis&#39;s efforts to return to professional play.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With the formation of the Professional Tennis Players Association, Djokovic also revealed more than just a few feathers. He had considerable support among his peers and had been debated for a long time, but the weather seemed wrong again. The opening meeting takes place on the eve of the US Open at Flushing Meadows, which offers 91% of the usual prize pool while missing out on the income of some 850,000 hungry and thirsty ticket holders.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Only Djokovic can tell whether attention has been focused on the new association and whether public opposition from Rafael Nadal and Roger Federer contributed to Sunday&#39;s event in New York. But he angrily fired the ball at the game billboard before being disqualified. He had just wasted three breakpoints, but instead he did well and didn&#39;t seem to be heading into a stressful afternoon.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The 33-year-old knows he has a golden opportunity to win his 18th Grand Slam this week and his next opportunity - the French Open at Roland Garros - will not be facilitated by the presence of 12-times champion Nadal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But Djokovic has repeatedly overcome difficulties in the past. He will recover; he&#39;ll win again - hopefully a little more humbly.</p>', 'Novak Djokovic, disqualufucation', 'Novak Djokovic_1599689641.jpg', '2020-09-10 02:14:01', '2021-08-16 10:00:54'),
(344, 7, 4, 104, 'leeds-back-in-the-premier-league-gerald-krasner-reminisces-about-the-pain-of-being-relegated-in-2004-1599689795', 'Leeds back in the Premier League: Gerald Krasner reminisces about the pain of being relegated in 2004.', 0, '<p>If Leeds United take on reigning champions Liverpool on Saturday it will be a mobile club with a bright future under Marcelo Bielsa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This is in stark contrast to what they did on 2 May 2004, when the only disobedience came from their supporters when Leeds collapsed in a 4-1 defeat at Bolton and crashed out of the Premier League, as he could not return in 16 sensible years.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Of course, there will be no Anfield supporters because of the coronavirus ban. If the opportunity arises, the distribution of visits can be repeatedly sold.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But even without fans, it&#39;s a weekend&#39;s first class - England&#39;s two biggest clubs meet as before, before one of them collapsed and went from being a Champions League semi-finalist to a championship in exactly three years. .</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;It was the best of its time,&quot; said Gerald Krasner, club president in 2004. Let&#39;s face it, Leeds are the first of many clubs to spend money on success and not.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You see it today - clubs pay ridiculous salaries and transfer fees to get into the golden zone known as the Premier League.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Leeds were at the end of the table when we bought him, but I was the chairman who let him go. It will never be forgotten.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>How Leeds midfielder Phillips won his call-up to England</p>\r\n\r\n<p>10 defining moments for a doctorate under Bielsa</p>\r\n\r\n<p>That summer, Krasner was the public face of efforts to keep Wigan Athletic on hold after the Latics were released by the Hong Kong-based owner.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>16 years ago, Krasner was an accountant who built an impressive reputation as a bankruptcy administrator by advising companies that could not pay their debts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Most importantly he was also a Leeds fan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The financial shift at Elland Road, started under Peter Ridsdale&#39;s leadership, was started by Professor John Mackenzie. At the start of 2004, Leeds were in a state of desperation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;For 30 years in my business life, I have been telling people what they did wrong,&quot; said Krasner.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I thought it was time to show people I could do it. I was never afraid to close the door, so I did the job when no one else wanted.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Krasner assembles a consortium of local business people to save the club. Others, including former Bradford City owner Jeffrey Richmond, were also involved, but Krasner is a public figure.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;It was an interesting experience, especially on Thursday night when the News of the World called you hoping you were drunk to get some news,&quot; said Krasner.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With Bielsa now given the hero status that brought Leeds back to the Premier League, Eddie Gray, the man who beat them remains a legendary figure at the club, and fans believe the Scotsman has been placed in an impossible position. when asked to take over the managerial position in November 2003</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It turned out that Gray, who will be commenting on LUTV at Anfield, won 2-1 over Manchester City in Krasner&#39;s first game as chairman.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But behind the scenes, Krasner was wrestling with some big problems.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Over &pound; 100 million in debt which doesn&#39;t sound like much at the moment - a central striker. That was huge in 2004,&quot; he said.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Trevor Birch runs the club. He knows me professionally because I taught him in the 1990s. He tells me what and for whom to thank. We had to put &pound; 20 million into our attorney&#39;s account. We found him - we pawned my son to the end.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;For six weeks I finished work at 5:00 p.m. and from 6:00 a.m. to 2:00 p.m. we went to the law firm. They had night shifts for me. We had to sign 113 contracts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;People say, &#39;Do you like him?&#39; &quot;I don&#39;t even like him. Don&#39;t buy a soccer club if you&#39;re under stress.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;You sit there and look at an entry gate and you are a million feet ahead, one against you and you are a million pounds less. There are professional companies that do nasty things in the name of money.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I sold the stadium and training ground, but I did it so they both could be bought back. The stadium was already there. We obviously sold a lot of players. A year later the debt was &pound; 24 million which is still ongoing. A lot.&quot; A lot.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;There was so much gunfire. At first, every day when I came home, I thought,&quot; Here&#39;s another one we survived. &quot;In the end it happened week after week, but money was always pressed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;We are making arrangements with everyone to reduce debt. I spoke with Inland Revenue and asked them to give me three years to sort out &pound; 10 million. When we sold the club, we lowered it to 3 million.&quot; Lose weight. I don&#39;t think they think so. &quot;It will take three months.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Krasner was sold to former Chelsea owner Ken Bates in 2005. After their relationship collapsed, he quit the club.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Krasner remains a fan and a source of bitter sadness as Norman Hunter, Jack Charlton and Trevor Cherry, three of Leeds&#39; legendary players - the first two he personally knew - were not present to see their old club revive.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He recognizes his place in the Leeds United journey but knows it is time for others to enjoy the limelight, hopefully with far less stress than he has.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;The problem is you don&#39;t have a football club,&quot; said Krasner. &quot;You may be in law, but really you are just a guardian for the next generation.&quot;</p>', 'Leeds, Premier league', 'Gerald_1599689795.jpg', '2020-09-10 02:16:35', '2021-08-16 11:39:01'),
(345, 7, 4, 103, 'mason-greenwood-the-british-forward-apologized-for-the-breach-of-quarantine-1599689881', 'Mason Greenwood: The British forward apologized for the breach of quarantine', 0, '<p><strong>British striker Mason Greenwood said he was &quot;only guilty&quot; of being rejected by Iceland for violating coronavirus quarantine guidelines.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>18-year-old Greenwood from Manchester United and 20-year-old Manchester City midfielder Phil Foden were forced to leave Gareth Southgate on Monday.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Both players made their debuts in Reykjavik on Saturday with a 1-0 win in the Nations League.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Greenwood said, &quot;I can only apologize for the embarrassment I caused.&quot; He added, &quot;In particular, I want to apologize to Gareth Southgate for disappointing him when he trusted me.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;The match for England was one of the proudest moments of my life and I have to blame him for this big mistake. &quot;I promise my family, the fans, Manchester United and England that I will learn this lesson.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;The British duo give Southgate an unwanted headache&quot; According to reports in Iceland and other media, Foden and Greenwood claim that they met two women in separate parts of the hotel, away from where the British team was staying.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Describing the players as &#39;naive&#39;, Southgate added: &quot;This is a very serious situation and we treat them and act as quickly as possible. &quot;We got it right. I know your age, but the whole world is involved in this pandemic.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In a post on social media on Monday, Foden said England&#39;s next League game against Denmark on Tuesday was &quot;painful&quot; and &quot;will learn valuable lessons from that mistake&quot;. &quot;I made bad decisions and my behavior was not up to the standards I expected,&quot; he wrote.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I apologize to Gareth Southgate, my team-mates in England, the staff, the fans and also the club and my family.&quot; The Football Association has launched a &quot;full investigation&quot; and apologized to the Icelandic Football Association for &quot;taking the right steps&quot;.</p>', 'Mason, British', 'Mason_1599689881.jpg', '2020-09-10 02:18:01', '2021-08-18 01:10:11'),
(346, 7, 4, 119, 'manchester-city-riyad-mahrez-and-aymeric-laporte-tested-positive-for-the-coronavirus-1599735732', 'Manchester City: Riyad Mahrez and Aymeric Laporte tested positive for the coronavirus', 1, '<p><strong>Manchester City winger Riyadh Mahrez and defender Aymeric Laporte have tested positive for Covid-19.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mahrez, 29, from Algeria and Laporte, 24, will not train with his team-mates until they isolate themselves according to English and Premier League regulations. Neither player has shown symptoms of the coronavirus, according to Manchester City.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pep Guardiola&#39;s team player will play Wolverhampton Wanderers in their first game of the new league season on September 21. Both players are in England and with 10 days of self-isolation, Mahrez and Laporte should be available for City&#39;s game with the Wolves in two weeks.</p>', 'Machester city, Riyad Mahrez', 'Manchester city_1599689988.jpg', '2020-09-10 02:19:48', '2021-08-12 00:04:27'),
(347, 7, 4, 85, 'parkrun-will-resume-in-the-uk-at-the-end-of-october-1599690076', 'Parkrun will resume in the UK at the end of October', 0, '<p><strong>The weekly mass parkrun events will resume in the UK at the end of October.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Parkrun events were suspended worldwide in March due to the global coronavirus pandemic. The event will be conducted within the government-approved Covid-19 framework, although the operating model has &quot;slight changes&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Parkron said it was a &quot;turning point for driving change&quot; to create a &quot;healthier and happier planet&quot;. Nick Pearson, CEO of Parkrun, said he was &quot;unable to set a consistent schedule for other national organizations because of other restrictions in Wales, Scotland and Northern Ireland&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;However, we recognize the consequences of opening up only in England and we are continuing our work to overcome the challenges,&quot; he added. The Parkrun Movement was founded in 2002 by Paul Sinton-Hewitt at Bushy Park in London and is now represented in 22 countries.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Runners or climbers can enter the 5K race on Saturday mornings, while the junior 2K races take place on Sunday mornings. The event is free and is run by volunteers. There are 729 different venues in the UK that host weekly events and more than two million runners have participated.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pearson added, &quot;Everything in life is risky and we know and accept that we cannot eliminate all risks from the Parkrun area. However, it is important to take advantage of the public health benefits of continuing our events towards weighing the risks to public health.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;We believe now, having taken the time to gather evidence and understand that the benefits of reopening Parkrun far outweigh the risks.&quot;</p>', 'Parkrun, Resume, October', 'Parkrun_1599690076.png', '2020-09-10 02:21:16', '2021-08-15 14:10:31'),
(348, 4, 5, 48, 'chinese-embassy-calls-for-twitter-inquiry-after-porn-clip-liked-1599733642', 'Chinese embassy calls for Twitter inquiry after porn clip liked', 0, '<p>China&#39;s UK consulate has requested that Twitter &quot;make exhaustive examinations&quot; after its diplomat&#39;s authentic record preferred an obscene clasp.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Liu Xiaoming&#39;s record likewise loved posts that scrutinized the Chinese Communist Party (CCP) and demonstrated blindfolded Uighurs being confined.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Authorities asserted that &quot;hostile to Chinese components [had] violently assaulted&quot; Mr Liu&#39;s record in a &quot;contemptible&quot; plot intended to &quot;hoodwink people in general&quot;.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Twitter presently can&#39;t seem to remark.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The movement initially drew consideration after the record loved a 10-second video posted by a grown-up themed page containing cuts with Chinese-language depictions.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A London-based common liberties campaigner hailed this to other Twitter clients soon after 09:00 GMT with a screen capture as evidence.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The clasp was thusly unliked by whoever was controlling the record.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tweet enjoyed by the ambassadorIMAGE COPYRIGHTTWITTER&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In any case, some different tweets stayed loved for a period before they also were turned around.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>One included cases that authorities had &quot;offered empty talk to non-obstruction&quot; so as to pull off slaughtering individuals from the Chinese open.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A second highlighted drone-caught film of Uighur Muslims being taken to what the post portrayed as a &quot;death camp&quot;.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Beijing has recently prevented holding huge numbers from getting individuals from the ethnic minority in camps without wanting to in the western Xinjiang area.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What&#39;s more, the represetative denied his nation was doing a progr