open&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Furthermore, he has been checking the days since the time they showed up at Moria camp - nine months and five days.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The camp was just expected to house 3,000 transients yet it has been home to more than 13,000. They incorporate individuals from 70 nations, however most are from Afghanistan.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Horrendous injury&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mr Hosseini says his time at Moria has been the &quot;most horrendous experience of his life&quot;. He saw a pregnant lady biting the dust of cut injuries in the camp, just as burglary and robbery.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I couldn&#39;t rest for quite a long time,&quot; he says. &quot;I was apprehensive individuals may get into my tent, slaughter me or assault my family.&quot;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A selfie of Talibshah Hosseini alongside his new greater tent in MoriaIMAGE COPYRIGHTTALIBSHAH HOSSEINI&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>picture captionTalibshah Hosseini and his family just had their greater tent for a month before it was obliterated&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For quite a long time, he lived in a little outdoors tent with his three girls and his significant other, who has kidney issues.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A little more than a month prior, after rehashed demands, they got a greater tent to impart to another family.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;We had recently got our new tent and it is presently worn out,&quot; he says. &quot;On the off chance that we hadn&#39;t got away, it would have taken we all with it.&quot;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The way to Lesbos&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is far based on what was a prosperous life in Afghanistan, regardless of the steady clash there.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mr Hosseini was a main individual from the Faryab National Theater in the north of the nation.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He was additionally a superstar in his old neighborhood, showing up on TV shows as a comedian scrutinizing guerillas just as raising social and policy centered issues.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In 2009, he got hitched and with his significant other, they have three little girls: Farima (9), Parisa (7) and Marjan (4).&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Talibshah Hosseini remaining in the middle following a presentation for rancher&#39;s day in Faryab Province</p>\r\n\r\n<p>picture captionTalibshah Hosseini (standing, focus) was notable in his home territory for his aptitude as a humorist&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>His significant other worked in a salon and life was acceptable until he reprimanded the Taliban and commended the Afghan military in one of his shows.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He began accepting dangers from a nearby mullah and the Taliban.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I love my nation and I wanted to work for the republic and the administration yet they didn&#39;t uphold me when my life was at serious risk,&quot; he says.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He has lost his dad, two siblings and a nephew to the times of brutality in Afghanistan. The time had come to go, the craftsman says.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As the family ventured out through numerous nations to arrive at Europe, his oldest girl Farima got a large group of dialects.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mr Hosseini is glad for his &quot;wise young lady&quot; yet in addition stressed over her. She was in elementary school when they left Afghanistan.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;She continues saying: &#39;Daddy I don&#39;t care for you since you took my school from me, I am distraught.&#39; It&#39;s so hard for a dad to allow his youngster to down,&quot; he says, near tears. &quot;I can&#39;t reveal to you the amount it harms.&quot;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thinking the unbelievable&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is a battle to get by, regardless of endeavors by the Greek specialists to help the destitute.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mr Hosseini saw a van disseminating food on Thursday however such was the interest, the driver was overpowered and left.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Individuals haven&#39;t got anything with them. Around evening time it&#39;s freezing, and they haven&#39;t got anything to cover themselves with,&quot; he says.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;During the day it&#39;s bright and there&#39;s no shade and they&#39;re urgently searching for a bit of paper or material to keep out the sun.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Kids are crying and families are in a tumultuous circumstance. They&#39;re completely startled.&quot;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A flying perspective on obliterated havens following a fire at the Moria camp for outcasts and travelers on the island of&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>picture captionIt is indistinct how the fire began at Moria camp however it pulverized everything in its way&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mr Hosseini says he has suffered such a great amount of enduring on Lesbos that he is puzzling over if escaping Afghanistan was the proper activity.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;There is no water, no food, no latrine and no specialists, I have mental issues and I don&#39;t have the foggiest idea what to do. I am loaded with lament,&quot; he says.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I can&#39;t take any longer. It would be better extraditing us in the event that they won&#39;t give us refuge.&quot;</p>', 'Moria camp', '_114318545_afghanfamilylesbos_1599859784.jpg', '2020-09-12 01:29:45', '2021-08-17 10:40:19');
INSERT INTO `posts` (`id`, `user_id`, `category_id`, `views`, `slug`, `title`, `type`, `description`, `tags`, `image`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(469, 4, 7, 51, 'coronavirus-six-months-after-pandemic-declared-where-are-the-global-hotspots-1599860054', 'Coronavirus: Six months after pandemic declared, where are the global hotspots?', 0, '<p>Covid is proceeding with its spread over the world, with almost 30 million affirmed cases in 188 nations and a loss of life quick moving toward 1,000,000.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A half year after the World Health Organization (WHO) announced it a pandemic, the infection is flooding in numerous nations and some that had evident accomplishment in stifling beginning flare-ups are likewise observing contaminations rise once more.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Nonetheless, the quantity of affirmed cases throughout the spring top is probably going to be a disparage of the genuine degree of contamination, as far and wide testing was not accessible in numerous nations prior in the year.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Where are cases and passings rising?&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Asia is the mainland at present observing the most noteworthy number of every day affirmed cases.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>India presently has the second biggest number of affirmed cases on the planet, behind the US, and is seeing around 90,000 cases for each day right now.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The flood comes as the administration keeps on lifting limitations to attempt to support the economy, but at the same time is an impression of expanded testing - as every day tests have ascended to in excess of a million.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Given the size of its populace, India has a low passing rate from Covid-19. However, almost 1,000 passings have been recorded each day from the nation over since 2 September.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In Latin America, Brazil has the most elevated number of passings, with around 130,000 up until now. It has additionally recorded in excess of 4,000,000 cases, the third most noteworthy on the planet.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Recently affirmed cases in the area are additionally ascending in Argentina, which presently has the greater part a million altogether.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the Middle East, Iran has been gravely influenced by the infection and archives spilled to the BBC Persian help recommend the loss of life there is more than twofold the official complete of around 23,000. Neighboring Iraq has likewise observed a spike in cases.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cases are likewise proceeding to ascend in Indonesia and the nation has recorded about 9,000 passings - the most noteworthy number in South East Asia.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Africa has recorded in excess of a million affirmed cases, despite the fact that the genuine degree of the pandemic in the mainland isn&#39;t known. Testing rates are accounted for to be low, which could mutilate official appraisals, yet South Africa and Egypt have seen the biggest recorded flare-ups there up until this point.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Covid cases rising again in Europe&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A few European nations are recording a rising number of day by day cases in the midst of fears of a resurgence of the infection.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Hans Kluge, the chief general of the WHO&#39;s Europe office, has compared Covid-19 to a &quot;cyclone with a long tail&quot; and cautioned that rising cases among youngsters could spread the sickness to more weak more established individuals.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Various European nations have re-forced nearby lockdowns in their most noticeably awful influenced areas, and there have been restored requests for individuals to wear face covers and adhere to social removing rules.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The example of rising diseases following the finish of lockdown limitations isn&#39;t restricted to Europe.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Different nations that have seen a resurgence of the infection incorporate Peru, Israel, South Korea and Australia.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the table beneath, nations can be reordered by passings, demise rate and all out cases. In the hued bars on the right-hand side, nations in which cases have ascended to more than 5,000 every day are those with dark bars on the significant date.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Covid&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>information in detail&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Parchment table to see more information&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>*Deaths per 100,000 individuals&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Channel:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The world&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Nation&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Passings&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Demise rate*&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Complete Cases&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>New Cases&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>0&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>10&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>100&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1k&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5k&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>**&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>US&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;191,238&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;58.5&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;6,357,902&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>24 JAN&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>10 SEP&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Brazil&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;129,522&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;61.8&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;4,238,446&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>India&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;76,271&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;5.6&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;4,562,414&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mexico&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;69,649&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;55.2&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;652,364&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>UK&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;41,608&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;62.0&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;358,138&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Italy&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;35,587&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;58.7&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;283,180&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>France&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;30,794&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;47.4&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;344,101&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Peru&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;30,344&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;94.9&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;710,067&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Spain&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;29,699&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;63.6&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;554,143&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Iran&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;22,798&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;27.9&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;395,488&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Colombia&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;22,275&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;44.9&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;694,664&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Russia&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;18,207&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;12.5&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;1,042,836&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>South Africa&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;15,265&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;26.4&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;644,438&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Chil