quality on the planet, trailed by San Francisco and Seattle, as per IQAir.com.</p>', 'Oregon wildfires', '_114334401_tv063266987_1599899031.jpg', '2020-09-12 12:23:51', '2021-08-17 22:53:28'),
(473, 4, 12, 59, 'peru-congress-opens-way-for-impeachment-of-president-1599899120', 'Peru Congress opens way for impeachment of president', 0, '<p>Peru&#39;s Congress has begun reprimand procedures against President Mart&iacute;n Vizcarra who is blamed for attempting to hinder a defilement examination.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The move was upheld in a 65-36 vote. Officials are required to banter one week from now whether Mr Vizcarra ought to be eliminated for &quot;moral insufficiency&quot;.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He is blamed for abusing open assets and afterward attempting to cover this up.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mr Vizcarra, matured 57, denies any bad behavior and blames Congress for organizing a political upset.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Peru nation profile&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What&#39;s the situation about?&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Friday&#39;s meeting of Congress was called after the head of Congress, Manuel Merino, was given spilled sound accounts in which Mr Vizcarra seems to talk about methods of concealing the supposed abuse of open assets.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The accounts are of discussions between Mr Vizcarra and government associates.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He is heard advising associates to minimize subtleties of his office&#39;s employing of a mostly secret artist, Richard Cisneros, to convey favorable to government persuasive talks. Cisneros was apparently paid $49,500 (&pound;38,000).&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The restriction blames the administration for squandering assets when customary Peruvians face financial difficulty from the Covid emergency.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Covid: What&#39;s occurring in Peru?&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In excess of 30,000 individuals have passed on of Covid-19 in Peru, which has one of the most elevated demise rates on the planet.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>How has the president reacted?&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>President Vizcarra, who took power in 2018, denies all the charges.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Prior on Friday, he depicted endeavors to eliminate him as &quot;a plot to destabilize his administration&quot;.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In September 2019, Mr Vizcarra broke down Congress, contending that legislators were blocking his enemy of debasement plan.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>No gathering won a general dominant part in the decisions that followed in January.</p>', 'Peru Congress', '_114334417_b8954b57-c1e9-4998-9b25-d5c534b60f55_1599899120.jpg', '2020-09-12 12:25:20', '2021-08-13 04:06:48');
