(477, 4, 7, 33, 'migrants-on-lesbos-europe-does-not-exist-this-is-hell-1599900077', 'Migrants on Lesbos: \'Europe does not exist. This is hell\'', 0, '<p>Scotti Kele was one of the fortunate ones: he had figured out how to locate a corroded old wheelchair in which his four-year-old girl could rest from the bubbling sun.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>That, and an unsanitary babygrow they got in the city, are presently their solitary things, past the garments they&#39;re wearing.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>They lay underneath a shoddy safe house out and about, next to some of 13,000 other people who had spilled out of Moria as Europe&#39;s biggest transient camp caught fire on Tuesday night.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;We are passing on of appetite here, we don&#39;t have anything,&quot; Scotti said.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;At the point when I was in my nation, Congo, and individuals talked about Europe, I thought of common liberties. Be that as it may, from what we see here, I don&#39;t think Europe exists any longer. Take a gander at the conditions our kids are in. This is living damnation.&quot;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Escaping Lesbos fire: &#39;Daddy, would we say we are going to bite the dust?&#39;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>How the transient emergency changed Europe&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The travelers and exiles who had populated Moria are currently dozing any place they can in Lesbos: in strip mall vehicle leaves, underneath the shade of petroleum siphons, even adjacent to graves in the neighborhood graveyard. Some meander erratically shoeless and in sediment recolored T-shirts.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Food and water circulation is scant. There are no latrines whatsoever.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\npicture captionMigrants who fled the blasting camp requested resettlement on Friday&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ringed by revolt police, shields and poisonous gas canisters primed and ready, some composed themselves into a dissent, holding standards perusing &quot;Moria murders&quot; and &quot;Get us out of here&quot;.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>They slammed their unfilled water bottles on the hot landing area in a drumbeat of hopelessness. In any case, the show immediately vanished, alongside their expectation.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The breakdown of Moria into a burned mass of debris and mutilated recollections has incited a new helpful emergency at the edge of Europe. Not exclusively are a great many travelers and displaced people without cover - however when the fire hit, 35 of them had tried positive for Covid and the greater part of those haven&#39;t been found.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Greek government says the blazes were lit by travelers fighting at confinement measures by the camp specialists.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The transients disprove that, demanding it was crafted by far-right Lesbos occupants, for quite a long time angry that their island has been on the forefront of Europe&#39;s relocation emergency.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;They consumed our tent - they state we consumed it, however it&#39;s false,&quot; said Nargis Amini from Afghanistan, as she hauled her couple of things behind her.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;The Greek public don&#39;t need outcasts here. We needed to run into the mountains just to spare our own lives. Furthermore, presently we&#39;re living like creatures in the wilderness - yet we&#39;re not creatures. If you don&#39;t mind help us,&quot; she said.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\npicture captionWater and organic product was disseminated to the individuals who had looked for cover at the Moria camp&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Strain is taking off here, with some neighborhood inhabitants impeding streets to stop good cause conveying help to the travelers.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What&#39;s more, it looks set to increment as the administration declares plans to remake shut gathering communities in Lesbos - more secure and greater, it demands.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>That is little comfort for shelter searchers stuck here and for a nation known for its cordiali