(536, 4, 14, 210, 'coronavirus-court-plan-will-not-ease-delays-lawyers-warn-1599915717', 'Coronavirus: Court plan will not ease delays, lawyers warn', 0, '<p>A huge number of individuals may hang tight until 2022 for equity in spite of an administration declaration to accelerate work in the Crown Courts, attorneys caution.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pastors disclosed measures - remembering holding suspects for longer for England and Wales - trying to oversee pressure on courts in the midst of the pandemic.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In any case, pundits state delays in criminal courts are completely of the administration&#39;s making and pre-date Covid.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In excess of 9,000 preliminaries have been returned since the UK went into lockdown.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What forces do the police have during the pandemic?&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Areas of the &#39;Songbird courts&#39; in England and Wales uncovered&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Priest cautions over legal dispute excess from infection&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On Sunday, the Ministry of Justice reported that it needs Parliament to pass impermanent enactment to expand the time that litigants can be held in authority in England and Wales while anticipating preliminary.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The law is one of the most significant wheels of the criminal equity machine since it guarantees that equity is as quick as workable for the two suspects and casualties.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At present, respondents must be held for 182 days after their first appearance in court, before there must be an application to an adjudicator to keep them inside for more.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Under the administration&#39;s proposition, from the finish of this current month that will be two months longer.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Practically speaking, this choice incorporates additional time with the court framework - and it is important for a bundle of measures to deal with the effect of Covid on the courts.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Picture copyrightGETTY IMAGES&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Picture inscription&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Ministry of Justice&#39;s primary workplaces in Westminster will house a brief court to facilitate the build-up&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Judges and court supervisors are battling to discover enough space to securely deal with the social separating of many individuals who might regularly come into their structures each day.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Yet, criminal attorneys state that the administration&#39;s case is pretentious. They express the deferrals to equity are of the administration&#39;s own making, not as a result of Covid.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>They blame pastors for taking a political choice to present yet more deferral - which could prompt cases crumbling if witnesses pull back participation - as opposed to finding the money to get more courts operational.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As indicated by authentic figures, in excess of 37,000 Crown Court cases were remarkable before the pandemic struck the UK.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Criminal Bar Association (CBA), which speaks to counselors who indict and shield the nation over, says the overabundance is currently 43,000.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lately, the quantity of courts in normal use has fallen as a component of slices to the courts spending plan - and as the quantity of sitting days has fallen, the accumulation of cases has developed.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&#39;Emergency they made&#39;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>James Mulholland QC, administrator of the CBA, said that the postponements to equity were harming to suspects, casualties and witnesses.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;You don&#39;t resolve the deferrals by fusing further postponements into the framework,&quot; he said. &quot;The individuals you rebuff unreasonably by this system are not just those wrongly blamed for wrongdoing, on the grounds that not every person in guardianship is blameworthy - but rather the observers who should stand by considerably longer to be heard.&quot;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;The excess could have disappeared if the legislature had permitted judges to sit. At that point along comes Covid, and the emergency that they&#39;ve made, they can&#39;t appropriately address.&quot;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Equity Secretary Robert Buckland said the administration&#39;s more extensive bundle of measures will get the criminal courts framework &quot;back to where it should be&quot;.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;This transitory expansion to guardianship time cutoff points will keep casualties and the open safe, and we ought not apologize for making that our need,&quot; he said.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Simultaneously, the measures I have reported today will get the criminal courts framework back to where it should be - lessening delays and conveying speedier equity for all.&quot;</p>', 'Court plan', '_114265201_gettyimages-503657848_1599915717.jpg', '2020-09-12 17:01:57', '2021-12-19 17:39:42'),
(537, 4, 14, 146, 'stalker-victim-feels-let-down-by-the-law-1599915835', 'Stalker victim feels \'let down\' by the law', 0, '<p>Ian Hutchinson will consistently fear what could have been the dismal results had he gotten back after working all day on time on a November night in 2019.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Hanging tight for him was 42-year-old Thomas Baddeley who had been furtively following the Chepstow dental specialist for a long time.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At the point when he was captured near Mr Hutchinson&#39;s home, Baddeley was outfitted with what investigators called a &quot;murder unit&quot; that incorporated a crossbow, enormous blade, ski veil, dye and a mallet when he was captured near&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mr Hutchinson said he feels &quot;let somewhere near the law&quot; in the wake of learning his stalker will be delivered from jail inside weeks.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Baddeley got an uncertain limiting request however confronted a lesser accusation since his casualty was uninformed he had been followed</p>', 'Stalker victim', 'download (4)_1599915835.jpg', '2020-09-12 17:03:55', '2021-12-19 17:39:28'),
(538, 7, 1, 164, 'scheduled-dc-parenting-staff-get-together-as-the-abortion-team-tackles-diversity-issues-1599916021', 'Scheduled DC parenting staff get together as the abortion team tackles diversity issues', 0, '<p>Employees at the National Planned Parenting Office in Washington, DC, said they had partnered with management to improve worker rights. The shift to collective bargaining occurs as parenting candidates and other abortion stakeholders are investigated about problems in the workplace, including a lack of diversity in governance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Union management told CBS News that about 70 DC employees who were eligible for their parent&#39;s plan had unanimously voted for the SEIU Local 500, the local branch of the second-largest union in the United States. , structure benefits and give members a voice in organizational decisions. &quot;&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The deal between the Planned Parenthood Federation of America and its UK employees comes after nearly four years of negotiations that began with former President Cecil Richards, union leaders told CBS News. Following the announcement of their intention to reunite in September 2016, negotiations were halted following the election of President Trump as Planned Parenthood defended itself against an unprecedented wave of abortion restrictions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The organization&#39;s DC offices are gathering &quot;to ensure long-term safety as planned parenthood and to build a collective strength for workers that will enable the organization to successfully fulfill its mission,&quot; said Aaron Wilder, a member of the contract unit management team. and regional campaign manager at Planned Parenthood.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;We are contractors: employees who come to work every day to work tirelessly for patients with planned reproductive and custody rights,&quot; Wilder said in an email to CBS News.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;The PPFA National Office fully believes in and supports the right of employees to organize and unite the DC and Miami unions,&quot; Planned Parenthood spokeswoman Melanie Newman told CBS News.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The reunification measures were organized after allegations of a poor work environment and unfair treatment of black employees at some of the country&#39;s most prominent reproductive health organizations, including planned caregivers. NARAL, an abortion advocacy group, was accused last month of not accepting enough blacks for leadership positions, including the board of directors. In planned caregivers in Greater New York, the group&#39;s largest subsidiary, allegations of violence and racial discrimination led to the dismissal of their CEO.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;The things that have been highlighted in some of our chapters are, well, the national bureau is not immune,&quot; said a Planned Parenthood official and union administrator who asked not to be named. &quot;White supremacy is growing badly everywhere, even in developed and charitable areas.&quot;</p>', 'DC parenting, Diversity issues', 'Planned parenthood_1599916021.jpg', '2020-09-12 17:07:01', '2021-09-23 08:14:41'),
(539, 4, 11, 163, 'oscar-winners-2020-see-the-full-list-1599916052', 'OSCAR WINNERS 2020: SEE THE FULL LIST', 0, '<p>The&nbsp;<a href=\"https://oscar.go.com/\"><strong>Oscars 2020</strong></a>&nbsp;are in the books! The show aired tonight on ABC, and now we all know which&nbsp;<a href=\"https://oscar.go.com/nominees\"><strong>Oscars 2020 nominees</strong></a>&nbsp;took home the most coveted prize in film, the Oscar&reg;. The moment was captured live here on&nbsp;<a href=\"https://oscar.go.com/\"><strong>Oscar.com</strong></a>&nbsp;as we updated the full list of Oscars 2020 winners all night long as they were revealed both here and on the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://oscar.go.com/winners\"><strong>Oscars Winners page</strong></a>. If you&#39;re looking to get your Oscars fix you can find full coverage of the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://oscar.go.com/red-carpet\"><strong>Oscars 2020 red carpet</strong></a>, highlights from the ceremony, acceptance speeches, and even step backstage for the Thank You Cam and press room coverage. It all started TONIGHT with&nbsp;<em>Oscars Live on the Red Carpet</em>&nbsp;6:30e|3:30p live on ABC.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h1><strong>OSCAR NOMINATIONS 2020 BY CATEGORY - 92ND AWARDS</strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><a href=\"http://oscar.go.com/nominees/actor-in-a-leading-role\"><strong>Performance by an actor in a leading role&nbsp;nominees:</strong></a></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Antonio Banderas in PAIN AND GLORY</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Leonardo DiCaprio in ONCE UPON A TIME...IN HOLLYWOOD</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Adam Driver in MARRIAGE STORY</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://oscar.go.com/news/2020/joaquin-phoenix-wins-2020-oscar-for-actor-in-a-leading-role-in-joker\"><em><strong>Joaquin Phoenix in JOKER - WINNER</strong></em></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Jonathan Pryce in THE TWO POPES</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><a href=\"http://oscar.go.com/nominees/actor-in-a-supporting-role\"><strong>Performance by an actor in a supporting role nominees:</strong></a></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tom Hanks in A BEAUTIFUL DAY IN THE NEIGHBORHOOD</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Anthony Hopkins in THE TWO POPES</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Al Pacino in THE IRISHMAN</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Joe Pesci in THE IRISHMAN</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://oscar.go.com/news/2020/brad-pitt-is-the-2020-oscar-winner-for-actor-in-a-supporting-role\"><strong><em>Brad Pitt in ONCE UPON A TIME...IN HOLLYWOOD</em></strong><em>&nbsp;<strong>- WINNER</strong></em></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><a href=\"http://oscar.go.com/nominees/actress-in-a-leading-role\"><strong>Performance by an actress in a leading role nominees:</strong></a></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cynthia Erivo in HARRIET</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Scarlett Johansson in MARRIAGE STORY</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Saoirse Ronan in LITTLE WOMEN</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Charlize Theron in BOMBSHELL</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://oscar.go.com/news/2020/rene-zellweger-wins-2020-oscar-for-actress-in-a-leading-role-in-judy\"><em><strong>Ren&eacute;e Zellweger</strong>&nbsp;<strong>in JUDY - WINNER</strong></em></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><a href=\"http://oscar.go.com/nominees/actress-in-a-supporting-role\"><strong>Performance by an actress in a supporting role nominees:</strong></a></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kathy Bates in RICHARD JEWELL</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://oscar.go.com/news/2020/laura-dern-is-the-2020-oscar-winner-for-actress-in-a-supporting-role\"><em><strong>Laura Dern in MARRIAGE STORY - WINNER</strong></em></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Scarlett Johansson in JOJO RABBIT</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Florence Pugh in LITTLE WOMEN</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Margot Robbie in BOMBSHELL</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><a href=\"http://oscar.go.com/nominees/animated-feature-film\"><strong>Best animated feature film of t