(693, 6, 7, 151, 'tokyo-stocks-advance-in-morning-as-trump-leaves-treatment-clinic-1601986253', 'Tokyo stocks advance in morning as Trump leaves Treatmentclinic', 0, '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tokyo stocks progressed Tuesday morning as U.S. President Donald Trump being released from emergency clinic and getting back to the White House in the wake of accepting treatment for COVID-19 decreased concerns fairly about the effect on the legislature.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average included 113.77 focuses, or 0.49 percent, from Monday to 23,425.91.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The more extensive Topix list of all First Section issues on the Tokyo Stock Exchange, in the interim, increased 5.29 focuses, or 0.32 percent, at 1,642.54.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Protection, elastic item and oil and coal issues involved those that best in class the most by the morning break.</p>', 'japan stock exchange, japan today, japan currency, japan news, japan products, usa and japan, japan trump, japan due trump, trump corona update, covid-19, jaan covid, usa today, trump vs biden', 'tokyo_1601986252.jpg', '2020-10-06 16:10:53', '2021-12-19 17:30:17'),
(694, 6, 7, 307, '3-deaths-and-1-harmed-in-houston-building-breakdown-in-usa-1601986799', '3 Deaths and 1 harmed in Houston building breakdown in USA', 0, '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A flight of stairs breakdown in the southern U.S. city of Houston left three individuals dead and another harmed on Monday, neighborhood authorities said.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Nearby media detailed that the building site where the breakdown happened is situated in west Houston. As indicated by the Houston Fire Department (HFD), the breakdown started in the structure&#39;s flight of stairs close to the thirteenth and fourteenth floor, and the flight of stairs fell right to the main floor.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>HFP affirmed the fatalities because of the breakdown and that the harmed specialist was moved to a close by medical clinic and stayed in stable condition.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>HFD Assistant Chief Ruy Lozano said there were 240 development laborers on the site at the hour of the breakdown.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Firemen and specialists are on the scene. Lozano said the structure was precarious for them to burrow inside and that architects are assessing when it&#39;ll be sheltered to start recouping the three perished casualties.</p>', 'houstan usa, houstan incident, usa today, houstan building, building collapse, houstan texan, bbc news, trump today, trump update, canada news', 'k_1601986799.jpg', '2020-10-06 16:19:59', '2021-12-19 17:30:05'),
(695, 6, 7, 244, 'india-south-africa-approach-wto-to-ease-ip-rules-for-covid-19-1601987216', 'India, South Africa approach WTO to ease IP rules for COVID-19', 1, '<p>South Africa and India have asked the World Trade Organization to forgo a few arrangements in the peaceful accords that control protected innovation rights, to accelerate endeavors to forestall, treat and contain the COVID-19 pandemic and ensure creating nations are not deserted.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The nations contend, in a joint accommodation to the Council for Trade-Related Aspects of Intellectual Property Rights dated Friday, that without a fast waiver of some current protections for licensed innovation rights, a few nations &ndash; especially creating ones that have been &quot;excessively affected&quot; &ndash; would think that its difficult to get to antibodies or prescriptions rapidly.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Activists have cautioned that a COVID-19 antibody could be accumulated by rich nations in a competition to immunize their populaces first. A few nations including Britain, France, Germany and the U.S. have requested a huge number of dosages of potential immunizations even before clinical preliminaries have indicated they are powerful.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Less fortunate nations, whose economies have been broken by the pandemic, are not in a situation to put down such wagers. With the world outperforming 1,000,000 affirmed COVID-19 passings, the desperation has developed.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>South Africa and India are looking for waivers to decides that identify with copyright, modern plans, licenses and the assurance of undisclosed data or proprietary advantages, and they recommend that the waiver be set up &quot;until boundless inoculation is set up internationally&quot; and a large portion of the world has created invulnerability to the Covid.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The nations state there are &quot;noteworthy worries&quot; about whether new medicines and immunizations being created for COVID-19 would be made accessible immediately and reasonably to fulfill the worldwide need.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The letter says the current adaptabilities composed into the principles probably won&#39;t be sufficient, and could bring about legitimate troubles for creating countries. Nations with a restricted ability to make drugs are especially helpless, and this could make the way toward bringing in and trading prescriptions &quot;awkward and protracted,&quot; it says.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Universally, there is an earnest call for worldwide solidarity, and the unhindered worldwide sharing of innovation and skill all together that fast reactions for the treatment of COVID-19 can be set up on an ongoing premise,&quot; the letter says. It asks that the chamber critically approach the WTO&#39;s significant level dynamic body, the General Council.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Medication organizations have said they have to ensure their protected innovation to support their costly examination. Then, the World Health Organization has upheld a COVID-19 innovation access pool where IP and information can be shared willfully.</p>', 'india and africa, india news, india today, india corona update, coivid india, usa today, trump corona update, modi in india, modi news, india breaking', 'd_1601987216.jpg', '2020-10-06 16:26:56', '2021-12-19 17:24:35'),
(696, 6, 11, 285, 'the-university-of-alberta-specialist-granted-nobel-prize-in-medication-for-hepatitis-c-disclosure-1601988551', 'The University of Alberta specialist granted Nobel Prize in medication for hepatitis C disclosure', 1, '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Briton Michael Houghton, who has worked in Alberta for about 10 years, won the prize close by 2 Americans&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>English researcher Michael Houghton, who works at the University of Alberta, and Americans Harvey J. Adjust and Charles M. Rice were granted the Nobel Prize in Medicine on Monday for the disclosure of the hepatitis C infection.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Reporting the prize in Stockholm, the Nobel Committee noticed that the men&#39;s work distinguished a significant wellspring of blood-borne hepatitis that couldn&#39;t be clarified by the recently found hepatitis An and B infections. Their work, going back to the 1970s and 1980s, has helped spare a large number of lives, it said.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Because of their disclosure, exceptionally delicate blood tests for the infection are presently accessible and these have basically dispensed with post-bonding hepatitis in numerous pieces of the world, extraordinarily improving worldwide wellbeing,&quot; the advisory group said.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Their disclosure likewise permitted the fast improvement of antiviral medications coordinated at hepatitis C. Without precedent for history, the sickness would now be able to be relieved, raising any expectations of killing hepatitis C infection from the total populace.&quot;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Houghton is overseer of the University of Alberta&#39;s Li Ka Shing Applied Virology Institute.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Michael Houghton&#39;s accomplishment couldn&#39;t be more important,&quot; said University of Alberta president Bill Flanagan. &quot;Dr. Houghton has improved this world a spot. As leader of the University of Alberta, the foundation where he has devoted his time, I am pleased and thrilled that his work has been perceived thusly.&quot;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The college said Houghton is the principal researcher at a Canadian college to win a Nobel in similar order in 97 years.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Frederick Banting and John Macleod, at the University of Toronto, won the Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine in 1923.</p>', 'university of alberta, nobel price, oscar award, oscar 2020, medication award, usa today, trump corona update, trump covid, nobel medications, university of usa', 'k_1601988551.jpg', '2020-10-06 16:49:11', '2021-12-19 17:24:23'),
(697, 6, 1, 125, 'trumps-dr-says-president-no-more-a-transmission-hazard-1602447418', 'Trump\'s Dr. says president \"no more\" a transmission hazard.', 0, '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>U.S. President Donald Trump, who tried positive for COVID-19 on Oct. 1, is &quot;not, at this point considered a transmission danger to other people,&quot; his PCP said on Saturday as the president arranged to continue crusade rallies.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In another notice on the president&#39;s status, White House doctor Sean Conley composed that he made the appraisal following a COVID PCR test toward the beginning of today by &quot;at present perceived norms,&quot; yet didn&#39;t uncover when Trump last had a negative test outcome.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Presently at day 10 from manifestation beginning, sans fever for well more than 24 hours and all side effects improved, the combination of cutting edge analytic tests got uncovered there is no longer proof of effectively duplicating infection,&quot; Conley said of the president, promising to keep on checking the president clinically &quot;as he re-visitations of a functioning timetable.&quot;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The 74-year-old tried positive for the infection on Oct. 1 and was later hospitalized for three days before getting back to the White House with proceeded with treatment.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the wake of Trump&#39;s contamination, various White House staff have additionally affirmed positive for the infection.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Top U.S. master Anthony Fauci on Friday distinguished a White House service revealing president&#39;s Supreme Court chosen one on Sept. 26, as &quot;a super-spreader occasion&quot; for COVID-19.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Subsequent to finishing a treatment and being medicinally cleared by Conley, Trump disclosed his first appearance since disease at the White House on Saturday evening by tending to many allies from the Truman Balcony.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I&#39;m feeling extraordinary,&quot; the president stated, while pronouncing COVID-19 is &quot;vanishing&quot; in the Untied States in spite of that many states are announcing rising quantities of cases.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Over the previous week, there have been a normal of 47,782 cases for every day in the United States, an expansion of 12 percent from the normal fourteen days prior, as indicated by a count by The New York Times.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The infection has contaminated more than 7.7 million individuals and executed 214,370 in the nation, demonstrated a dashboard run by Johns Hopkins University.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Trump will hit the official battle field on Monday with an assembly in Sanford, Florida.</p>', 'trump corona, trump corona update, election 2020, usa today, usa daily, newyork stock exchange, trump vs biden, biden news, obama usa', 'f_1602445992.jpeg', '2020-10-11 23:53:13', '2021-12-19 17:29:41'),
(698, 6, 12, 115, 'united-nations-head-invites-nagorno-karabakh-truce-understanding-1602447394', 'United nations head invites Nagorno-Karabakh truce understanding.', 0, '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A man shows slug and shell openings on a house harmed during the new round of Nagorno-Karabakh struggle among Azerbaijan and Armenia in Fuzuli area of Azerbaijan, Sept. 30, 2020.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Under the truce understanding, the particular boundaries of which will be conceded to also, Armenia and Azerbaijan will trade detainees, other kept people, and groups of the dead under the intercession of the International Committee of the Red Cross.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Joined NATIONS, Oct. 10 . UN Secretary-General Antonio Guterres on Saturday invited the concurrence on a compassionate truce in Nagorno-Karabakh declared on Friday by the unfamiliar pastors of Russia, Azerbaijan and Armenia, said his representative.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Guterres required the truce to be regarded and for a quick concession to the particular boundaries of the truce system, said Stephane Dujarric, the representative, in an announcement.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The secretary-general praised Russia for its intervention endeavors, and invited the duties by Armenia and Azerbaijan to starting considerable dealings under the protection of the Organization for Security and Co-activity in Europe (OSCE) Minsk Group Co-Chairs - delegates from France, Russia and the United States.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Guterres spoke to the worldwide network to help the truce understanding and keep on urging the gatherings to determine their disparities through serene methods, said the announcement.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Under the truce understanding, the particular boundaries of which will be conceded to also, Armenia and Azerbaijan will trade detainees, other kept people, and assortments of the dead under the intervention of the International Committee of the Red Cross.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The two nations consented to start considerable exchanges for a serene settlement at the earliest opportunity under the intercession of the OSCE Minsk Group Co-Chairs.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Armenia and Azerbaijan have been at loggerheads over the bumpy locale of Nagorno-Karabakh since 1988. Harmony talks have been held since 1994 when a truce was reached, yet there have been inconsistent minor conflicts.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Another round of equipped clash broke out along the contact line on Sept. 27. The conflicts have purportedly caused substantial losses.</p>', 'uno, united nation, uno head, uno about kashmir, usa today, usa daily, trump vs biden, trump corona update, election last date, eusa today, electon 2020', 'us_1602446466.jpg', '2020-10-12 00:01:06', '2021-12-19 17:27:10'),
(699, 6, 10, 196, 'commission-postponed-second-trump-biden-battle-1602447434', 'Commission postponed second Trump-Biden battle.', 1, '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The second discussion between U.S. President Donald Trump and 2020 Democratic official chosen one Joe Biden won&#39;t occur, the Commission on Presidential Debates (CPD) declared on Friday.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The choice came after the board moved to hold the subsequent go head to head, booked for Oct. 15 in Miami, Florida, basically, for the wellbeing and security of all included.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;In this way, the missions of the two up-and-comers who qualified for interest in the discussion made a progression of articulations concerning their individual positions with respect to their ability to partake in a virtual discussion on October 15, and every currently has reported substitute designs for that date,&quot; the CPD said in an announcement. &quot;It is presently obvious there will be no discussion on October 15.&quot;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The neutral commission said it will direct its concentration toward arrangements for the last Trump-Biden experience planned for Oct. 22 at Belmont University in Nashville, Tennessee, which the two applicants have consented to participate in.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Nashville discussion will be isolated into six 15-minute portions, the subjects of which will be chosen and reported by arbitrator and NBC News journalist Kristen Welker at any rate multi week before the occasion, as per the announcement.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Trump, who&#39;s recouping from COVID-19 disease at the White House, has clarified that he won&#39;t have a virtual discussion with Biden. His mission on Friday called the CPD &quot;one-sided,&quot; blaming it for &quot;shielding Biden and keeping electors from getting with the two possibility for president.&quot;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The previous U.S. VP had consented to a virtual arrangement yet later decided to go to a municipal center in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania that night rather in the wake of his Republican opponent&#39;s resistance to the change.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In an announcement, a Biden crusade representative said it&#39;s &quot;disgraceful&quot; that Trump dodged the main discussion appearing as a town meeting, in which the citizens will pose the inquiries.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The rivals met for their first discussion in the 2020 race in Cleveland, Ohio, on Sept. 29, two days before the occupant was determined to have COVID-19.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Biden has gone through various tests since Trump freely affirmed he had gotten the malady, with every one bringing negative back.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Trump has finished his treatment, as per his doctor, who has additionally therapeutically cleared the president for public occasions from Saturday. In any case, the White House has consistently would not reveal when he last had a negative test outcome.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Republican, who is following Biden in public surveys, is apparently booked to hold an in-person occasion at the White House on Saturday. His re-appointment crusade reported on Friday that he will go to a meeting in Sanford, Florida on Monday.</p>', 'trump corona update, trump covid, covid-19, usa today, usa daily, trump news, usa news, breaking news, us election, us politics, election date, biden vs trump', 'tr_1602446865.jpeg', '2020-10-12 00:07:46', '2021-12-19 17:24:11'),
(700, 6, 17, 183, 'flooding-covid-sees-1272-million-russians-contracting-infection-1602447670', 'Flooding Covid sees 1.272 million Russians contracting infection.', 1, '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Russia has enrolled 12,126 COVID-19 cases in the previous 24 hours, and this new single-day record increment (up from 11,493 on Thursday) brings the combined case absolute to 1,272,238, the public Covid reaction focus said on Friday.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The nation broke the past record of 11,656 COVID-19 cases investigated May 11.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;In the previous 24 hours, Russia has affirmed 12,126 COVID-19 cases in 85 locales, of which 3,272 (27 percent) were distinguished effectively, with individuals demonstrating no clinical manifestations,&quot; the reaction community said in an announcement, determining that the complete tally has arrived at 1,272,238.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The biggest increment was distinguished in Moscow, where 3,701 new certain tests were enrolled (up from 3,323 yesterday). A sum of 469 new cases were recorded in St. Petersburg (up from 461 yesterday) and 411 cases were affirmed in the Moscow locale (down from 433 yesterday).&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The reaction community announced 201 new Covid related fatalities, up from 191 yesterday, raising Russia&#39;s complete loss of life to 22,257.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Upwards of 7,092 Covid patients were affirmed to have recouped throughout the most recent day, up from 7,054 yesterday, carrying the absolute number of releases to 1,009,421.</p>', 'russia corona, india covid, italy covid, corona update, russia today, russia news, usa today, trump corona update, covid-19, usa politics', 'cor_1602447670.jpg', '2020-10-12 00:21:10', '2021-12-19 17:24:00'),
(701, 6, 15, 223, 'us-vp-pences-head-of-staff-tests-positive-for-covid-19-1603628901', 'U.S. VP Pence\'s head of staff tests positive for COVID-19', 0, '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>U.S. VP Mike Pence&#39;s head of staff tried positive for the Covid on Saturday, as indicated by the VP&#39;s press secretary.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Today, Marc Short, Chief of Staff to the Vice President, tried positive for COVID-19, started isolate and aiding the contact following cycle,&quot; Devin O&#39;Malley, the press secretary, said in an announcement. &quot;VP Pence and Mrs. Pence both tried negative for COVID-19 today, and stay healthy.&quot;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;While Vice President Pence is viewed as a nearby contact with Mr. Short, in meeting with the White House Medical Unit, the Vice President will keep up his timetable as per the (Centers for Disease Control and Prevention) rules for fundamental faculty,&quot; O&#39;Malley said.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Short has voyaged widely with Pence, who has kept up a bustling effort plan.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Likewise, Bloomberg News announced prior Saturday that one of Pence&#39;s nearest political counsels, Marty Obst, gotten the infection Wednesday. In spite of the fact that not an administration worker, Obst has every now and again been in contact with the VP, the outlet stated, including that he has not been in nearness with Pence since about seven days back.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On Saturday night, Pence conveyed a mission discourse in Tallahassee, Florida, during an excursion wherein Short didn&#39;t go with him. Short was with the VP Thursday for a meeting in Indiana.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pence has kept a forceful itinerary as of late, crusading eagerly for the Trump-Pence ticket as the Nov. 3 Election Day draws near. He is required to head out to North Carolina, Pennsylvania and Minnesota and different states in the coming days.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The VP&#39;s representative, Katie Miller, was determined to have COVID-19 in Ma